Item_Response: I, Peter Fan, is a trainer. Every morning I wake up at 7:30 get dressed and then go to the food car. Today we are having a show so the crew is setting up the tents and lights.   At 9:00 I go to school. This school is normal it has computers, tests, homework, and report cards. The circus performers in the circus come from many places and speak French, Russian, Chinese, and Italian. When we learn our geography lessons sometimes we get to see the real deal.       3:30 school is over we practice our routine for the show. I am training elephants to blance on a beam. We first try and do it on lower ground. The elephants are sucssesful. Yay, I , the trainer is proud to be with the elephants. At:6:30 we eat in the food car. After a light dinner we get ready for our show in the afternoon.       9:00 the show is over I was so nervous I almost forgot my part. Now I'm pooped. I go to bed at 11:00. I also think of my home in California wondering if we will be able to stop performing and go back and live a peaceful live at home.

Item_Response: Even before I fell of the tightrope, I was having a sucky day. When I woke up at 7:00 I was on the ground, my blankets thrown all around me and I had a hurting back. By the time I had got my trailer and myself tidy I was 20 minutes late for breakfast. Then when  went to the pie car to grab sommrthing to eat, I discovered that everyone else had finished all the food, so I had to drink only cofee.        Then when I was waking to our one room schoolhouse, I tripped on a bannnana peel and spilled cofee all over myself. When I went to study in the calssromm, everyone started laughing at me, as I was known for my flexibility and balance. Embarresed, I took a towl from the back and dryed myself off.       When I was  playing with my friend's juggling balls they all veered off course and fell on my head. In a fit of anger, I rushed off and slammed the door of my trailer. Then someone tried to pull a prank on me by putting a bucket full of water on my door. Me slamming the door had caused it to fall down and spill on my bed. I was so angry that I did not do anyone of my chores.        Then for the finalle of bad things that day, when I was walking on the tightrope with everyone waching me, i fell off!!!       It was truly a very bad, no good, stinking day.

Item_Response: There is a lot going on in the circus. We do different kinds of tricks and many shows.       At our circus, some of our many performences include acrobatics and tighgtrope walking. We also work with many animals such as horses, leopards, elephants, lions, and chimpanzees.       Performing is very fun. If you put your mind to it anything is possible. I started performing when I was 11. Then, I wasn't even close to being perfect but I practiced and practiced. Now instead of only seeing the performences I can do them better than ever.       Our circus does ten shows a week. Two on Wednesday, Saturday, and Sunday and one on the rest of the days.       The circus is always a big job. There is almost no time to sit down and relax. When I come back from school I only have a short break before I have to go back to chores and then practice.       The circus is a big job and there is a lot going on. There are many animals, tricks, performers which means a lot of practice so it leaves almost no time to relax. No matter what, being in the circus is something you won't regret. You will love everything you do.

Item_Response: Everone thinks a circus is crazy but it really is'nt .It's really fun ,funny ,and hard to do you            have to work all day and we move 20,000 miles ever seven months.                         Here's  a typical day for me:                           At 7:00A.M. I wake up get dressed and then I go to the pie car for eggs and bacon then we           are crews help set up the tent and lights and music.                          At 9:00A.M. I have to go to school .I go to are school house and learn ,test ,and do language.           my famly teaches me Franch ,Russian ,and Italian.                            3:00P.M. school is over i ask the clowns if I can play with some of crops and I play with are dog             Noodles I sometimes want to play base ball but we dont have time to do sports.                          At 6:30P.M. its dinner and we go to the pie car to eat we eat a littel then becaues we have are preformances.             We have have shows ever 10 days a week.                                         At 12:00A.M. the show is over and im wiped we do are hardes. We go to are trailers and sleep for tommarow            and maybe tommarow we can go to a new town.

Item_Response: Javier the great                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                     Javier was born on October  25,1982. But he always did his best at everything he tried.                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                The End.

Item_Response: The Fun of the Circus       By Adelyn Chen       Lola was trying to act nonchalant as she walked out. She couldn't fall on the tightrope, nor fall on the bars triple somersault. Even though that was a burden, Lola LOVED being in the circus. She loved rhythmic gymnastics, playing with animals, and even just training them. It was so fun watching too!       The first part of the show came. Lola jumped and did a triple somersault and grabbed onto Harry's ankles, swinging back and forth, then jumped onto the platform on the other side. The circus was fun! She bowed and curtsied as the audience cheered. Then she went offstage to find the elephant trainer. The elephant trainer's cue was when Lola walked over to her. Lola sauntered because there was about two minutes until the elephants actually had to perform. The main elephant could do a trunk-stand!       Even though it was really fun, she still had to eat really fast, get dressed and shower quickly, practice hard, and wake up early. The clown would be juggling and handing out balloons in the crowd. Lola started to talk to Isabelle after she'd finished her part. Then she had to go change for the tightrope part. She was in the middle of changing when the circus master came rushing in and said, 'Lola! We're all waiting!' Lola finished changing and zipped out onto the stage. Her dog darted out of the way, letting her pass through as she slowed down to a stop, then walked out  on the stage so she didn't look like she was in a big hurry. The circus master sighed with relief as Lola performed well then rushed to change again.       After three more hours, the show was over. The crowd was tired. They bought some cotton candy and toys for the children, then went home. Lola was dog tired. She flopped onto her bed and drifted to sleep five minutes later.       The next morning, at 7:00 am, Lola's alarm rang again. She zoomed out of bed, grabbed her clothes and toiletry, then rushed to the bathroom. She showered quickly, brushed her teeth, washed her face, and sprinted out of the door to meet her colleagues at the bottom of the stairs. The matinee circus started. While Lola changed, the torch juggler was juggling swords and torches, and riding a unicycle at the same time around and around an elephant. Suddenly Lola heard a big THUMP and heard a cry.

Item_Response: Life of the Circus                     I am Olivero Dian,most people call me Oliver though, I am 10 years old and live in the circus with my family. My dad is the coordinator of the circus, he arranges everything from designing the graphics for posters to setting up auditions for new performers. I normally don't see him come out of his office in the day, he only comes out at night to see the show and my mom and I. For someone who has to deal with so much and work so often, I'm suprised my dad dosen't get stressed out.My mom is like the nicest person ever, I swear that she is the nicest person anyone could meet. Life at the circus is fun, but really hard.I basically get only 5 hours and 45 minutes of sleep everyday. After that, I go to the pie cart and get my favorties: pancakes,muffins,bacon,fruit, and some milk. Around two hours later, I go to school it's a one room school house, we learn math,writing,reading, and science like any other school. After that I practice for the show with my mom, we do the animal acts. I learn how to train animals, it's really interesting and fun because I really love animals. Finally, after 5 long hours of practice I take a break. I play games on my dad's computer in his office, read books, or play with around with some of the clown's equipment. Last but not least, I eat a little bit and preform in the show I love the cheer of the crowd, the bright lights shining on my face, and just letting all my worries go. Exhaustedly, I drag my self over to the trailer manage to fall asleep. Then after 3 days, we pack up our things and go move to another location. I love the circus, even though it's tough  I

Item_Response: Dave The TroubleMaker At The Circus           There was a boy, Dave, who worked in the circus, at first he thought working at the circus was going to be fun, but it turns out he was wrong...          First of all, Dave was suppose to feed, water,and brush the animals, instead he was messing around. He was riding on the clown's unicycle, Dave fell and broke the unicycle. He thought he was dead meat, and the show was about to start! An idea popped in hes head. He grabbed the sticky glue and glued the unicycle, by mistake he added glue on the seat. The show was starting, he saw the clown walking by to get his unicycle, so Dave hid behind a barrel. The clown went on stage with the sticky unicycle...Dave yelled and told the clown that the unicycle had sticky gule on the seat, but the clown didn't listen. The clown sat on the unicycle and heard a splat, he tried to get up, but he was stuck on the unicycle. He tried again,but this time he was glued on the unicycle, the crowd gasped at first and then bursted out laughing. The clown ran off the stage, at first he was very mad at Dave, but the clown found out that the crowd loved him...the clown shooked Dave's hands and thanked him.            The second thing Dave did that almost messed up the show was that he forgot to put the animals back in the cage. Dave was looking for the animals everywhere, but he couldn't find them anywhere. He lost the horses,elephants, and even the lions! He thought he was going to be fired, if he can't find the animals. He saw a black and orange stripped cat running away from a brown dog, and he came up with a idea. He went outside with a net, and tried to catch the dog and the cat, but they were too fast. Dave slip, fell, and trip in the mud. Then he went back inside and brought out a toy cat and a dead fish. Daveput the toy cat in the tree... when the dog saw the toy cat, he barked and barked. Dave on the other hand sneaked behind the dog and got him in the net. Then he put the plate of fish on the ground, and waited. Five minutes later he saw the cat eating the fish, then Dave got out from his hiding place and got the cat! He went back inside and sneaked in the dressing room and dressed the dog up into a horse, and dressed the cat in to a lion. All he needed was the elephant, he thought and thought, and he came up with an idea, he was going to buy an elephant from the Zoo... when he got there he saw that the elephants was for free he needed two elephants, there was five elephants left there. People crowed there trying to buy the elephants, but Dave sneaked through the people, the people didn't even notice, they were to busy fighting with the other people. When the Zoo opened, Dave ran and ran... when he got to the the elephants, he asked if he can get them, they said yes. Instead, the Zoo Keepes gave him all five elephants! Dave told the Keepers he only needed two elephants. The Zoo Keepers said 'Take it or leave it,' so Dave took all five elephants. When he got back to the circus, The show was starting... during the show, Dave was wishing that the show was going to be a hit, and it did! Everybody laugh and laugh!              The final thing Dave did wrong was that, he forgot to wash the dusty, old, dirty bicycles, he was to busy sleeping. Someone yelled that the show was about start in five minutes, Dave woked up and got soap, rags, and a bucket of water, he thought he can't wash all ten bicycles! So, he gave it a shot, when he was done with one bicycle, it took him three minutes! He had two minutes left! He looked around and around, and saw a hose and a bunkey of yellow/gold paint, he thought that it would only take a minute to paint the bicycles with a hose...he poured the bucket of paint in the hose,and turned it on. It sprayed and sprayed, the bicycles was all painted, it took less then a minute! Dave heard the speakers said 'Show will be starting in 10...9...8...,' Dave saw people coming to get their bicycles, Dave thought that the paint was still wet... the people grabbed the wet, painted bicycles, Dave tried to stop them it was no use... He heard the speakers again '3...2...1... Show is now starting,' the people rode on stage with the wet bicycles. When the show was over, the people got up to bow, and turned around... The crowd laugh so hard they almost fell off their seats! The people was so shy, that they ran of stage as a puff a smoke. After the show, the crowd said 'This is the best circus in the wrold that I have ever gone too!'and some even said 'I am coming here everyday from now and on!' The people who worked at the circus, thanked Dave, and told him to stay and work at the circus. But Dave who was tired, said thanks and when back home... when he got home, he went right to bed, and said 'Best day ever!'        As you can see, when your working at the circus, you have to work. You might not always play games or have fun like Dave,who almost messed up the show.

Item_Response: Before this circus visit I thought circuses were a bunch of animals doing thing way to silly, but now, I know that there is also some serious stuff like trapeze or tightrope. I thought the only 'cool' animal thing would be a bicycling bear but there is also a lion tamer and painting elephants.After this visit the circus was a whole lot different to me. This circus was a very amusing one to. The lighting was nice and the special effects.               What I thought about the animal acts are either, the elephants, the lion tamer, and the uni-cycling bear! Even though I thought a bear would be thought to us a tricycle it turns out they train it to use a    unicycle which to me is about a thousand times harder! I really liked the elephants because they taught them how to paint!!! and the art was only stick figures but especially because the used their trunks!!! I also thought the lion tamer was cool because he put his head in the lions mouth and the lion didn't chomp his head off!         What I thought about my favorite acts without animals was the trapeze, tightrope, sword swallower, and the really flexible guys.   I thought the sword swallower was amazing because swallowing swords is so hard because it goes down the throat without cutting themselves!!! Also those really flexible guys are really crazy because 4 of them can fit in a small box and still fit with the lid closed!!! what I thought about tight rope was that they actually use a uni cycle holding a large stick with 2 people on his shoulders and going across a really thin rope!! And the trapeze was really cool because they swing rope to rope like how monkeys swing vine to vine but they also do flips and sumersualts to!!!         I sort of liked the clowns even though they dress wierd they were pretty funny becuse they throw creme pie at each other and they squirt water out of flowers. But I dony really liked it becuase i thought clowns were acting a bit to over reactive but like 10 clowns can fit in a tiny car. But I also like the juggling becuase they juggle like, 10 balls!!! They even juggled knives which to me is pretty risky.         But I thought the knife throwers were really cool becuase they have someone spinning on a wheel and throw knives around him. Also, the knives go just between the legs and sometimes pinning the clothes but missing the body! The acrobats are also cool becuase its like the trapeze but they do flips and they also jump and grab a rope then jumps and grabs someones hand and they jump around doing backflips and stuff. The acrobats are a lot like the trapeze but with partners. The acrobats are also really light becuase whan they land you can hear only a little of them becuase they are pretty light.         Finally, I thought  the finale was cool becuase they were standing on top of each other and balncing an a ball! There were people and a seal! It was cool becuase they were making a castle by standing on top of each other. And people were standing on the shoulders. That was pretty cool because it fell withoout anyone getting hurt!!!         That was my favorite things at my first visit at a circus. It has never been so cool until now. Before I thought it would have no that many stuff, but I found a whole lot more intersesting things thats what I thought about the circus. I now like the circus better than before! I hope you enjoyed!!!

Item_Response: All About the Circus!!!!                      Hi! My name is Clarissa. I'm a circus performer. The circus I work for is the CIRCUS!CIRCUS! place in Las Vegas, Nevada The way you see the circus is pretty funny and humorous. The thing you don't know is that under all those suits and makeup, is a LOT of hard work. Yup, that's right, WORK. When you're in the circus, you have lots of fun watching, but the question is, ' How do they do all those performances? ' Well, let me show you my point of view.       Getting Into Shape                       First, I'll tell you how I trained to do my job, being an acrobat. As you can see, you have to be very flexible. When, I first started my circus career, I wasn't as stretchy as I am now. That's because they told me that I wasn't really in good shape. I have to admit, I wasn't that athletic until now because they took me to a gymnastics class. My gymnastics class was held at a special circus training area in Vegas. In gymnastics, they trained me to become as flexible as an octopus. They also trained me how to be balanced and concentrated, too. That's how I'm able to do as many flips as I can, jump, and land on those elephants with my other acrobats. After taking that class 8 hours each day, I became one of the most flexible acrobats in the circus. All in all, that's already a lot of work just to get myself in shape. Now, here's the REAL deal.       Acrobat Routines               Like all performers in the world, we have routines. A routine is a type performance that requires lots of practice, determination, and talent, such as doing a dance, or a cheerleading. My routine as an acrobat sounds really easy if you watch, but very hard if you know what to do.           In the acrobat routines, most of the time, you'd see people make pyramids and stuff like that. What others do is nothing compared to my most favorite routine. First, we hang on a tight rope and make a long ladder by hanging on to each other. Next, we climb down the human rope and we each get a normal-sized red, bouncy ball. Using our balance and concentration, we step on to the ball, and flip on to our hands. It sounds fun, but it's not easy. Then, we roll ourselves by a gigantic, red, porcelain ball and carefully flip back onto our feet. After we do that, we jump onto the ball and hold each others' hands. We then do a hand stand, link legs, and we're finished! Right after the audience applauses, we let go, slide of, and bow, and of course, we do these routines at CIRCUS!CIRCUS!          The really difficult thing about this is that we practice our routine almost 24/7, until our next performance. Another thing to worry about is that we have a performance almost every 3 days, twelve hours, for 7 months. As I repeat, it's not easy being a circus performer. Oh yeah, let me tell you what we acrobats get to wear!       Crazy for Clothes                First off, you know that acrobats can't use their pajamas as a costume. It would be really silly. Yes, I know that a circus would be all about silly, but in the circus world, it would kind of be considered improper. The acrobats' costumes are spandex coveralls with polka dots. The girls get a tutu & silly cap included. On the other hand, the boys get a spiral slinky belt and a pointy cap.            I'm really crazy about this because it's not like you can get these anywhere! Circus costumes are made especially for circus performers ONLY. We get our special costumes made by the ringmaster's special business.  That means they are very rare in the world. Although, it's not like we where these in practice.            In practice sessions, we wear spandex footed tights and a spandex t-shirt. It's very similar to what we wear during shows and mantinees, but simple. Now you see why it's very difficult to be an acrobat because spandex can slip off a polished, porcelain ball easily. Also, I'll bet you're wondering why we wear spandex. Acrobats use it because it's easier to stretch and use our flexibility. That's what we acrobats get to wear.                 So you see, living a life as an acrobat isn't easy. There are difficulties, billions of practice runs, shows and mantinees, and LOTS of hard work. Being a performer requires talent, determination, the right body, and confidence. If you can complete those tasks, you're ready to go! But don't forget, it's not easy at the circus!

Item_Response: A CONTORTUNATIST       HI MY NAME IS ALYSSA. I AM A PART OF THE CIRCUS. I AM VEY DEDICATED TO MY JOB. I WILL GIVE YOU ALL A BREIF LOOK OF MY LIFE AT THE CIRCUS. MY LIFE IS VERY HARD. MY WORK AMUSES CHILDREN, AND MAKES ME FEEL LIKE A LITTLE KID AGAIN. EVERY SHOW THAT I PUT ON FEELS GREAT. I FEEL AS IF I WAS A PART OF A BIG FAMILY. WHEN YOU JOIN A CIRCUS YOU WILL NEED TO KNOW, THEY MAY NOT ALWAYS WELCOME YOU NICELY, BUT IF YOU CAN SHOW THEM THAT YOU HAVE A GREAT TALENT THAT MAY IMPRESS THEM, THEY WILL ACCEPT YOU. WHEN YOU JOIN A CIRCUS, IT IS LIKE JOINING ONTO A LEGACY. WHEN YOU HAVE JOINED INTO A CIRCUS YOU WILL FEEL LIKE THERE IS NOTHING HOLDING YOU BACK. I WOULD NEVER HAVE THOUGHT THAT I WOULD BE WORKING IN A CIRCUS BECAUSE OF MY FEAR OF CLOWNS, BUT I GOT OVER IT. MY FEAR OF CLOWNS ENDED AFTER I MADE FRIENDS WITH SOME OF THE PEOPLE IN THE CLOWN SUITS. THE REASDON THAT I HAD A VERY BAD FEAR OF CLOWNS IS BECAUSE OF A SHOW THAT I WATCHED AS A YOUNG CHILD. ONE OF THE SHOWS THAT I USED TO WATCHED WAS A SHOW CALLED SUPERNATURAL. IT WAS A VERY CREEPY SHOW. THIS SHOW SHOWED CLOWNS THE CLOWNS THOUGH WERE KILLERS. THE CLOWNS WERE ALL NOT KILLERS I NOW KNOW THAT AFTER MEETING ONE OF THEM. I AM NOW A CUTORTINATIST I CAN BEND MY BODY IN ANY WAY POSSIBLE. THIS IS MY JOB, THAT IS MY ACT. I HAVE HAD MANY, MANY TORN MUSSCLES. BUT IT IS ALWAYS WORTH IT!

We wake up in the morning at 7:00 just like you. We even have to go to school.       Now I am going to talk about training animals. Training animals is not super easy it is super hard. You have to teach them how to do tricks and how to dress them for the when they go out on stage. This is the hardest thing to do that I think in the circus.       Then they setup is very hard you have to drag every thing on set so the circus can use it. Then you have to get the animals on stage which is very very hard.       So that is the life of the circus and to show you that it is not all fun and games in the circus.

Item_Response: It's hard being in a circus!       It's hard because you have to have no fear of hieghts, faling, accedently geting hurt, or the tent catching on fire.Itis also hard because it's almost always nonstop and you don't get to see your family a lot.You have to practice a lot and train animals too.                                   It's hard being in a circus but we the circuspeople make it look easy.Everybody has a fear or aweakness.Mine is hieghts that is why I am not an acrobat I am a clown.What I don't like thogh is people make horror movies of clowns.Now if I say Hi to acring little kid to make him feel better he jut screams even more!Anyway in the circus everything is harder in the circus when you have a fear because it limites you from a lot of things people would do like the acrobats who get  all the glamer.                               Another thing that is hard is that you have to wirk and work and WORK!everyday weekdays weekends every day of the week.Don't you think I would quit by now,but no!there is one thing that keeps me going. That is the stage. Oh....How I love being on stage. Well that one passion keeps me going Oh and the people are tere are like family exsept Rebecca Van Husan is mean to me,but she is stilllike family.                                 I also have practice every morning.I wake up super early to practice.I also go to bed super late because the shows.My teacher is really nice her name is Violet she has been a circus performer since she was 10 the year she ran away from home.She says she would of died from the cold if Bill (theguywho runs this whole thing.)Didn't save her and take her under his wing.After she tells me her stories of her childhood we practice the acts for later that night.                                                later in the afternoon if there is no show I will train the baby animals.I have two fears one is hieghts and the other is getting eaten by animals.                                 That why being in a circus is exstremly hard.

Item_Response: I want to tell you about when I was in a Circus. It was really fun. My job was with the Lions, Bears, Monkeys, and Elephants. I was a very talented girl. I was 10 when I had tried out. Before, I was the girl who danced before it started and after it was over. Then they moved me over just with the Monkeys for 6 months. Then they moved me with the Monkeys and the Elephants for another 6 months. They noticed I was very talented and was working hard so they moved me to the Lions and Bears.   They had try outs so a 7 year old girl made it, her name was Valerie. She was talented, but needed alittle help so she was my assisant  for 7 months. In thoughs 7 months she was moved into Lions and Bears.Then I was moved to Tigers and  Chimpanzes.A few months later she was moved to Monkeys and Elephants. She didn't appear for the 3 shows. Then her doctor had called because she couldn't got to the next 10 shows because she had gotten in a car crash and broke her leg. We were sad, but we couldn't do nothing.   My ruteen was not very tiring. At 8:00 we got up and dressed. At 9:30 we got breakfast.  At 10:30 we got droped of at school. At 4:00 we got out of school, at 6:00 we ate dinner and at 8:30 we went to bed. Then I got tierd of ding the same thing for 10 years so I started working at a resturant called El Pescador.

Item_Response: Circus Life                                                    Some people think that the people that live with the circus are crazy. Let me tell you some are and some aren't. My name is Bob Evens I am a clown. I travel 20,000 miles, I go to around 150 city's. We work form sunup to sundown. The circus life is good.            Do you want to know what my schedule is? Here it is, At 7:00 A.M. I wake up get dressed,and go to the pie car to get some breakfast.While the crew sets up the tent, lights and music for tonight's show.            At 9:00 A.M. it's school time. The one room school house travels with us. It has computers, test, and report cards. Some of the circus performers are from other country's  they speak different languages. In the circus our geography lesson comes to life.            At 3:00 P.M. school lets out. We get a quick break. We play with some of  circus toys. I play with the baby leppords. I shot spit balls at the lions. I give the elephants peanuts.            At 3:30 I put on my make up and practice my tricks like the others. Somtimes I feed, water, and groom the horses. The trainers train some of the animals. Somtimes goff of for practice.             At 6:30 P.M. it's dinner time. I normaly don't eat much. some of the people eat enough to fill a elephants stomach. their belly normally hurts after the show. If I mess up my make up I have to redo it.             At 10:30 P.M. The shows over we go to bed that night. most people go right to sleep I don't. I love my circus life!

Item_Response: Hi. Have you ever wanted to be a clown or another person who works at a circus? Do you ever think people in circuses have a nice relaxing life with tons of fun and play? Well life is not like that. My name is Darwin and I work at a circus. I have to work for more than 12 hours a day!       Working at a circus is hard work. I must train for a few hours and perform in front of a live crowd. If one person is injured, the whole event is ruined, and everyone will feel ashamed. There are many consequences of not practicing well, so we need to train for many hours.In a circus, we still have school and other programs. We live in trailers and we learn things like other students.       Even though circus life is hard, it is a fun job that we still like.

Item_Response: Life  at  a  Circus               One day i was playing zombie tag with my friends Michael , Tony , Sergio . Michael was it so Sergio and i hid at the creek . We heard someone laugh so we went to see who it was . We saw a tall clown and he knocked us out with a bat . When i woke up i was in a small room . I looked out the window and saw clowns all around . I went outside and asked a clown ,'' Where am i .'' He said ,'' Your at a circus ''.I looked around and thought Sergio . '' Where is my friend '', i asked . He pointed to a car so i went there and saw Sergio on a bed . I told him to wake up and said we were at a circus . We went outside and a tall clown and two body guard clowns were in front of us .The tall one said ,'' See me at my office ''. We went to his office that had what he calls '' art '' and alot of clown tools . He asked us if we could be his new clowns . Sergio always wanted to perform with circus horse an i always wanted to be launched in a cannon so we said ,'' Yes'' . He offered us pancakes and bacon and i ate my whole plate . I guess i was hungry .                       After we ate he showed us around the circus . We saw the schoolhouse , circus office  , concession stands , stables , and trailers . After that we inside the circus and saw clown practicing their act and some were practicing with animals . When Sergio saw one of the horse he started riding it and doing stunts . I asked him what i'm supposed to do and he asked if i wanted to be launched in a cannon and and i said '' YESSS '' . He said i could but first i had to train first . I had to jump in a pool and ride a unicycle . After we trained we had to go to our trailer but first the boss said there was a contest the next day . The next day we ate waffles and sausages and got ready for the act . We practiced for a little while then we left .                         It took us 10 minutes to get at the circus . When we got there the announcer said the winners win 5,000 dollars . Our circus went first . When Sergio went he was doing tricks on a horse and he jumped through a hole with fire . Then it was my turn and i got launched on a cannon and landed on a trampoline . Then it was the other circuses turn . In the end we won 1st place and won 5,000 dallors . The boss took off in a unicycle with nitro with the money . We chased him on a horse and caught him . We took the money and left to our house . The next day we told everyone but they didn't believe us .

When you get there you will see that people will be setting up tents,lights,and music for your show. At 9:00 am it is time to go to school you will learn about how to behave in a circus and any geography lessons that will come to a point in the circus.            You think that all you do in a circus is do all sorts of crazy stuff but really you aren't you have to follow a routine that you get assighned for the circus. so you will have to memorize it and all the stuff you will have to do in the circus.                      Before you get ready to put on a show for the circus you have to get you costume on then put makeup on to make you look silly. The different types of circus stuff is acrobats, jugglers, and tightroping.

Item_Response: The circus is fun to play but a lot of responsibility. Every day I have to get up early in the morning. I go to the pie truck and have a omelet. Then I train the dogs or the horses. the dog's favorite trick is to ride a bike. The horses favorite trick is having a girl jump on their back.         Each kind of animal has its own truck. The clown's truck is pretty wacky. My truck is red like all the others with a bed and desk. The classes are pretty easy and I have quiet a few friends they are really smart and funny. Most of the time we hang out with the dogs or the clowns.         It has been alomost a month since I have seen my family. They come to the circus every once in while. I miss them a lot. My friends are always their comfort me. The circus is also my family.

Item_Response: circus   If you have ever be in a circus you have to wake up at 7:00 get dressed eat breakfast and set up tents and lights. 9:00 A.M. you go to school. 3:00 P.M. you get a quick break . Then you go practice juggling. 3:30 P.M. you have to feed and groom the animals and practice somersaulting off a horses back and leaping off trampolines onto a horses back then you have to train the elephants, lions. At 6:30 it is dinnertime and eat a little amount of food before you perform. Every week youhave to perform 10 times.  10:30 P.M. the show is over you have to take the tents and lights down then you go to bed. Then the next morning you have to get up and ready to go to the next location you are going to preform.

Item_Response: If you think that being in a circus is just having fun and goofing off, then you must be crazy. Being in a circus isn't always just fun and games.                              Here is my regular day.       7:00 am I wake up and go to the pie car to eat pancakes and bacon for breakfast.       9:00 am I go to the one room schoolhouse which travels with us as we go. Just like any other school we have tests, computers, and report cards. Many kids in the class come from all over the world and they speak a different language so sometimes it is a little tricky to understand them.       3:00 pm is when school gets out. The clowns let me play with the unicycles and juggling balls. It's alot of fun.       3:30 PM I do my chores and practice my act. I feed, water, and groom the horses we use in the act. Today my dad has to practice summersaulting off of a running horse. I am a little bit nervous for him but I'm sure he will be okay. I practice leaping from a trampoline onto a horse's back, it takes balance and focus to do it. Other kids my age are practicing juggling and acrobatics. My neighbor takes baby leopards out for walks. Trainers work with elephants, lions, and monkeys for the show that is coming up.       6:30 pm time for dinner, I'm starving! my family and I head out for the pie car for dinner, but we are sure not to eat too much before the show. We do ten shows a week. One on each weekday, in addition to the manitee on Wednsday, two on Saturday, and two on Sunday.       10:30 pm the show is over and I am SUPER tired! We go back to our trailer and pass the circus ofices, concession stands, stables, and trailers. In two days we will be in a totally different town.       12:00 am I'm in bed and thinking about the end of our touring season. It will be great to get back to my real home in Florida. Then I wonder if I will still be in the circus when grow up. I have no idea what I am going to be because i am just a kid. The circus is really fun and exciting, but sure is a lot of work.

Item_Response: The Circus Trip of a Lifetime   By: Alexis Carver           Hello, I'm Dellak. I live in Brazil. You've probably never heard of the town I live in because, well, it's tiny. In fact the population is only 382 people. If you really want to know the name, it's Bakshea. Brazil has been split into different color districts. Each color district has two or three small towns in it. The six color districts are, The Green District, the Red District, the Blue District, the Yellow District, the Purple District, and the Orange District.           My mom  asked me to go to Shealey, the next closest town to us, where all the shops were, for bread, milk, butter,cheese, and cloth for the next two weeks.I left home at sunrise, even though I was about to fall asleep just talking to my mom. I walked the two miles to Shealey, bored out of my mind. Once I got to Shealey I walked into the Bakery. There wasn't much to gawk over since the baker didn't have a glass counter to put treats in, but he did have a plastic case for a cake. The cake that was in the case was a strawberry cake with chocolate icing and strawberries to decorate the top. 'How could anyone afford this cake?' I thought. I ringed the bell on the cold stone counter. After a few seconds a bald plump man with a dirty white coat came up to the counter. 'Hi Mr.Trumpers,' I said.           'Hello Dellak. Do you want the usual?' Mr.  Trumpers asked.           'Yep. Three loafs of bread,' I answered.           'Okay. Hold on a minute.' Mr. Trumpers replied.           As I waited for Mr. Trumpers to bring me the bread, I thought, 'I wonder if Mr. Trumpers has any children.' I decided to ask. Mr. Trumpers walked back into the room and I thanked him for the bread, payed him and asked, 'Mr. Trumpers do you have any children?'           'No, why'd you ask?' Mr. Trumpers replied             'I don't know, I guess I just wanted to meet someone new,' was my answer.            I left the Bakery and headed for the Dairy Farm. The walk wasn't bad since it was only two blocks away. When I got to the Dairy Farm's lobby I saw a sign that said Win front row seats at the Bellini Circus! I thought,'The Bellini Circus! In the small town of Shealey! I can't believe it! But it would be so expensive. I have to win this contest!' I walked in to see Rosy, the farmer's daughter.           'Can I help you?' Rosy asked.           'Yes. I'd like four pitchers of milk, with lids, in a container, two sticks of butter, and two wheels of cheese, please,' I said trying to sound polite not rood and pushy.           'Okay, Dellak. I'll go get that for you,' she replied.            She was almost out the door when I shouted after her, 'Oh and, Rosy, how do you enter the contest for front row seats to the  Bellini Circus?'.            She turned around and walked over to the counter. Then she answered my question, 'You write a story that takes place in a circus and turn it in to me by May 28th.'            'Today's April 29th so I have a little less than a month,' I thought. 'Okay, thanks Rosy.' I said calmly even though inside my heart was pounding so hard it was a bomb's timer counting down until it explodes.           'Your welcome. Now let me go get your stuff,' she said sharply, but also being goofy.           'Okay, okay,' I said, which made her giggle.           After Rosy gave my my things I paid her and left. I went to the fabric shop got the cloth my mom wanted and headed home, never stopping thinking about the story I was going to write.           By the time I got home it was clearly afternoon. I walked inside helped my mom put away the groceries, and ran strait to my room to start writing my story. It was harder than I thought it would be. I had only gone to a circus once, and it was a long time ago. I could remember that there were men and women with painted faces and big red noses. There were also lions, tigers, and bears. Another thing I can remember is that there were people that rode a bicycle with only one wheel on a rope really high up in the air and people who swung on bars and did tricks up in the air.       I ended up writing the winning story. I title it The Mysterious Trip of a Lifetime.

Item_Response: The Perfect Show   by:Margaret Tibbetts           I, Maria, am a tiger trainer at my family's circus, Jim and Tina's   Circus Life Experiance, and I have had my tiger since I was six. I got Chloe, my tiger, on my sixth birthday. Chloe and I have been working on the preformence  for our biggest show happening tomorrow in Kansas City. All the performers of  our circus are so exited and ancious, yet so nervous.       In the early morning, every body is getting up, eating, practicing,   and are setting up for the big show tonight noticing that it is a sad rainy day. we are post poning the show to tomorrow. since everybody else's act could be inside, we still have to practice today. I got Chloe ready and we are going outside to practice. As I was running in circles with Chloe, I slipped and broke my ankle.       Mom and dad found another trainer to fill in for me. Item_Response: Hello, I'm Anne and I work at the circus. My parents grew up in the circus too. My mom's a trapeze artist, and my dad is a juggler. We get to travel all around the world. I go to over 150 cities per year! The whole circus is like my family.                 The circus isn't always that fun though. The shows are long, and some tricks are hard to do. I miss my home in California a lot. I don't have a regular home. I'm always moving around. I never see my family except for my mom and dad. I don't even have the weekends off.                   My daily schedule starts off with school. I wake up at 7:00 AM and go to the pie car to eat. At 9:00 AM school starts. It's like any other school, but my classmates come fro all around the world. They all speak different languages, like, French, Russian, Italian, and English like me. 3:00 PM, I take a quick break. At 3:30 PM I do my chores. I feed and water my horses, Belle and Jack. I use them in some of the circus's acts. Then I practice for the show. I always wanted to join a sports team but I've never had the opportunity. At 6:00 PM I have dinner. It's very light though because we're about to preform. I do 10 shows a week. At 10:00 the show is over, I'm very tired.                  The circus is very fun, but it is also very busy and tiring.

Item_Response: My life at the circus is about having fun, but here is my usual day.           6:30 TIME TO WAKE UP!!!!!   It is six thirty and i have to get up. I get dressed and brush my teeth and do my hair. Then I get ready for the day.       8:00 SCHOOL IS STARTING!!!!! Item_Response: The Last Show               As I walk on to the beginning of the tight rope to take my place I can hear the crowd cheering for me. I am nervous but I know I can go across the tight rope which is 60 feet off the ground. I have gone across it before but this time, my father told me to make a twist to the act and wants me to go across the tight rope while doing the hula hoop. Even though I practiced walking on the tight rope while hula hooping, I am scared because the whole circus is depending on me. Only if the European promoter is pleased with our show, our circus will be able to go on a world tour to Europe.          I slowly take step by step on the tight rope and began to hula   hoop. I close my eyes and think about how I will feel when the European promoter promotes us. I made it across the tight rope! The crowd cheers as I climb down the ladder. I walk back into my dressing room with joy and nervousness. I can hear the promoter talking to my father, the manager of the circus. When I hear the promoters foot steps as he leaves back stage my father knocks on my door and tells me that the promoter loved out circus act and promoted us to the Europe world tour. I do a cart wheel with joy. I help my dad pack our stuff because tomorrow we have a long drive to Europe.                The next morning the whole circus loaded their stuff into the bus and we all ride on the bus for seven whole hours. Even though I am bored, I am excited about my first performance in Europe. When we arrive at our designated place, I help to set up the tents. Since we finished setting everything up earlier than we planned my dad says I can go and explore the city.                I come back at seven o'clock, right before show time. I dress up and hurry to my spot on the tight rope. I easily make it across the first time. The crowd cheers and wants me to go across again on the tight rope but this time with two hula hoops. I ask my dad what to do and he says I should give it a try so I do. I almost make it across the tight rope when I loose my balance and fall off. I fainted. When I woke up, I was in a hospital. My dad came up to the bed I was laying in and told me what happened. I had broken my neck and leg. My dad told me that I had undergone a surgery and turns out I will not be able to perform ever again. I was so disappointed that I started crying.                I went back to the circus and after a few days I got over the fact that I cannot do the thing I love most, perform.

Item_Response: The New Job       As I was walking into computer class I was wondering if I would ever find my true protential. My best friend has a wonderful job so I want one too.I have been looking in all the news papers for 2months and still can not find a job that fits me.Today in computer class we were going to learn about how to get job on the computer because I asked my teacher for help so hopfully there will be a job that is hiring people, so wish me luck!   Well, turns out that there were no jobs I was interested in but just because I did not see one today sometimes if you add a little faith you can accomplish anything. That morning something unexplainable happened! Today was when the news paper came so I jumped out of my bed and rushed to get the news paper in the driveway.After 2 min. went by there was a page that had a big pictre of an elephant and people training them and under it was big bold letters..................                          NOW HIRING at THE CIRCUS   As soon as my eye caught the big bold letters something was telling me that this job might work so I called the number!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!                                         910-555-7689                                         Getting into Buisness       When I called my mom to tell her what happened she was so happy that she cryed.She said that my father used to be in the circus when he was about 13 years old and I said no wonder something was telling me to check it out and see if I like it.The next day I went to the circus because it was the day that I might get hired.When I got there they were examining me and I told them that I was confedent and very positive and that I was very determined to do anything.Then they asked me if i did gymnastics then I said'' When I was 5 to16 but now I am 18.'' When they said thank you and I left I was so ancious to see if I was hired. The next morning they called me and said that I was hired!   As soon as heard the word HIRED i almost exploded like a volcano!   They wanted to see me at 9:00a.m. and I said how about a little early   ''Ok Great''.                                     The World's Grandest Show       When I started my new job everyone there said that I was the leader because I was never afraid of anything pretty soon after a few years the circus was the most popular in the world. I was the main person doing everything but even though sometimes I felt like giving up I tried my best to make it through and when you beleive in yourself great things could happen so never give up on anything,even though it is hard sometimes.               Moral: Never give up on anything

Item_Response: In 1956 there was not much but what there was is the famous circus called 'THE AMAZING CIRCUS'.All my life I wanted to get tickets and I always wondered how the circus life would be.        Anyways this can be my big move to see that circus show.This circus only comes once a year.My friend Jacob he has an uncle who works in the 'THE AMAZING CIRCUS'.Jacob might get us tickets but the tickets cost $00.25.Do you know how much money that is I can't afford that neither can Jacob.We might have a plan.We can contact his uncle , but how are we going to get to him?        Today we went to school and our teacher was also talking about the circus coming to our town 'Brooklyn'.We asked her if we can help in anything.Well she told us we could post these posters around town.        Well we did so many people got interested we got scared that there wasn't going to be any more tickets.After posting all that we hurried up to the circus.There wasn't enough time.       We ran till we reached the circus.We saw his uncle Jorge just walk inside the huge tent.We ran but then a big bodygaurd came and got us from our shirts an yelled 'NO KIDS ALLOWED AROUND HERE'.He put us down but instead of running we went under him and ran to the big tent.It was 4:00 p.m.        We saw so many people they were all chasing us but then Jacob's uncle Jorge got us and said I know these kids there fine.Why did you come here said Jorge.Jacob said we wanted tickets for show.Oh,said Jorge I already sent tickets to your houses.Thank you Jorge,Jacob and me told with a big hug.Jacob and me went to see the show.My big wish happened.

Item_Response: Ever wanted to know what it's like to be a circus performer? if you do then read on. In this story, you will learn about what it's like to be a circus performer as a young person. it's a hard, rough, and exhausting life.       Marlla Mandora was an active and performing loving 12 year old girl. she was never shy and loved to perform anywhere anytime. She was a dancer, performed ballet, and even musical gymnastics. She would enter every talent show she could and anything she was good at.        Marlla's parents were proud of their daughter. They supported her in anyway they could. 'When I get older, I wanna join the circus! Oh how fun it would be doing acrobatics and swinging from high! It would be a dream!' she said to her mother. Like I said, her parents supported her in anyway she could.       When Marlla was 18, her parents signed her up for circus tryouts. Marlla knew it was gonna be hard. There were many people trying out. Some breathed fire. Some juggled chainsaws. Some even did funny acts! but only few were chosen. And one of them was me!       Marlla was happy and sad at the same time. Marlla got her dream but she had to leave her supporting parents. But her parents knew that their little girl had to leave. With that, a circus member took Marlla and gave her a tour of people and animals and equipment.       At 10:00 P.M., there was a show. But Marlla wasn't in it. She had to watch to see how the showed worked. Marlla was thrilled at the stunts and funny tricks. She couldn't wait for her first show! She especially loved the stunts on horseback.       Marlla woke up a 7 in the morning and went to the pie cart and had breakfast. She asked the animal keeper if she could help with anything. the keeper said yes and gave her a job with the horses. She groomed and fed them and mucked out their stalls.       Something excited is happening today. Today will be Marlla's first show! Marlla was doing acrobatics. She was very excited. But first, they had to setup the Big Top Tent and then a bunch of others. it was hard work setting up all the tents.       By the end of the day, Marlla was wiped out. She was so exhausted. But then she had to help put down all the tents and put away the animals and give them their dinners and fix their beds. Then Marlla got to finally sleep.       The next day, it all happened again. Marlla performed and loved it but it was too much work everyday, having to perform 10 times a week with four shows on the weekend. She missed going home to her parents and performing for them once in a while.       She decided to quit and go back to her home in Alabama. She surprised her parents by returning without them knowing. 'What. Why are you here?' her parents asked, 'Oh, it was too hard too keep up with all the shows and taking tents down and taking care of the animals,' she said.       With that, she lived with her parents and still performed.She eventually found a husband and had two children. She inspired her children to act and surprisingly...her children became movie stars!

Item_Response: Circus   Days              There was a town called Hilltop town there was a school called Hilltop Elementary School and a kid in 5th Grade named Johnathan.He likes to go to gymnastics he is training for the circus.He always wanted to go to the circus he wanted to do something exciting.He wondered how it will feel if he was all the way at the top of a tightrope trying to balance your self.That should be scary.Johnathan!His teacher was calling him. Oops he forgot he was in school he was day dreaming.         He got back home his parents were packing up?His parents are called Lily and Jake.Johnathan said 'Why are we packing up.'Lily said 'Your going to be a circus actor.'Johnathan said'Yippee.'The next day they had everything in their RV they had to go to San Diego for their first circus act.Johnathan he had to be on the unicycle juggling balls it was very hard for him.He wasn't going fast because he might fall and get hurt.He was nervous really nervous.After the show he was tired he wanted to go to sleep.Jake said'Hurry up you need to go to sleep for tomorrow.'          The next day they were already driving to Las Vegas but Johnathan did not know were they were going.Johnathan said 'Where are we going.'Jake said'Were at Las Vegas.'Johnathan said'For what'Jake said'For your circus act at Circus Circus Johnathan said'Awesome.'When they arrived to the hotel Johnathan saw a pool he wanted to go to the pool, but he had a circus act to do at night.Then he was going to the circus.Then he saw a big giant circus tent right behind a building.He got the chills in his bones,he was afraid what kind of act he was going to do this time.              When he got inside there was a lot of people on the seats.I was so nervous I just wanted to run and hide some where dark.So he went back stage with the other clowns and the acrobats .When they told him what he had to do Johnathan told his parents and Johnathan said in a slowly voice'I have to do the tightrope walker.'He kind of froze when he had to do that.Slowly he walked to the middle of the circus tent climbed up the ladder onto the platform.He had to hold a long stick.He started to walk on the rope every one was clapping he started to laugh.Then he was losing his balance every one gasped and the cushions weren't there but the clowns were barely coming out then he fell.The clowns barely came on time, he was saved.he did not want to stop doing circus acts after that fall.               THE END

Item_Response: What I learned from the story Win front row seats at the Bellini Circus! is that being in the circus could be fun and difficult. You have to be away from home for a long time and barely get to see your family unless they are with you.You have to live in a RV to travel places.Your going to have to wake up early have to wake up early, do chores, practice, have fun for a little and go to school. Once the week has gone by everyone  packs up the circus you pack up your stuff and move to the next town. Then everyone sets up again keeps doing the same stuff all over again but not everything the same all over again because every day is a new day. That is my wonderful story about the circus and thank you! Life is a circus!

Item_Response: The Daily Life of a Bustling Circus               You may think that The Circus is just some place for funny people and contortionists. But no, you're wrong, the circus clowns and acrobats do so much in the daytime to impress you. They get up, get dressed and spend all day getting ready, while you just sit their and watch T.V. or whatever. 8:00 P.M. is show time! you get up to the tent, seating everywhere, concession stands and the big ring stage. After the performance the clowns and contortionists get a large standing ovation from the audience. When you leave that tent, remember, you have it good, clowns don't because they spend all their life and dedication to make you laugh.

Item_Response: 'My pies my pies,' Olly the clown yelled 'My pies my pies,' Olly yelled again now sounding more desperate     'Olly it's OK we will find your pies,' said the ring master    'really...,' asked Olly now full of hope.   'Well maybe... the only lead we have is that some one ate them...All,'.  Olly stood still he thought he was going to have a heart attack!   'some one ate all my pies...that's impossible only I can eat 6,038 pies,' suddenly Olly gasped 'I know who did it!'    'Really,' said the ring master sounding surprised 'who?' He asked       ' Jolly Joe,' said Olly 'He knew that he could never make pies as good as me, so to even the score he stole mine ,' He explained  'Now why would the circus chef steal your pies?'                                 'I just told you !' said Olly as his temper stared to rise that's it,' Olly said aloud as he grabbed a hold of the ring master by the hand and dragged him all the way to Jolly Jo's trailer just as Olly was about to knock the ring master interrupted him 'Olly stop... I ate your pies,' the ring master confessed       'But why,' Olly asked       'Oh no I didn't really, I just wanted you to get over it,' The ring master replied        ' I still need to know who ate them,'Olly said as he barged through the door of Jolly Jo's trailer but instead of finishing his sentence he froze his mouth gaping open there in the middle of the room was Jolly Joe takings Olly's pies apart piece by piece and studying them so that he too knew how to make them.        Then he looked up from his work and muttered the word busted ' Olly this isn't what it looks like!'.  But Olly was already on the floor weeping.   'how could you do this to me?' Olly asked       'Olly I never meant to hurt you,' Jo said trying to explain 'I didn't think you would teach how to make your pies so i took them... I was going to give them back       ' Really?' asked Olly standing up and wiping away tears       'Really,' Said Jolly Joe now smiling       'Well now that this mystery how about we all go out for pizza ... it's on me,' Suggested the ring master and they all left the trailer, piled into one of those tiny clown cars and drove of.

Item_Response: The Circus                                    By: Natasha Hussain       Hi, my name is Jason. I am a performer in the circus. My act is lion taming. It looks easy but actually it is very hard and a bit scary. First of all, you always have to have pure concentration because if something goes wrong, you will be a lions dinner for sure. When you are up there with the lions,always remember not to get on their bad side. Other then that,it is not that stressful. As I always say, become one with the lions. Let hem understand that you are their friend.   Over the years, have become very close to these big cats. in fact now all the guys at the circus call me the lion whisperer because I have this connection with them. I sometimes go in their cages and fool around with them. I sit with them while they sleep next to me or lick my face. To me, honesly their just a bunch of house cats. Big house cats. I like to hear them purr when I stroke them and brush their wild manes. If you feel like I do, like you feel like you connect with lions, dont be so sure that you feel like you can just walk right into a lion cage and expect them to be all friendly. Actually,in my case, it was not love at first sight. I remember when I first walked into the cage. The biggest male lion,Muzala, growled at me and bared his teeth. Afterwards, I kept my distance and was patient. Now they are like my cats. I love my job and intend to keep doing it for as long as I live.

Item_Response: My life in the Circus                                            by Carry smith             Circus life isn't just some crazy nonstop madhouse thats just crazy talk. I, Carry Smith know what its like being in the circus. I live with my family in a circus trailer. We travel around the world almost every year. And over 200 different citys every year, maybe even more then that.           Mostly likely a day for me:           6:00 A.M. I wake up, Take a shower, Get dressed. And go to a gastation or nearby food truck for breakfast alot of times bacon and pancakes. Then help the circus crew get set for the show for tonight.               11:30 A.M. Time for school:              There are many different things then in a regular school like yours. Many people in my class speake different languages like german,french,and italian. My family only speakes french,german and english. As we travel around the world every different lesson seems to comes to life.             4:15 P.M. School is over:            Time for a quick snack and a break from school until tomorrow. The trapeze artist let me play on the trapezes. Also the clowns let me play with there clown cars and juggle. I also play with the tiger, Cuddles. I want to play on a cheerleading team but, we never stay long in one place for me to play a sport.             4:30 P.M.  Practice:         My dad and I feed,water and groom the tigers and horses.We use in the tiger act and horse act. Today, my mom practices taming the tigers more I help her it is sometimes really scary. I'm also working on doing a horse back trick.         5:15 P.M. dinner time:          My family and I usually go to a resturant to eat some a gas station if we cant find a resturant.We dont eat very much before the show that happening tonight anyway. We do 8 shows a week. one each week day and a special one on Saturday.            9:45 P.M. Show is over:         I'm wiped out. We walk back to the circus trailer, We stop at the concession stands sometimes. But, we really pass the other stuff like the stables,circus offices, and other trailers. Now when I'm asleep we'll be in a different town tomorrow.          11:45 P.M. In bed:          im thinking about the end of this season of touring. The circus is fun and all But, I miss my ranch in South Carolina. When I grow up, I think I'll still be a circus performer. The circus is fun but, it's not so easy as a life.

Item_Response: Afternoons At the Circus   Hello, I am Zoe Walik and I am here to tell you about what goes on during a normal afternoon in the circus. There are upsides and downsides to the afternoon but its all worth it.           After school you will have to rehearse with the animals and feed them. Doing this will help prepare them for the performance. When you finish practicing with an animal you will have to move on to a different animal so this might take some time. While you're practicing with them you will also be learning more yourself. When you have finished rehearsing with all of the animals you will need to practice your own routine. You might think that this sounds silly but  you do need your practice too.              When you are finished practicing with the animals and yourself, you will need to get ready  for your performance. You will also need to eat but do not eat such a big meal before your performance because depending on what you are doing you do not want stomach cramps.  After the performance you are wipped out so it is time for bed and boy will you be tired in the morning!               Being a circus performer is tough but it is all worth it if you are having fun and doing what you love. If you do want to become a circus performer I reccomend you  stick to your mind and try your best.

Item_Response: Have you ever dreamed of being in the circus? Well, circus life is harder than you might think. It takes a lot of practice, talent, and work. In fact, much of the life in the big top is working and practicing. Here is what a day would be like if I were a circus performer.       I would start off the day by waking up, getting dressed, and going to the pie car, the place where circus performers eat. If I have time, I would go help the performers set up for tonight's show. Next I would go to the schoolhouse car. So, if you think circus life is all play and no work, you still have to go to school. After school, I get a short break, but after that, it's chores, chores, chores, and time for practice, practice, and more practice. Next, it is time for the show. I must do my act, which could be tightrope walking, juggling, lion taming, or even being a human cannonball. The show would last for hours, but after that it's time to rest and sleep. This same schedule would last every day. As you can see, circus life can be tough, yet it's all worth it in the end.       However, before you even step into this wild life, you must become a circus performer. You must have talent and determination. Sure, you get to travel the world, but it could be months or even years before you see your family. There are also many people in this world, so don't get your hopes up about joining. However, if you have a special talent, like being flexible, super strong, or fast, you would be a great candidate. In short, preparing for circus life is just as exciting.        In conclusion, there are ups and downs to performing in the circus. A day for a performer is hectic, yet amusing. It takes a lot to get in the circus, but it is most definitely worth it. The circus, from my point of view, is a tough profession, with fun and work all in one.

Item_Response: A Circus Life       'Okay Seth it`s time to get up. It`s a big day today. We have three performances to go to', my mom said. 'All right', I yelled back. Your probaley thinking what does she mean by performances? Well I work at a circus. Now, let me tell you one thing it`s not that easy. First you got to have a talent for something to be in a circus. You also should start young so you can build up your learning so when you get older you`ll know a lot about circus see I started when I was five, now I`m twelve. That`s seven years of being in the circus and I`ve learned a lot.       Now let me tell you about the bad parts of being in a circus. You`ll have to travel to a lot of places and by the end of the day you`ll be beat because you traveled to so many places in one day. Believe me it`s tiring. Sometimes there could be at least four performances in one day that you have to go to.       So in the end I recomend you to join the circus because it`s a lot of fun, but there are some faults about the circus. So I`m off to my first permormance of the day!

Item_Response: A Normal Day At The Circus                 The crowd cheered. Cameras flashed. Klaus was confused as he woke. He thought he had messed up. The rips on his shirt, his broken bones and the unconscious heap of the clown  proved it. Yet they were cheering. Suddenly realization dawned on him as he saw the pistol in now officialy sociopathic Tennyson's limp grasp and the braying horse next to his body with his startled Father on it, the reigns tight in his hands...             The air was tense in the tent. This would be Klaus's first big act with the Giavanni circus, and it was odvious the other performers doubted his aptitude to perform. Especially Tennyson. Tennyson had been a limber clown when he started, so it was said, but after years of eating in the pie car and lying on the train's cozy couch, a potbelly had protruded and now all that was left of his formerly skinney self was the thin face that resided under the wig he wore. Rumor was that he was bald, but this was yet to be proven due to his never removing his fake purple curls, even when asleep. Tennyson also was growing increasingly jealous of Klaus's father, who led the circus, because he thought he was the rightful leader. Under Tennyson's sneer, he emerged from the tent and out onto the ring, feeling genuinly worried. Here I go, thought Klaus as Father emerged on horseback for their act.             Klaus's act was going reasonably well. Their act was simple, but hard. Clowns would be juggling around the ring, and inside it Father would be riding around the ring, going clockwise. In the center, on a trampoline, Klaus would be doing flips, cartwheels, and other tricks until Father rode around the ring for the sixth time. On the sixth round, Klaus would backflip off the trampoline and onto the horse and land standing. They were now on the fith rotation, and Klaus could feel his heart rate increase. He had done well enouph to recieve roars of aproval from the audience after each trick, but now he was only faintly hearing all background noise. Clip clop, clip clop went the hoove beats on the ground, as the horse was nearing the end of its sixth time around. Boom Boom, Boom Boom, went his heart, which was now in his throat. He bounced, his legs went over his head, and...             Klaus heard bones crack as he hit the recipiant of his leap. Only they were not just his ribs that had broken, but another person's, too. That was all he remembered before he blacked out.            Tennyson was angry before he was knocked out. His plan to avenge himself had been ruined by his nemesis's stupid son, who he was supposed to shoot, had accidentally timed his jump wrong? Inconceivable. This was his last rational thought before he would awaken days later in a prison cell.

Item_Response: April 25,2013                                     THE CIRCUS                        The Circus is a world inside a world. With lots of new people inside that world.You can see typical circus animals,acts,and people  such as clowns,lions,trapeze artists,tight-roping, and more. Some Circuses are amazing like Cirque du Soleil. People from all over the world come to see circuses when they come into town.  People from all over the world also participate in the circus.                           OOOOOOOOOOOHHHHHHHHH, AAAAAAAAAAAAAHHHHHHHHHH fill the circus tents. Everyone is amazed on daring, incredible tricks everything can seem like an illusion in the circus tents. Elephants seals, lions zebras ,cheetahs a lot of unordinary zoo animals all participate in the amazing show. Five clowns in one small car?! AMAZING! A man diving into a small pool thirty-five feet high?! INCREDIBLE! A man tight-roping from the top of the tent?! NERVE - RACKING!!!!!                  Being in the circus isn't all fun and games for the performers. Most of the time they practice almost nonstop.They do this because in a show you need to know exactly what you are doing. If you aren't practicing you will typically be doing things like what you do at home...chores. Everyone has a job to do. Whether it's grooming the show horses, or setting up the tent , people will always be doing something.                                  Put yourself in the shoes of the lion tamer or the ring master. You would be a big mess wouldn't you...I bet some of you would hide and run, or just stand there not knowing how to do anything that you intended you thought you knew.To avoid this that's why all members in the circus practice.( in the paragraph above ) Has anybody in the circus mess up? Of coarse they have. Anyone can mess up in a play or performance.ANYONE  Anyone can mess up , but only a few people can cover up a mistake by going along with it.                Traveling around the world is what the circus does. Pretending to be in a circus or be a lion tamer at home to entertain is one thing, but being in the circus is another. Some people can get this one in a lifetime chance of being in the circus, but they have to commit to all the practice,being away from home, and constantly traveling almost nonstop.                   Imagine having a closet full of clothes for all different acts. people in the circus have that .You can't just have one pair of costumes for every act so that is why they have so many costumes.How many places can the circus go in a year? Perhaps hundreds.In a lot of circuses they have a highly trained man or woman who may do magician tricks. Such as Houdini's water tank trick. In this trick someone has to go in a tank full of water while they are in a whole bunch of chains wrapped around their body.               Circus animals are highly trained before acting in the circus. Especially the wild animals such as the leopards and tigers. All these animals need to be trained in order to be in the circus. If not the people working with them might get seriously hurt or even die.

Item_Response: THE CIRCUS                                         BY:CHLOE ARNOLD                 'Yes! We won!' I yelled to Cameron, jumping with excitement.   'What did we win again?' Cameron asked.   ''We get the front row seats to the Bellini Circus!' I screamed with joy. 'Its at 6:30 pm.'   Cameron checked her watch.   ''It starts in seven minutes.' Cameron said. 'We gotta hustle.'             We could hear loud clapping and cheering right outside the entrance. We walked to the front row, and saw a  man tight roping on a unicycle 50 feet in the air!  Clowns were throwing pies at each others faces and a woman was taming a hungry lion with a whip.         Then, we could hear a 'THUMP, THUMP, THUMP' coming from behind a black curtain.   'Elephants!'' We could hear a little girl say. Six of the huge, gray, elephants come stomping out in a line. There is one trainer sitting on top of each elephant, giving it instructions. Then, we heard a loud squeal.   'Its coming from one of the elephants!' Cameron yelled. An elephant lost control and ran into a section of people. There were screams coming from everywhere. The elephant rammed through the red and yellow striped tent and ran away. Cameron grabbed my wrist and started sprinting in the opposite direction.We ran behind a tree and waited until it was all over.

Item_Response: I start climbing across the tight rope. I'm doing an act where I do a handstand and crawl across a tightrope, jump off, do a back flip off a trampoline, and then land on a horse. It is a hard act, and I haven't even completely mastered it yet.                 I'm half way through when my stomach starts to hurt, It feels like to bears fighting inside myself. What could I have done? I think to myself. I've never had stage fright. No, it has to be something else. I only ate what I always eat, So I know it wasn't that.                 I realized that I was tilting on the rope. I try to fix it, but that makes it even worse. I start falling off. Well, might as well make it work. I think to myself. I launch myself off the ripe and did a double back flip. I'm going towards the ground at an alarming rate. I could see my self going towards the ground. I brace for impact.                 Then, out of the corner of my eye, I see my bright white horse, Charlie, running out. My ringmaster must have seen what had been going on. My horse saves me right when I was just about to hit the ground and carries me backstage.                 'Well, that was...interesting' I say as I approach my trainer. His face cracks into a grin. 'I can't wait for the real thing.'

Item_Response: We were finally at the circus after four long hours in the car.  My little sister had wanted to see a special group called the 'Many Men' group.  When she found out that they would be preforming so close to where we live around her birthday she begged my parents for days and even months.  They said yes after making her be patient and then things got better for her worse for me when she won 5 tickets from school.  The reason I said worse for me is a whole other story.      I was seven years old and getting to go to my very first circus.  I was so excited because My parents got very good seats and I had been saving money up for snacks.  I had enough for an ice cream cone, a medium drink and three bags of skittles with $20.00 left.  The minute that I woke up, though, I knew that today was going to be terrible.      We were going to leave my dog at my neighbors house while we were gone those two days.  My older brother and I both felt like we should take him with us but our parents told us to let them handle it and everything would be alright.  We didn't listen.  We were getting into the car when we heard a screech.  We looked up to where the sound came from and gasped at what we saw.  A black  and grey cat dangled from up above.  We mom ran over with her arms out-stretched as if to catch the cat.  It fell after 20 minutes of my mom doing that and we finally got to leave.         After that delay we were keen to leave and miss one of our bathroom breaks.  That wasn't a problem for me because I never drink a thing but my brother drinks at least a liter.  The bathroom break was going to be at the 1/4 mark of the way.  We were about at the halfway mark when it happened.  My brother had an accident in his pants and we had to pull over to let him get into clean clothes.  That was a delay that took 5 minutes. Eever since my brother won't go near a drink while we're on the road.        We had just gotten to the circus, not bothering to go to the hotel after all of those delays.  I grasped my coin purse that held my money and we headed inside.  My dad took my brother to go get our seats and my mom took me to the consesion stand to get us snacks.  I ordered for myself  a small chocolate ice cream cone and a medium slush.  My mom got a big pretzal with cheese and a large sprite.  We got my brother two bags of ms and my dad a water.  We found my brother and my dad a minute later and the show began.  Halfway in the show my brother fell over the ledge and into the arena.  We had to go home early because we disrupted the show.  My dog was fine but that was the worst experience that I had ever gone through in entire life.  That was the reason that I didn't want to go with my sister to the circus for her birthday.
