Item_Response: The Mmissing Ttiger              Once upon a time there was a girl named Elizabeth.(Lizzy for short!) Lizzy lives an amazing life at a circus. She got to travel around the world. She see's many different places that have very different people with interesting cultures. Another thing about Lizzy is that she has a best friend that performs with her. Her best friend is a white tiger named  'The amazing Tortellini.'.               Lizzy and Tortellini do a very fun act in the circus. They do a trick  where Lizzy rides in on two white horses. Tortellini is stuck in a cage on the other side of the area being laughed at by three clowns. Lizzy dodges a number of different obstacles and jumps of off the two white horses. she land on a big rubber ball and works her way over to the cage. When she gets there she jumps off of the ball sending it forward and knocking out the first clown. then she uses karate on the other two. She saves the tiger and the crowd go's wild. She often does photo's after each act.                one day Lizzy got out of bed and went to see Ttortellini but, he wasn't there. she asked the worker that was on cage duty if he knew where the tiger was but he didn't. She looked every where and asked every single worker that she possibly could if they had seen the tiger. They all let her down. The next day her parents,(who were clowns putting on all their makeup for the big shoe tonight), let her go to town. She hung posters up all over town. Soon the news about the missing tiger was every where even on the news. the animal catchers were every where, patrolling the city, dart guns in hand. Lizzy decided to go search for the tiger her self.                  In just seven days she had been to three different states looking and asking people about tortellini. In approximately two months she had been to two different country's and to so many different states that she lost count, and she still had no sign of the tiger. Meanwhile back at home, Lizzy's parents had sent out three search party's every day, three times a day. they were worried sick about their little girl.                 A couple of months later , Lizzy had made it all the way from AAustin Texas, to some where in London. She had not even seen a hair from the soft, furry, coat of the white tiger. ' It's like he just dissapeared.' She thought. Then all of the  sudden some thing knocks her over from behind, and starts licking all over her face.  When the licking finally stopped, Lizzy looked up and saw some thing that was very unexpected.  Tortellini was standing right in front of her looking as happy as could be. ' Tortellini!' screamed Lizzy. ' I thought I'd never see you again!!!' And Lizzy took her best friend and went home.               After about five months of walking, jogging, and running, Lizzy and the tiger finally made it back home. Lizzy was thinking about how her parents were going to act when they saw her. Were they going to ground her for the rest of her life? Were they going to make me clean up elephant poo for a month or two? Well there's only one way to find out. She thought. So she tied Tortellini to a post and went into her parents trailer.  As soon as her parents saw her they jumped up and gave her a giant hug. They told her that they missed her so much and how they wouldn't let the circus go on without you. They also told her how they new that she would find her way back home because she was such a determined young lady. But the two things they didn't do was ground her or make her clean up the Elephant poo.              Lizzy grew up and started a circus of her own. She had a lot of animals and people doing very different acts. but the best act out of all of them was the one including a little girl and her best friend. The white tiger.                                                             The end

Item_Response: The Regular Circus Way                     As I walked out of school I saw a guy pacing a paper on a billboard.         Once the guy was done, I saw a picture of elephants and many clowns, all behind a  yellow back splash with the elephant dressed in a royal blue rug around their waist and the clowns had on their regular poke-a-dotted baggie genie uniforms that make them look like there sixty year old trying to put on a show.          ' Hey Maggie.' said Leo as he looked up to see what I was looking at. ' Hi.' I said unenthusiastically. ' I...um... see they have a circus going on in town tonight.' ' Ya, isn't lame. People dressed like there sixty and there trying to put on a show!' I said as I realized my temperature was rising and decided to tone it down.' It's stupid.' I murmured.                   Leo obviously didn't hear me because the next thing I know Leo's asking me if I want to go.' Wh...wh...what?' ' Ya you know go to the circus.'                    Then, off I go to the circus and me going to watch the elephants.                    'That was great!!' I said,' I'm definitely going next year!

Item_Response: The life at the circus                          If you think that the circus is fun then you are thinking just like me. Me, Kautious McNeil, loves working at the circus. Me and my family live in a gigantic mansion. We travel all over the world every 6 months. We visit 250 cities each year.                  This is the time I get up every day to work:                        6:30 A.M. I get up and brush my teeth, wash my face , take a shower and get dressed.Then I go to the kitchen to get some pancake and sausages.We all setup the lights, the tents, adn music for tonight.                                      9:30 A.M. is school time, I get all of my books and things for school. Then I put inside my bookbag just in case I need it for school. Just like any other kind of school we had computers, desks and ect. Because, I was a circus performer all over the world, some of my classmates had different languages:Chinese, Japinese, Russian.   The more we would travel the more I would learn about it in school.                      3:30 P.M. it is dissmissal time in school, meant that it was time to go home. The clowns let me ride their small cars and their juggling balls. I also played with my puppy,Pluto. Now its almost time for me to practice for the circus. so i put up Pluto and began to clean up.                          6:30 P.M. dinner time now. after I have finish dinner, now it's time to go to the show. We do a show every saturday and friday.   now the show is over at  10:45 P.M. I am so tired now, I am so ready to go home and get in the bed and go to sleep.                    1:30 A.M. Now I am in bed. I'm dreaming about becoming a acrobat this time. I can not wait until it is time for the touring season. I cannot wait until we go to Flordia for the summer break. Still when I grow up I want to be an acrobat in the circus. Do you think that will happen? It's still tough, busy, and fun just like always.

Item_Response: Working At the Circus                                                         by:yphai bkrong                                                          My name is yphai bkrong.i work at the circus.It is very hard because i have to do alot of work.I have to train the animals,prastce my stunts i also have to help others train.it takes alot of work to work at the circus.I have to travel around the world and do the same tricks or practice a new one every month.i live in a trailer with my family and a dog named crouchy.I usually wake up at 6:00 A.M in the morning to work but first i have to go to a pie car to eat breakfeast then i groom my dog.My sister is and acrobat she does trick my brother is an circus tightrope walker.My dad a circus juggler.               For our matinee it starts at 5:00 P.M it ends at 11:00 P.M i get to bed a 12:00 P.M because i have to clean up all the other things that people are done using. Some people keep there equipment.It takes a long time to clean up because of the trash people throw on the ground.Most circus performers like to stay up and do other stuff.we also use animals as performers such as lions,tiger,bears,birds and other wild animals.It is fun to play with the animals sometimes.               we travel all over the country italy,south america,north,america we travel almost all over the world.We travel by trains and ships.we sometimes dont have to travel.I sometimes miss home because i never get to see it i always have to travel from one place to another.my family have really fun time at the circus because they always get to watch for free cause  my siblings and my dad work there.Everyone that work there really like how it is.I always stay with my brother because it is fun to play around.Circuses look small but they are big you have to be very active to work at a circus.                People think it is easy to work at the circus but it is not.You have to practice alot to be able to get better at it.It takes hard work determination to be able to do tricks.Most of the tricks are scary.It takes a long time to get better at it.Some peoples parents are people are circus performers at the circus so it is easy for them to do tricks and stunts from there parents.The circus is alot of fun.Once you see a circus it will be alot of fun.

Item_Response: The Circus!              Have you ever been to the circus? If not well don't worry today I'll tell you all about the circus. I'm Jane Parks I'm originally a Circus Acrobat from Circus Town you may or may not have heard of it but I travel all over the U.S. My mother and father Mr and Mrs Robin and Mike Parks Travel with me. They're also in the circus. My mother is a tightrope walker, and my father is a circus juggler, but lets talk more about the circus and not about me.             The circus is a terrific place. We travel about 20,000 miles every year, you think that's a pain in the neck take a look at my schedule below.           Here's my schedule:          7:00 A.M. - I get up brush my teeth and my hair get dressed and go down to the pie-car to eat breakfast while the crew sets up for tonights performance. (The pie-car is where circus performers go to eat breakfast, lunch, and dinner.)          9:30 A.M.-2:30 P.M. - Time for school. Our school isn't that big it's a one room school house but we still have just about everything regular schools have like computers, tests, report cards and reading logs. Sometimes as we travel we perform with people that don't speak our language like once we were performing in Mexico and most of the students in my class spoke Spanish, I know a little Spanish but not enough to communicate with them so I just stayed quiet.          3:00 P.M.- School is over. This is usually the time to take a break and relax and play with friends or pets. I usually go to play with the my dog Snowball.          3:30 P.M.- 6:00 P.M.- At this time I would probably be doing daily chores and practice. I water, feed, and groom the three horses that we perform with. Then I have to put the head and body piece on the elephants.          6:30 P.M.- Time for dinner. Before our show we go back to the pie-car for dinner, but don't eat to much because after dinner we perform and the last thing you want is to get a stomach ache in the middle of the show, trust me its happened to me before.          7:00 P.M.- Getting ready for the show as I put on my performance suit.          11:00 P.M. - Show is over the day is done. I am exhausted and ready to fall back on the bed and go to sleep.          12:00 A.M.-In bed ... falling .......asleep... Zzz... sorry dozed off there for a second. Well I better end this before I doze off again.              Well there you have it, a nice little schedule about what happens in the circus everyday. I'm getting a little tired myself I better hit the hay before I fall asleep too.

Item_Response: A Circus Life                      It is hard to work at a circus.It is hard to be a circus performer because you have to go to wake up and get ready then you need to go to school, do chores,practice, eat dinner, take a shower, then go to sleep.If you think that working at the circus is really fun, it is but you also have to do your living like any other and especially a lot more.                              At 7:00 they have to wake up and get dress.Then they go to a pie car to eat breakfast.Then after they have o prepare for the show that going to happen tonight.So they first have to set up the tents.When there done doing that they then go fix the lighting.Afterwards they fix up the music and make sure everything is going just fine.                          At 9:00 after they are done setting up for the show tonight,they have to then go to school like any other family.There school might not be like ours but they still have to do test,reports, and a lot of homework.They also have computers like any other school.They don't just do that they also have to speak many different languages  because they travel around the whole world and the countries they sometimes go they speak different languages like French,Russian,and Italian.As they travel around the country their geographic lesson comes alive.                         At 3:30 they have to start doing a lot of chores.First they feed,water, and groom.then they also sometimes practice while doing there chores. So like your dad might uses somersaulting off a running horse.You would work on leaping on a trampoline onto the horses back, it takes a lot of balance and concentration.The others are then practicing juggling and acrobatics.Their neighbors walk baby leopards on a leash.The other trainers are working with the animals such as elephant,lions,and chimpanzees.                        At 6:30 It is dinnertime and the family and they go to eat at the pie car, but they don't really eat much because they are performing and they might do flips and they don't really want to bommet.If you work at the circus you have to work 10 shows a week so if you are going to be a circus person it might be tiring.                        At 10:30 when the show is over you might be wiped out and you have to walk it back to your trailer passing the circus office,conssesion stands, stables and trailers.Then two days from there they would go to another town and setup.                       At 12:00 you take a shower and think about how you did in the touring season. You might want to move back to your hometown where you were born.Then you go to sleep.                        When you grow up you may want to be a circus performer and think it will be fun but it may also be a hard challenge because you have lots of things to do  in the morning throughout the night and get to have a little sleep.The circus is fun but is a busy and a tough life.

Item_Response: Hi my name is Emma and today I'll be telling you about what my life is like in the circus.    Today were in Las Vegas,Nevada and I just got up and right now I'm practicing for the circus , I'm a lion tamer.The lions are very friendlily and sweet, what I do with the lions is very fun.What I do as my act with the lions is I put them on their stands and they walk around on them and then it's time for the fun ,they jump off the stands and stand on their hind legs for a second and then come back down  they walk around me a couple of times then I go on the stand then,  and one of them follows me up then I sit on that one that came on the stand and ride on  it back stage.     I wake up in the morning and me and my friends meet up and practice,a couple of my friends are trapeeze artists and some of my other friends are dancers their acts are amazing! tonights another show and I got to watch my friends what an awesome job they did!     As people say practice makes perfect .You just have to practice. So if you want to be in the circus practice hard.      And thats my story of how my life is in the circus.

Item_Response: I'm just an average kid, with one exception. I work at the circus. Although most people think that being in the circus is an easy job, they're wrong. I have a very busy schedule. I'm occupied for most of the day.                 In the morning, I go to the pie cart and eat breakfast (7:00 A.M.) then I go to school at 9:00. I learn geography and math today. Soon, my geography lesson will come alive when we move to another city. At three school is over. I get a break for awhile. I get to ride on the unicycles and juggle, but soon my break is over. At three thirty I go do my chores and practice, I groom the horses and give them oats and a bucket of water. I have to keep my skills up so I can do the shows.                  Three hours later at six thirty I go get dinner with my family. We don't eat too much because we have a show and don't want to get cramps. I go to the main circus tent and get ready for the upcoming show. Lights. Camera. Action. The stage comes to life as everyone moves about. I brace myself and do a triple back flip of a diving board into a tub full of water. As I do this I think that it's really strange that my parents want me to do circus. They never get worried that I would fall or sprain an ankle, or even break a bone! I wonder why. Is it because they believe I have something for circus and I'm very talented? Or maybe they're just careless. Whatever the case they don't worry that I'll fall. I come out of the water and a lion jumps over my head. The crowd cheers. I leap out of the water and run up a ladder. A tightrope comes into my field of view and my heart starts thumping. This is my favorite part. I start walking across the tightrope. I pretend to lose my balance halfway through. The crowd gasps. Just as it seems I'm going to fall I grab the rope with my feet and lift my arms up to pull myself across. I get off the ladder at the other end and leap onto a horse that then throws me right onto another horse. That horse throws me up in the air and I come falling back to the earth, but, a lion comes and breaks my fall. I get off and take a bow. The crowd goes wild. They talk with each other and make gestures with their hands.                  All the performers go back to there trailers. I'm exhausted, but I can't wait until the next show. Now it's ten thirty so I go back to my trailer. On the way there are lots of venders and booths, but most don't have anyone in them. When I get back to my trailer I plop down on my bed, exhausted. I can't wait until the next show. I think about how in two days I'll be leaving this city and move to the next. I drift off to sleep on a matter of minutes.

Item_Response: AT THE CIRCUS                                                                One day at the circus the worlds best clown came and said hows it going guys then fell to the ground.In shock the crowd started to cry but then he got back up and said the show must go on.But it was to late the worlds best clown past away but before he died I said I would take his spot In honor of the worlds best clown. Item_Response: CIRCUS!            Yesterday we went to the circus and it was a lot of fun we saw stacking elephants and tightrope walkers and even clowns they were really scary.Yeah ,it was the best experience ever! Me and my friend Kristin went together to the Puyallup circus and we had a blast, me and Kristin were both in the front row and it was scary because when the elephants stacked they just about fell our way and we both screamed it was a bit embarrassing everyone was silent.                      The circus is a lot of fun but when I talked with one of the clowns I felt kinda bad I mean he never gets too see his family anymore there just in one place for so long and with the hours they work and the only day they get off it would be really hard to live like that.That night me and Kristin had a sleep over she was asleep but I just layed there with my eyes wide open just thinking what it would feel like to not be able to see your family.                  That next morning me and Kristin had break feast after I asked her about how she would feel if she were that clown she said ' I don't exactly know?'.Kristin left that afternoon it was still bothering me but I sort of let it go when we went to the circus again I don't know how so don't ask me.                    I asked my mom if we could go to the circus again just me and her she told me 'I guess so'.That next day we went to the circus but I didn't see that one clown that did the juggling I asked someone who worked what had happened to him he said 'he quit and he said something about going up to California to see his family his wife Teresa and his daughter Jordan and his little boy on the way Daniel.'                           I was shocked but so so so so so so so sooooooo happy for him!                 In the end everything turned out good I called Kristin and told her the news she felt the same way I did so when you go to a circus make sure you don't make fun of the people thank them for giving up there family and friends to travel all around the world to entertain you.                                                                                     THE END!               (BY THE WAY THIS STORY IS NOT TRUE I JUST MADE IT UP)

Item_Response: The Chicago Circus                                                              There once was a circus in Chicago. It had all kinds of animals, elephants, lions, tigers, bears, ponies, horses.  We have kids on motor cycles riding in cages shaped like a ball, the bear juggling on top of a ball, the horses and ponies dancing to Mexican music, the elephant squirting water to the audience, lions doing the hula hoop, and the tiger goes through a hoop, but, the hoop is on fire.   One day Melanie went to school and handed out flyers for the show.  The flyers worked because a lot of people came.  But this show was not good because the tiger got on fire when he went through the hoop. Then the whole tent got on fire. It was a disaster.  Then they lost the job.                                                        It was a month later, Melanie's dad got a call on his phone. It was they circus company.  They said that will give them another chance but, if they mess up, no more chances.  Melanie and her dad were so excited. They called everybody so they can start practicing as soon as possible. They got the animals back. Melanie handed out papers at school and her dad handed put them on walls. They where back in business. Today was the show. Both of them where supper nervous. It was the beginning of the show, everything started out good. Then it came to the tigers performance. Tiger made it through with out catching on fire!  It was a perfect show! They get to keep the job!  Yay!

Item_Response: One of the upsides of being in the circus is that you get the chance to travel the world. Philippa has worked all over the planent, including Australia, Japan and all North America. The circus has given me the opportunity to go so many different places and meet so many different people. I travel on the road with 100 people who are like a circus family to me, who are with me the whole time. When you're young, it's the time to do it. It's the time to travel, the time to grow and experince your life. Philippa also gets a thrill from performing in front of  a live audience. I get to play and have fun every night. It's great to see the faces of the audience just jump alive when I make eye contact with them during the performance. You can see the audience being transpoterd to antother world. Despite what many peoplr think, the life of a circus performer isn't all high flying fun games and clowning around. And more glamores than being a accountant, but there are some drawbacks.

Item_Response: Circus             'Hello everybody and welcome to the amazing circus!!!' Mr.Pamper said,he is the one how runs the circus.He coaches the circus people and help them practice.              'Now Mr.Pamper can I amaze them with my act?' I said to Mr.Pamper.Hi,I'm Katherine,and I'm,in the circus.I'm an acrobat.I can do flips,jumps and a whole bunch of  other things.               'Yes you may.'he told me.I knew I wanted to be an acrobat when I saw my first circus show,I was 10.I saw the acrobat doing those jumps,flips and other things to.So when I got home from school everyday,I went outside everyday and stretched.By the time I was 15????? I was able to stick my feet over my head and make a circle with my body.               You guys might think being in the circus is amazing as people say,it isn't.You have to practice all day and practice is all i ever do.It might be different for other people but for me it is always going places and having fun.Here is my schedule.                 5:00:I get up around 5:05 and then take a shower.eat,brush my teeth.7:30:Practice bending my body and practice retinue.Go around the city and take pictures.11:35:Eating lunch.Go back exercise some more.Bend body some more.Practice retinue again.I do that for about an 4 hours.4:00:Getting ready for show.6:30:Showing starting,still practicing.Ready for retinue.Show starting.                The show has started.                    'Now for the amazing Katherine and her lovely friend Jared!!!!'Mr.Pamper said.We did our retinue.It was awesome.So that is what usually happens in my day at the circus.

Item_Response: Well, life in the circus is very fun but it is also very hard work. I'm in my yard right now practicing my juggling which I think I have the hook of! It is kind of like I have a second family. Alot of people want to be in the circus but aren't very determined, you have to be determined if you want to be in the circus.       I love to being in the circus because it is very fun and challenging, and I love a good challenge. I love all of the traveling and seeing all of the different places in the world. I also love all of the animals but they are a little smelly. I love alot about the circus but my favorite thing about it is performing!       The thing that I don't like about the circus is that there are alot of long tiring days. You are away from home alot. You also don't see your family alot either. The only thing that you really think about is the show that night.        The circus is really fun! Don't let the down sides keep you from trying out the circus. You would probably have alot of fun if you were in the circus. I hope you like the circus just as much as I do and I hope you try it out someday!

Item_Response: I wake up in the at 7:00 A.M. in the morning. I look out the trailer window to see the birds are still chirping for the sun to rise and I can smell the sent of pancakes and bacon coming from the pie car. My favorite! I run over to dad's bed and tug his covers off with a rip. Oops, i probably shouldn't tell him about that, good thing he was asleep. I walk away like nothing happened, suddenly i hear a loud roar. Uh oh was a lion loose. I turned around to see my dad was the one making all that noise. Seriously. 'Somebody was bugging me in my sleep!' my dad says loudly. I start laughing so hard I fall over. He does this almost every morning, it's hilarious. We walk over to the pie car and gobble down our breakfast. School starts at 9:00 A.M. so i have to get ready fast. In our school people speak different languages. Another thing cool about our school is that as we travel on tour for our circus our social studies lessons come to life. 3:00 P.M. School is over and I get to play around a bit with the clowns. This is the only free time I have during the day. 3:30 P.M. and it's time to practice my act. Today I am practicing jumping from a trampoline onto a horses back. My dad is practicing somersaulting off of a running horse. 6:30 P.M. is when dinner comes around I can't pick out the sent of what the cooks are cooking, but I know it is something light on our stomachs because we can't eat to much before the night shows. Today especially because it is a Wednesday and we have a matinee after the main show. We go through the show with no problem. During the show it is fun to see the audience come alive with you and your acts. 10:30 and the show is over I am wiped out. It is late at night now and I'm thinking if I will stay in the circus like my parents or not. 'The circus sure is fun,' I think to myself, 'but it can definitely be busy and for sure tough.'

Item_Response: In the story Life's a Circus,  Bella Castini know differently. She was a clown. She live in a trailer. She would travel 20,000 miles in 7 months each year. In 1 year she would visit 150 cities. Bella would work from a sunup to a sundown.         Bella had to do a lot of stuff as a kid. At 7:00 A.M. she have to wake up, get dressed, and go to the pie car for pancakes and bacon. At 9:00 A.M. it was school time. Her one-room schoolhouse travels with her. At 3:00 P.M. school is over for a quick break.          At  3:30 it would be time for her chores and practice. At 6:30 P.M. it would be dinner time for them. They would go in the pie car to eat. They would also perform 10 shows a week. At 10:30 P.M. the show time is over. Bella would be wiped out. The last thing they would do was at 12:00 A.M. By that time she would be thinking about the end of touring season.

Item_Response: Life in a Circus                   Life in a circus is fun but, crazy!I live in a big trailer with my family,we travel 20,000 miles in seven months each year,visiting 150 cities.7:00 A.M.get dressed,go eat pancakes and bacon in the pie car.              9:00 A.M.School.School travels with us.Circus performers are from all around the world so they speak different languages: French ,Russian, Italian and more.3:00 P.M.Schools over,after we take a quick break we play with the clowns unicycles and juggling balls.               3:30 P.M.Chores and Practice: Feed, water groom horses so the horses will be ready for the show.My family   practices somersaulting off a running horse.I work on leaping from a trampoline onto the horses back it takes balance!other kids are practicing juggling and acrobatics.                6:30 A.M.Dinner we go to the pie car and eat we don't eat much because we have to do are show.10 shows a week :one each weekday plus a matinee on Wednesday , Saturday and Sunday two shows.10:30 P.M. shows over were tired and wiped out we give are all in are shows to make sure they adiance enjoys it as much as we do.                 12:00 A.M. in bed thinking about our season tour I am so excited for every state to see are circus we are going to practice and work as hard as we can!                    I HOPE YOU GET TO SEE ARE CIRCUS SOME DAY!

Item_Response: Being in a circus has its ups and downs. It takes dedication, skills,and confidence. Not everyone can be in a circus and if you are going to be in one you need to know that your scudele will be filled. Every minute counts.       Your morning will be similar to this. You wake up at 7:30 get ready and eat your breakfest while the other staff sets up the tents and other things for tonights show. If your a chiled around 8:30 is when you go to school and learn about things any other student would along with the history of the circus.       School is done at about 3:30 and i help out with the chores and rehersal. I tend the animals by feeding them, bathing them, and getting them show ready. At rehersal we go threw all the acts and make sure everything goes smoothly. Finnaly at 6:00 sharp the show starts and we perform in front of our audience of 600 people. Let the show begin!      At 8:00 the show is done and we are all tired. We eat a big meal then shut all the lights of and wash all the makeup on our faces. Im in bed by 11:00 and I think about the show and my home back in Arizona.       Its 7:30 and I am ready for another day at the circus.

Item_Response: The Circus                     This was a big day. Maggie had been in the circus for a long time but she had never been in a show before. This was her day and she was determined to make it perfect. If she messed up she would promise herself never to go into public again.                 She got herself dressed into her nicest clothes and decided to go out into the fresh morning air. Once she got outside she ran over to the gym to practice her part in the show. When she got there she noticed her dad was already there practicing tightrope walking.                When she walked in she startled him and made him fall. She wasn't afraid for him though because she knew her father was a great acrobat too. She watched him fall and then bounce off air as he grabbed the rope to stop himself from falling all of the way.                 That night, the night of the show, Maggie was more nervous than ever. She kept on trying to run back to her camper but her dad stopped her every time. Maggie had to be an acrobat and didn't want to have to do that in front of millions of people because she was afraid she would mess up.                 It was finally her turn and she went out onto the stage. She jumped up onto the rope and started to climb as high as she could. Then she started to swing the rope and hung upside down while it was swinging. She heard ooh and aah as she did the rest of her part without any mistakes.                 At the end she was so relieved that she had done it right she decided she wanted to be in the circus forever. Even though she did make mistakes sometimes, Maggie grew up to be a famous acrobat.

Item_Response: THE CIRCUS                                                                                                   by: Annabella  Esquivel                                                      Stephanie Roberts, a 12 year-old girl, who is in the circus, has a very full, adventorous, and exciting life. Every day of her life is full of tamed lions, flexible acrobats, horn hoking clowns, and cheers from the audience when she does a show.                     Stepahanie's act in the circus is the tightrope, cannon balling, and doing acrobat acts. ' The cannon balling is my favorite act because, when my brother lights the cannon with a match, I feel like I'm flying.' qoutes Stephanie.                    If you thought Stephanie travels alone in the circus, well, you thought wrong! she travels in the circus with her older brother Scott, older sister Samantha, younger brother Jimmy, mom Jessica, and dad Brian. Each year, Stephanie and her family travel hundreds and thousands of miles.                   Being in the circus can be fun and games and all, but there's also your studies and dedication that you put into your act in the circus. Stephanie and her family also travel with lots of helpers that help with putting up the tents, music, lights, and training for their acts.                     Stephanie and her family live in an R.V. during the circus. They eat in there, play games, and eat. When the Roberts family are not doing the circus, they spend thier time in thier two story house on the beach in Miami, Flordia. The Roberts family do the show 7 times a week. One each day of the week. They do the circus for 2 1/2 months and then go home. That is 'THE CIRCUS'

Item_Response: The Circus                                          By:Elecziahn                One day me and my mom won tickets to the circus so we got front row seats and circus treats and drinks. Me and my mom was excited because we got speciall treatment and we were waiting on our favorite thing to see was the Circus Acrobats and we never got a chance to see them in real life and it was great for me and my mom to see .So as me and my mom were trying to keep quite from being excited the host asked us are we ready and everybody  said 'YES,' and he said alright then and that when something special came out.                When some of the lights cut off i was scared but when two lights came shining on two people on ropes everybody in the crowd was like 'OOOHHH,' 'AHHHHH,' then the lights got darker and darker because when the lights cut back on they were hanging upside down meaning they were really upside down.               So yea it was fun but, it got funnier because the Circus Clowns came out and they were on little bikes fighting each other with balloon swords and one of them had fell off of the bike and the one that didn't fall off of his bike got up and squirt the man in the eye with a flower and the they just kept falling it was just really 'FUNNY,'  and it was so funny that when my mom was laughing she was crying at the same time and it was just funny the whole time.                The next thing we saw was a Circus Juggler and it was cool because the man had 6 bowling pins and 2 hoops and then he started to juggle everything all at once and he went in a pattern like over and under , up and down and even round and about all over the place then he ask for a volunteer, lucky me because he choose ' ME'!! and guess what he ask me to do? He asked me to go and hold a hula-hoop and he had 6 bowling pins and 2 small hula-hoops and then he jumped threw the hula-hoops and then started to juggle it was amazing and I thought he was going to hit me but he didn't. 'WOW,'                   The Circus Tightrope-Walker came out and it look like he was going to fall way up there but he didn't he was very careful and then he did a split up there and laned right on the rope i thought it had hurt but it didn't and after the show me and my mom got to take pictures with the performers and we got a free snake on our way home so i told my mom that we must be the luckey ones today and she said yea and then that was it  for today                                                THE END!!

Item_Response: If you want to work in a circus,you would have a busy schedule.You would have to wake up at 7:00 A.M. to get dressed,and go to the pie car for pancakes and bacon.The crews are setting up tents, lights, and music for the show.That is alot already, I would be sleepy.They are setting up for the show.If I was at that show I wouldn't be able to wait.            Then at 9:00 A.M. you would have to go to school.The one-room schoolhouse would travel with you.Like other schools your school has computers,tests,and you get report cards.Circus performers are from all over the world, many of the performers speak other languages like French, Russian, and Italian.As you travel around the world,your geography lessons come alive.            Then at 3:00 P.M. school will be over,you will have a break.you might see clowns there sense it is a circus school.If you do see a clown they might let you play on their unicycles and juggle their balls.You can also play with one of the circus dogs.They might even have a tiger there, but I would stay away from that if I were you.            Then at 3:30 P.M.Time to do chores and practice.You would have to treat the horse.You wiil have to groom it and feed it.You might see people somersaulting off a horse.You might see people jumping from a trampoline onto the horse's back.            At 6:30 P.M. It would be dinnertime.For dinnertime you have to go to the pie car again.You don't want to eat alot because you have to preform at the circus.You would have to do 10 shows.After the show is over,you would walk back to the trailer, and wipe off all of the makeup.After you wipe off all of your makeup you would go back home and do all of that stuff the next day.

Item_Response: My life in the Circus is pretty hard because we have to travel 20,000 miles, in 7 months each year.We visit 150 cities. Here a typical day for me:                            7:00 A.M.    I wake up,get dressed,and go to the pie car (1) for pancakes and bacon. The crews are setting up tents,lights, and music for tonight's show.                           9:00 A.M. School time.              Our one-room schoolhouse travels with us. Like any school,ours has computers,tests, and report cards.Because the circus performers are from all over the world, many of my classmates speak other languages:French,Russian, and Italian, like my family. As we travel around the country, our geography lessons come alive.       3:00  P.M.  School's over.   school's over-time for quick break. The clowns let me play with their unicycles(2) and juggling balls. I also play with my tiny dog, Noble; our trailer is too small for a large pet. I'd like to join a soccer team, but we're never in one place long enough.               3:30 P.M. Chores and practice.   I feed, water, and groom(3) the horses we use in our horseback acts. Today, my dad practices somersaulting off a running horse. I'm working in leaping from a trampoline onto the horse's back; it takes balance and concentration.Other kids are practicing juggling and acrobatics. Our neighbor walks baby leopardson a leash. Trainers are working with elephants,Lions, and chimpanzees.              6:30 P.M. Dinnertime.   My family and I go to the pie car to eat , but we don't eat that much because we're preforming tonight. We do 10 shows a week: one each weekday,plus a matinee(4) on Wednesday, two on Saturday, and tow on Sunday.            10:30 P.M. The show is over.   I'm wiped out(5). Walking back to our trailer, we pass the circus offices, concession stands, stable, and trainers. Two days from now, we'll all set up in another town.                 12:00 A.M.  In bed.   I'm thinking about the end of our real home in Florida. When i grow up, will i still be a circus performer like my parents? Who I still be a citrus performer like my parents? Who knows? The citrus is fun, but it's a busy and tough life.                  This is how you can be a circus performer go to htt://WWW.kidzworld.com/article/4481-becoming-a-circus-performer                Becoming a Circus Performer                Have you ever dreamed of running away from  home and joining the circus? Think you have what it takes to be a acrobat or a trapeze artist, you think you have what it takes? To find out some of the ins and outs of becoming a circus performer, kidzworld  spoke with Philippa Handball, an acrobat and dancer with Cirque du Soleil's circus, Quidam.                Circus Performers - Getting Started            Not everyone can get in the circus and become an acrobat or a trapeze artist. You have to have the right body type and a specific talent. When Philippa's was five years old she stared in the circus. She did  Ballet , and  musical theater and all kinds of music, singing, acting and home craft. When Philippa was 11 years old she know what she want to be when she grow up a performer. So, she went for it. She gave up everthing else and concentraed  on her way for dancing and performing.                   Circus Performers - The Upside              Philippa got the change to go travel the world.  she go to see many different places and meet many different people. she traveled with 100 people.      Circus Performers - The Downside          The circus is not high-flying fun and games and clowing areund, but it is more than  just fun and ggames you have to work hard every day. But you can have some fun but you have to work. The circus you have to send time away form home. You have to do shows on the  weekdays and on the weekends. You do not get to seeyour family. You have to work long hours and weekends as well. You have to want it if you want to be a perfomer because you do not get to  see your family and you have to work long house.                                       BY: KAMRON A CHESEBRO-FILDS

It is easy to get used to the stratagies.  The curcus life is tough but fun.

Item_Response: Life in the circus                     At 7:00 A.M Mia has to wake up, got dressed, went to there car and ate pancakes and bacon when the crew is setting up the cameras,the tent, lights, music, and more.           9:00 A.M Mia has to go to school and do homework, other work, test, and a lot more but most of the people in her class speak different languages that she does not like at all. All Mia wishes is if she could be in a class with all Americans. But Mias class come true like the geography because they travel around the county.           3:00 PM Mia's classes are over and she gets a break before the show. She plays on the clowns unicycle and plays with her cute little dog named Noddle. But Mia wishes she had more to her life. She wants to join a soccer team, or play a fun sport. She wants to go back to her home state Michigan, But she is to busy working in the circus when she feels like she does not belong beacuse she is only 11.           4:00 PM Mia does her chores and practices for the the circus because she has 10 shows a week and when she is done she is wiped out because there shows are so long. But this show was going to be  her best show because it was time for her to step up her game and become a acrobat!       6:00 PM My family and I eat dinner but not to much dinner because tonight we had a show coming up. We eat like that on a normal basic scedueal.           10:00 PM Mia comes back from the circus and she was so happy and tired. Happy because she did so great in that performance she wishes she could do it again. Then she thinks that she can do it again because she will do it tomorrow and that made her think being in the circus is what she is good at and that she is going to stay in the circus for now and see that happens next!           12:00 PM Mia is in her bed thinking about how good she did last night and how she wants to do it again because she never gave up on what she did so she could be moved up to a trapized artist acrbat or even a tightrope walker.               By: Courtney

Item_Response: At 6:30 A.M Lily Variant and James Variant's alarm goes off. They open their sleepy eyes and stare out at their magnificent view of the Eiffel Tower. The sun is just coming up and is peaking through the holes of the Eiffel Tower. The crisp autumn air fills their lungs as a breeze enters through their open window. They drag themselves out of bed and into the bathroom. They are in a circus in Paris, France and are the famous twin trapeze artists with an act called Fire and Ice.            Half an hour later they are roaming along the cobblestone streets of Paris looking for their favorite chocolate shop, A Dream in Chocolate. Finally they spot the chocolate shop. It has old stone walls, a wooden door, a small sign above the door with fading purple paint, and three stone steps that lead up to the shop. It has a strong aroma of cocoa that you can smell from a mile away. They walk up the steps and into the shop. The store is amazing! It has rows of truffles, chocolate eggs, chocolate bark, chocolate hearts, chocolate covered strawberries and more all sorted by milk chocolate, white chocolate , and dark chocolate. The twins walk up to the counter and order their favorite, dark chocolate hot cocoa with milk chocolate truffles dipped in it.           Once they finish the hot cocoa they sneak back into the circus arena. They are not supposed to eat at chocolate shops, they are supposed to eat at the circus's pie car. At 8:30 they rush the circus's school where they learn French, English, Math, Spelling and much more. They listen to their teacher drown on and on until finally at 1:00 schools over. They walk to the circus arena to start practicing. The circus arena is a large tent rainbow colored with bright gold stars and flashing colored lights. During the show it is where everyone preforms, where all the seats are, and where they will be selling sickly sweet cotton candy that dissolves in your mouth faster than any other kind and buttery popcorn that smells so good you just can't resist.             James and Lily harness up and practice dancing through the air, flipping and catching each other. Finally it is time for the real show. James and Lily watch eagerly as other people preform tricks with lions and juggle swords until finally the announcer calls, ' And now introducing the fantastic, the amazing, the thrilling, Fire and Ice!' James and Lily hold their poses as they get hoisted up into the air , then finally the break their poses and burst into a scene of dancing a flipping and spinning in mid air so magical that it transports you to a different world.              At 10:30 the show is over and James and Lily get out their costumes and curl up into bed until tomorrow when they wake up and go through the routine all over again.

Item_Response: The Perfect Show       It was a bright sunny day in March.All the kids were outside because it was to hot to be inside.Everyone was outside eating ice cream or getting wet.Everyone except Mackenzie.       She was inside practicing to be a acrobat.That was the only thing she wanted to be.She had gave up everything else but being an acrobat.She specifically wanted to be a acrobat.Not a lion tamer,not a ring master,not a clown,NO,she wanted to be an acrobat.       'MACKENZIE!I told you to go outside two hours ago.'Mackenzie's mom yelled.'Hey mom!Guess what?I'm going to win this contest the 5th grade teachers are doing!And what is the prize Mackenzie?Two TICKETS TO SEE ONE SHOW AT THE CIRCUS!AND WE GET TO MEET AND TAKE A PICTURE WITH ONE OF THE PERFORMERS!That sounds lovely Mackenzie.All I have to do is come in 1st,2nd,3rd,4th,or 5th in the marathon they are having.The only problem is,it's tomorrow'       Sure enough the day was here.Mackenzie took everything she needed.She took her high flying air breathing running shoes.The marathon was in the morning.All the contestants were stretching.Mackenzie started to get nervous.READY,SET,GO!The race was off!Mackenzie was in second place so far.She tried to get to first but Randy,the fastest fifth grade runner,was in first.They all had to run 4 laps.Mackenzie was on her last lap.She was in 2nd place,about to catch up to Randy.They were around the corner,almost to the finish line.Mackenzie caught up to Randy!She won and finished in 1st place!She was the HAPPIEST girl on earth.Mackenzie got a trophy and 2 tickets to go to the circus!       The rest of the week went by fast.All she could think about was the circus on Saturday.By the time it was Friday,She did her homework faster than usual,she ate her dinner faster than usual,and she even went to bed earlier than usual.It was Saturday.Mackenzie couldn't wait to go.She was so eager she kept telling her mom to wake up at 6:00 in the morning and telling her the show already started.It was 10:00 now,the show starts a 12:00 noon.Mackenzie was already ready to go.By the time they got there it was 11:30,perfect timing to get their ticket,buy some snacks inside,and sit down.The lights started to dim.Mackenzie was starting to get goosebumps.The show started with clowns,acrobats,and ring masters.It was just like Mackenzie dreamed.The next act was some elephants and a lion tamer.The last act was a tightrope walker.He was so high,he gave Mackenzie and her mom goosebumps.The show was over.       'Now it's time to meet some acrobats!'And we get to take a picture with them!'Mackenzie was so amazed when she met them.When she got home,all she would talk about was the circus.Her mom didn't mind Mackenzie talking about it all day.But she would get annoyed of Mackenzie if she talked about the circus for the rest of the week.Mackenzie yelled,'BEST DAY EVER!!!!!                                                   THE END

Item_Response: 'Sarah, its time to wake up. You are in the big show today!' said my mom. Im in the circus by the way, and i do tricks on the tight rope. Now i need to climb on chairs. I stack them up one by one, untill I get to 6, then I do the handstand. I am done.            My mom and I did good.  To celebreate, we all went out to the pie cart and had ice cream.

Item_Response: On a nice summer day I saw a circus phamphlent saying NEED CIRCUS PERFORMERS. I took the phamphlet and looked at where the circus was. I was pretty good doing flips and somersaults I thought if I joined the circus I could go all over the continent. I registered to practice and see if they'll hire me. Next, it was my turn to perform for the judges. I said to myself quietly 'I can do this'. I did some cart wheels then a somersault, jumped on trapoline then flipped in the air. Then the judges talked for a couple minutes and said that I was hired to do the circus. I had to pack my stuff to go on the world tour              On the way I packed my clothes and things I needed and things that I could remember about my family. I took my suitcase outside and said good bye  to my family I thought to my self if  I really want to do the circus or stay here with my family. I went to the person who was in charge of the circus I was hired to. Then I asked hime if I could my family a few times a year here and they said only once a year or twice a year. I told him that I'd like to do that so I could come visit my mom and dad and my sisters. I was really excited because I LOVED traveling but I love my family too. But I would send the some of my money that I earned from performing in the circus to my family so they'll remember me.              Me and some other people from the circus got to go to Japan, Australia, Wisconson and lots of other places. I stayed as a circus performer to earn some money and have some fun with it I also got to visit my family. It was really fun to do this job because you get to learn about each other and it's like my circus family on my trip. We stay'd together on our tours we were never left behind or been mean to each other. It was a fun time doing this and having more friends but I had to leave my best freiends behind after I left for the circus.             One Monday night I thought to myself I have'nt gotten to see my family and friends in a while I quitted my circus life after 4 years of being in the circus. I missed everyone in my home town and some new neighbors came to move in. I thought I could open a little circus show once in a while with no tours. That means I could live on my dream and stille stay with my family.   I hope some of my circus friends come visit me some times. I sure miss them too.                                                           The END

Item_Response: The Circus Trick                  When I went to the circus with my friends, I was looking forward to it, especially the trapeze. When it came, the performers barely did anything. All they did was jump from one trapeze to the other until they reached the tightrope pole. It was simple as that. I told my friends that I could learn how to that in a couple of hours. As soon as I finished my sentences, I got transformed in to a circus performer! I was in practice, doing the trick I saw the performers doing. I then started doing the trick, but I missed getting onto the first trapeze. I brushed myself off, then tried again. this time I made it to the second trapeze. I realized this would take a while to learn how to do this.               When I got back from the schoolroom (I was about my age when I was in my own body) I learned how much free time I had. About a half hour. At home, I had a few hours of free time. I realized the circus life wasn't so easy.                Eventually, After a couple hours, I learned the trick. It was just in time, because the show was about to go on! I had a bit of time to eat at the pie car, but only a few minutes. The food was hamburgers. Not the best I've had.                At the show, I was after the tigers, and before the clowns. The tigers were a big hit, I got a good bit of applause, and the clowns were a riot. (a good type of riot) After the show, I cleaned up like everybody else. Sure it was quick, but I was wiped out. I got in bed at about twelve thirty (12:30).                The next morning, I packed up to go to Belize. Wherever that is. The show was easy, but I really couldn't understand anything. I was part of a South American tour. I went to Brazil, Argentina, and Chile. I wonder why the circus was such a big thing there.                The circus life is a lot harder than I expected. I thought it would take an hour or two for learning the trick, but this was a lot harder than I expected. Suddenly, I turned into myself again! I wondered how it happened how it all happened, but I was happy that I was back in my old body again. I learned that the circus is harder than it looks.                I learned not to underestimate anybody or anything (especially the circus). I tried to explain what happened to my friends, but decided to not tell that. Nobody really knows what happened right then and there. I guess that I froze time or something. Strange!

Item_Response: Once there was a circus clown and he was not just any circus clown, He was the the GREAT AND MIGHTY circus clown. He was the only clown treated that way and all the other clowns felt like nothing. But one day all of that changed. the GREAT AND MIGHTY had passed, his day's were over. But all the clowns were very happy! But then Mr. Henndersmocks  (the king) came to talk to Orangey (the clown) about what happend...                         The next day was a day of regret. Mr. Henndersmocks didn't know for sure but he thought that he was pretty sure that Orangey and his little clown gang did it. Murdered the GREAT AND MIGHTY!!!! ''No sir.'' said Rue. (the other clown) '' why do you think we did it?'' said pinky.'' I know you did it.'' said Mr. henndersmock. ''BUT WE DIDN'T MURDER THE GREAT AND MIGHTY!!!!!'' said rue. Okay! Okay! you didn't do it then. But who did?!   ''We don't know?'' said Orangey. ''Well, you guys better find out who did or I'll still tink it's you guys.'' Okay?'' Can you do that for me?'' I guess. Okay! we'll do it sir. well let's put Bluey in charge of cleaning up the messes and... NO! said Bluey. I'm always cleaning up for you guys. I want a real job this time Orangey. Okay Bluey! you can be the cubbose. FINE said Bluey. Rolling his eyes. Pinky, your the cleaner this time. Okay? Why can't you ever be the cleaner. YOU never have been that job yet Orangey?! Okay... says Orangey. Pinky your in charge of leading the line and greeny your cleaning with me. Okay? ''OKAY!''                   Okay everbody here? Pinky, Orangey, Greeny and bluey?! GOOD! Everyone's here. AHHHHHHHH!!!!!! Oh No! what happend Pinky? That mean man hit me and he's right there! GET HIM!!!!!! CHARRRRGGGGEEEE. Got him! good job Bluey. What's wrong with you? REDDY?! Where have you been? we've been looking everywhere for you. Your the murderer of the GREAT AND MIGHTY?! Yes. wow. I wasn't expecting that either. Ha ha!!! Let's go home now. YEAH! I'm tired too. Okay let's go home. HA HA HA HA!!! THE END!?                                                                                                                                                Sorry that this is so short!                                            Sinserely: Macie Chicketti.

Item_Response: Circus                                                            By:  Kelly Felice         Here I am.  My first show now that I'm a pro circus entertainer!  According to my paper i have to meet at the pie car for breakfast.  Do I get pie for breakfast? Aperantly no, how sad. Turns out i just get pancakes and bacon.  More healthy than pie of course but I'm sure that everyone would want pie for breakfast.        What I have to go to school?  i thought that going to the circus would get me out of school!  Wow school ends at 3:00 instead of 3:15?  Awesome kinda.   We still do have to learn all the subjects but our school day is a little shorter. I have to do chores too?  Why i thought the circus was a no rules zone no fair!    I have to feed brush and groom the horses enven though I don't even ride them.  So not fair!       Dinner time but why not so much? I don't think any of us can eat that much cause 1.  newbes might be nervous and some might be sick if they eat too much.  Why cant we eat after we preform! Oh ya I'm in the circus but why can't I eat anything it's not like I'm on the trapezz I'm a tight rope walker!         Time for the show! I'm a little nervous but the anounser said its compleatly normal to be nervous before your first show.  The show was a complete success!  But is 10:30 it takes us hours to clean up!  Ok maybe hours is a little exarting but it did take us a long time!           OK fine I'm in bed bu 12:00 am but i am in the circus!  I wonder if anybody ever ran away from the circus instead of to the circus!  Funny thought!  As i close my eyes I think about how my life has now been changed! And I even got to change it by myself with no parents input! Now I might even one day get over my fear of clowns!  After a long day I'm happy to go to sleep!  That is  a first for me normaly im so full of energy but now I'm just tired!   So after a lot of thinking I think that being a circus performer is  nice but also hard work so never just say one day 'Oh I think I might join the circus today!'  Think about it it isn't all just fun and games it's hard work too.

Item_Response: The First Time I Went to the Circous                       I remember the first time i went to the circous. When I got to the circous I was so happy I got out of the car and ran to the other side. I remember that there was a perfesional singer, and every body was dancing,but i was more attracted to the circous performers they were really good at gymnastics and there was a clown with really bushy blue hair, I think it may of been a wig cause I have never seen hair like that befor.Then out of nowhere two clowns came from rops and landed on there feet and started riding bikes.                       After I saw the circous performers I went over to the rides.Me and my dad road this one ride that was 30 feet up in the air and was going back and forth at 120 miler per hour. My dads and my heart started beeting fast, so we decided to take a break for about 30 minutes and head over to the games. There was this one game that you had to trough a horse shoe around a bottle three times and my dad actually won something for me. He asked what I wanted so I said ''That big teedy bear in the leather jacket.''                          After that I got tired so we went home. The circous was about an hour away from my house so I fell asleep in the car using the teedy bear as a pillow and using his coat as a blanket.

Item_Response: Inside the Big Top       Hi I'm Mo! I'm in a circus! I know what your thinking! Mo can't be in the circus, she's only 10! Well guess what. I can! But it's not all fun and games. My life is a lot like yours. But you know, In a clowning around type of way. I go to school just like you were we learn and play. But I do something you probably don't! I perform!                       I have to perform 10 times a week! Once every week day and twice every weekend day. But it's not too bad. I get to do awesome stuff like tightrope and trapeze and my personal favorite, Horse back riding! Horse back riding is when you do stunts while riding on a horse. And that's hard!                      Another thing I get to do is travel. I travel to different places every week! The bad part is I don't really have a place to call home. And I never really get to see my family. Sometimes I wish I was back home when I lived in Kentucky. but then I would never get to see my parents and little sister Hannah. I still just wish my agenda wasn't so crowded.                      So in conclusion, My life is ruff tough but fun all at the same time.

Item_Response: I am 13 years old and my name is Lindy Park. I am a very busy circus performer because being in the circus is lots and lots of work. I do many different things at every show. For example,sometimes I do comedy as a clown,train animals to do tricks,flip as an acrobat,and most of the stuff you usually see in the circus. Today, I'm in the trailer lounge,while a show is going on,eating pie and resting because I broke my leg being an acrobat yesterday. So the story is when yesterday my mom and dad were finished riding the elephants while I was dressing up with my older brother , Mike who was a clown that day, in the dressing trailer. When the clowns were finished with their act then it was my turn to perform. So I started of on a tall balance beam flipping and standing on my hands. Then I climbed up a mountainous ladder to a thin rope with a huge net under the rope about 100 feet below and then started hanging off of it with my legs and doing flips with catching the rope again with my hand. On my 6th trick, I tried to do a trick that I've succeeded before where I hold the rope with my mouth and spin in a circle with my body. It was all fun and games when I then noticed that the rope was bigger than the ones I've used before. I suddenly let loose of the rope because it was too big for my mouth and fell to the net painfully on my leg. The good news was that the audience thought that was the end of my act and clapped without noticing my slight tears. But the bad news was that my leg was broken and I tried hard not to limp on my way back to the trailer which had made my leg hurt even more. So it was very hard but, I've still got a show today just being a clown on a wagon while my brother and dad (who are clowns) fall while pushing my wagon. When the act was finished, my brother helped me do chores when  a week passed everything was perfect until my mom got pregnant and had my baby brother,Joey. He turned out to be the funniest clown while only being 4 years old. So life as a circus performer is hard  but I managed to get through. I wonder what's going to happen next in my circus life.

Item_Response: The Great Circus Mystery             It was a warm sunny day like a normal day Grace was on her way to the her trailer then it happen it was a loud yell anyone could hear it. Grace went to go check it was her  best friend who yelled Mary. Both of them worked as acrobats up in the sky high with Jason there best friend.Grace asked 'What had happen Mary?' Mary said that someone stole her costume made out of fancy gems. Grace remembered that she had one too and even Jason. There costumes were to be used that night. So she search in the trailer but no where to be found but something didn't seem right in there.Then she found it a small but white glove in there.Who could have a small glove?she thought. Then she ran out to see if they stole her costume and they did she couldn't find it no where to be found.By that time it was almost time for the show and still didn't have a clue who could it be.        Jason still had his costume and the others did but why did they didn't have there costume. A note was flying down to Mary's and Grace's feet Grace picked it was a to do list.                                                      To do list           First get gems Second still costumes Third sell gems Forth get rich    Grace said'I'd seen this writing before but where?' Mary thought and thought but couldn't remember. Then came there answer it was Larry the janitor. He was the one who did it now that they knew they needed a plan.        The plan is to try to get the janitor to get the costumes and get him fire. 'You know what to do right.' 'Yes I do!' said Mary. Mary went to distract the janitor and Grace went in to his office.When he was gone Grace went in his office and fond there costumes she tried to get them. But then came in the janitor and with Mary, he smiled but the evil kind h. He didn't seem worry at all he just was clam and told the girls what he is going to do with them and why. He locked them right in his office and went out with the costumes. Mary yelled'You won't get away with these!' but it was to late he was gone. Grace thought and thought then told Mary that she will climb up in the air vent. That she will go get help and Mary can yell to see if any one can hear her. So they did that it was there only plan they had when Grace got up the vent and fond her way out even though it was gross and dirty. She fond Jason and Larry together talking what they were going to do with the costumes. She hid behind a tree once they got out of the way she ran as fast as her legs could carry. She found out that the show already started and that the ring master (manger) was intruding the aerobatics and Jason still wearing his costume. Grace ran out to the stage and told the audience that Jason and Larry stole there costumes that was valuable. Once Larry and Jason heard they ran to nearest exit they could find 'Stop them!' yelled Grace.Then it happened he police came with Mary in front of them. 'Mary!'yelled Grace they hugged each other. The manger fired Larry and Jason and they got sent to jail for a year.Grace and Mar got there costumes back and they got to do there show.

Item_Response: My name is Bart, and I am ten years old. I have been in the circus for about 10 weeks now, and I haven't seen my family for a while. I got into the circus by hard work, and dropping everything I did so I could just focus on the circus. There are some down sides to being in the circus. you have to work about 24 hours a day and you almost never get to see your family, but I'm OK here because I have a friend my age named Dan.              Now I will tell you about my day. It all started at 6:00 am when I went to the pie car to get some breakfast. As usual, me and Dan met up in the hallway. 'Are you ready for the big performance tonight.' asked Dan. 'I sure am.' I replied. Oh yeah, I forgot too tell you about Dan. He is ten like me, and we are both jugglers. We have a juggling act together and, it will be the grand finale in tonight's show.               Me and Dan finally get to the pie car, and eat our pancake breakfast. We talk about what we should add to our performance. ' I think we should stick with the flaming torch juggling act.' said Dan, and I agreed. We had worked on it for a while now and the grand finale was a good time to reveal it.                                                                         ~               A few hours went by and we were at school. Today, me and Dan just wanted school to be over so we could practice the act, but we still had geography left to do. Geography comes alive in the circus because you study the places you travel to. Mrs. Worm, our teacher, does a really good job of it.                After school me and Dan practice. Practice goes fairly smooth except for one mess ups. In the act, me and Dan are tossing pins to each other. Dan accidentally threw it when I wasn't looking and it hit me in the face. ' Sorry Bart, are you OK?' said Dan. I was OK, but I wouldn't have been if the torch was lit!                                                                       ~                                                     It is 7:00, and it is time to start the show! The clowns come out first (Maggie, and James) and get the audience rolling in the isles. Next comes out Phil the tight rope walker, and he rides a unicycle across the tight rope. Next Pablo does an amazing trick where he gets a horse to sit down! After that, Bob the acrobat, did a triple back flip of a diving board into a kiddie pool. Now, its finally our turn. Me and Dan are too nervous too explain. We start to juggle, and we we get into a serious juggling rhythm. Before we know the act is over, we didn't mess up, AND THE CROWD GOES WILD! We did it!

Item_Response: LIFE AT THE CIRCUS                                If you think you can just join the circus the blink of an eye you are wrong.  Joining the circus is hard you have to have the right kind of skills and everything.  You have to learn how to juggle good and to ride a unicycle.  For me joining the circus was just part of my family so basically I had no choice.  Oh yea and I forgot to mention that you if you want to be an acrobat you have to be at least a decent dancer, but you definetly have to be very flexible.                          I guess im pretty good at dancing, but definetly most of the adults there are a lot better.  I keep my head held high because I know I wll get there.  My mom is an acrobat.  She is the best one I have ever seen.  It really isn't fair to me, because I try my hardest all the time, but like I said I keep my head held high.                                 My dad has one of the most fun jobs, well, I think it would be. He is the announcer that may not sound very fun but my dad makes it look like fun.  When he does the announcing he makes all of these funny jokes.  Even though he has told them all to me before I laugh every single time.  The bad thing sometimes about the circus is I never get to see family or friends, but I like what I do so I deal with it.                            When I get older since im already an acrobat I want to be an even better one when I get older.  Maybe one like my mom.  She knows how to do everything when it comes to acrobatic things.  I hope  you understand how fun but hard sometimes the circus can be from my writing.

Item_Response: Being a person in the Circus is something that you have to work up to. You can't just decide you want to go and sign up or audition a short speech. You have to have a purpose, a talent, and you have to be able to have fun and not give up if you do something wrong the first time. When you are in the Circus you have to be ready for an adventure of a lifetime. But first, you have to think if this work fits your personality.   There are three very important keys for being in the Circus. Number one, bravery. In the Circus, there are very scary acts that you have to put on for the audience. So you have to work hard to be brave in those acts. The second key is working hard. In a Circus, you have to work really hard and put 100% work into it. The third key is endurance. You have to have a lot of endurance when working in the Circus. Like when you have to work hard, you won't just give up if you mess up.   Despite the hard things in the Circus, you can have a really good time. You can acomplish things you have never acomplished before. You also get to go around the world to some really fun places. You can perform really fun things and you can expeirience things that you have never before.   So, if you want to join the Circus, you might want to keep this for the times you want to give up and go home.

Item_Response: A Day In the Circus.          Sarah's mom was an acrobat in a circus coming to our town so Sarah invited Megan, Stella, and me to the circus. So at 9:00 A.M. we all met at her house and went to the circus. 'Hey, I am so happy you all could make it,'said Sarah. 'Of course, why would we miss it?' I said. We all headed to watch the show. 'I am going to get some popcorn,' Sarah said. 'Okay, butcome back sorton. The show is going to start,' said Megan. 'Okay. I will come back soon,' Sarah promised. 30 minutes passed. Sarah did not come back yet. We all suspeccted something. So we left the show and went to find Sarah. So I called Sarah. I heard a cell phone ring near us. It was weird but I knew SArah ws near us. I just couldn't find her. 'Hello?' I asked. ' This is Sarah. Sorry I did not come back.. I had to um go to the restroom?' she said in a strange way. ' Well we are glad you are okay. We thought you were kidnapped or something. Anyways, where are you?' I questioned. 'Well, I am near the trash can in front of you,' Sarah said. I looked up. I saw a clown that looked a lot like Sarah. Sarah wsa making balloon animals for little children. She walked toward us. ' Hi everybody. It's me, Sarah, your friend,'she said. We all were surpirsed. ' Look, I didn't want to tell you all because I knew you would laugh at me. Sorry,' Sarah said. 'We don't care. We are your friends so we don't care if you are a clown and look silly. We care only about you. We judge on what the inside has. Not the outside. We are your friends so we won't laugh at you,' Megan replied. We all nodded. Then we all shared secrets about ourselves that nobody knew so our friendship would be stronger.

Item_Response: the circus life              if you want to become a performer, you have to have some sort of special talent. when i first started the circus it was tough for me because i was the youngest and everyone else was very experienced.at first i was shy to practice in front of everyone else,but now that I've been with them almost a year, i feel like they are my family.during a tour we have to get a lot of practice and a lot of sleep.you might think the circus life is easy,but when you experience it its a whole lot harder than you think it was.here is what i have to do everyday.                      6:30 a.m. i wake up greet my circus family and eat some breakfast,fix up the tent,make sure the lights are working and feed the animals.               9:30 a.m  go to my tutor's room and start school with the other circus kids.we don't have computers like regular schools,but we do have lots of books that are informative and really help us.not all of us speak the same language, so its tough to understand what some people are saying,but we still are friends.               at around 2:00 p.m. we start practicing for the nights show. i get to practice with my friends, but we do different acts so we cant practice the same thing.my act is to juggle while riding a unicycle.               at 4:00 p.m. we get to take a break and eat lunch.when i finish eating the clowns let me play with their stuff.once i got the flower and gave to my mom then the flower squirted water in her face.i played with one of my friends called Rosa.Rosa is from Mexico so she only speaks Spanish but i understand her and she understands me.               7:00p.m. we are getting ready to start the show.first my dad introduces all the acts. then music starts playing and we start off with the horses.               9:30 p.m. the show is over and we are getting ready to sleep.               when you live your whole life in a circus, you forget about the stress.i love the circus life.

Item_Response: There was a girl named Sally.Sally was 11 years old when she became part of the circus.She had always wished to be in the circus.Each time she saw a circus on t.v she screamed above her lungs.She always pretended that she was in a circus and that she was the star of the show.She pretended that people clapped at her and yelled her name over and over again.Sally drew pictures of her in the circus.She always wonderd what bieng in the circus would be. Item_Response: There was a chill in the air as I stepped down from the steps of the trailer. I really wanted to go back inside and read, but I knew I couldn't because I had a responsibility. I had to feed and groom each horse to perfection. Good thing there were only two of them. When I got to the stables, they were empty! I looked in the makeshift barn and all around, but I couldn't find them! Then I heard a:   'Nay!'       I turned around to find both horses standing a few yards away.       How should I get them in their stables? I thought.       Then I see the big box of oats and an idea was born.       I know what I'll do. I thought. I'll put a trail of oats leading to the stables! When the horses start eating the oats, they will end up in the stables.       I carefully placed the oats into a trail. As soon as I set two oats up, they were consumed. Little by little I got the horses back into the stables.       When I went home that night, I was quite pleased with myself because I thought of a soultion to a problem.
