Item_Response: Working At The Circus                              If you are just starting out at a circus you might want to clear your schedule. Being a acrobat is a hard and long routine. You will need to learn all the tricks. Other things at a circus is easier. If you fall when doing you acroat tricks it heurts if theres no net or if it riped.?                      If you want to do somthing else you also need to practice that. Juggiling is hard, that takes concertation and skill. You need to have even objects. If you don't have even stuff you will mess up and get embaressed. If you use sharp things you need to be extra careful.                      Other things are a bit easier. Taming animals is easier because the animals are half trained at the zoo and half at the circus. Only certain animals are at the circus. Monkeys, tigers, and dogs are the main animals at the circus. There are so many I named a few.                                         Also another job is mortor cycling. Where you are in a big cage and do tricks and loops. It is the coolest thing you could ever imagine and see. It is the most popular thing to do.but it takes major concentration.

Item_Response: What Happens In The Circus?                Have you ever wondered what happens in the circus Annavelle knows shes in the animal act.Everybody plays and horses around.But if you think its all fun and games your wrong.They have to practice and practice.'Its not just thinking that everythings going to go well in the show' says Abigal whose in the pony act.'You need to know the shows going to go well and be confident it well' said Fernando the juggler.               Ana the boss and dancing salsa master said, that you practice and never everthink the circus is a joke.Junior the tightrope walker said that it is really hard to walk on a rope.You need to be really focused and need to be goood at balancing.'You really need to be careful with the horeses they are tricky' said Angel he's in the horse act.I'm the animal trainer Guadalupe.We have five dogs Paloma,Pepe,Bonbon,Diego, and Gita.               Then theres the youngest performers Hector,who we call Juju is 5.Ariana is 6.Their in the acrobats act.Nows the clown Miguel,who we call Miguelito.He is 7 and extremely funny!The dogs are funny too.Once they did a pyrimid and fell,then they got in a fight because when they fell they all hit each other.Once in a while we all throw a free show for everyone.We also have a motorcycle guy,Arturo.We have a elephant named Tom and a cheetah named Jerry.Outside we have a pony ride and a cheetah run.The two ponys are called Chunky and Munchy.We are all the Circus Family.

Item_Response: My big suprise   by Abby Neal       The day before the big suprise I went to my G-mom and G-dad's house(who are my grandma and grandpa.)they said they had a suprise for me and my little brother Gavin, who was 4 at the time.We were so excited but G-mom said 'we can't do it untill tomarrow, ok'.              We both  said ok.Gavin said 'I wonder what it will be, maybe a new pool or a big huge new playhouse'  'I don't think it's going to be that big' I replied back to him.the rest of the day me and Gavin couldn't stop thinking about the big suprise we just couldn't seem to get it out of out head's.           That night I couldn't go to sleep because I cept wondering what it was.I tried to turn music on and that didn't work,I tried to close my eyes and that didn't work,And I tried to count sheep but that didn't work either so I just stayed awake but all of the sudden I hear a sound in Gavin's room so I go in there the lights are on and he's under the cover's playing on his leap pad.           So I sneak up to him  and pull the covers off real fast and he gaspes.He say's 'sissy' real loud I say 'shhhhhhh try to be more quiet'.He say's 'ok I can't go to sleep so I decided that I would  play on my leap pad'.           So I say 'can I play on It too'? 'sure' Gavin replied.So me and Gavin played on it for hour's and hour's untill I look at Gavin's Angry  bird alarm clock and it was exactly 1:00 AM in the morning.All of the sudden I tell Gavin really fast its 1:00 in the morning.           Gavin say's 'we better get some sleep' I agreed with him let's get some sleep.Gavin put's his leap pad up and jump's in bed.I go back in my room and fall right back to sleep.           In the morning I get up wake Gavin up and we go into the bathroom to brush our teeth we look in the mirror and we both have bags under our eyes so I go through G-moms makeup bag and find some liquid foundation so I put it under our eyes and we looked good as new.           We all got dressed and got in the car G-mom and G-dad drove us to our big suprise.IT WAS A CARNIVAL!!!!!!!!! Me and Gavin were siked we all ran out of the car after we parked and dashed right through the door when we all got in there,there were thousands of  people.               So me and Gavin held G-mom and G-dad's hand we stopped by the cotten candy magine and the popcorn stand and got all kinds of stuff.When we walked through the doors to get our seats it said 'The Amazing Ring Ling Brothers.               When we got our seats the lights went off and the big speakers said 'welcome to the ringling brothers stadium.when the show started we all were so excited.Once they started everybody screamed and shouted they were so excited  and so were we.           they jougled and walked a rope over a shark tank and made clowns pop out of a teeny car and people were also spinning on giant ropes.And a whole lot of other stuff that was really cool like make lions jump over you it was fantastic.           When we got home we were worn out we went right to sleep on the couch it wore us out. and that was our big suprise.       THE END

Item_Response: Life In the Circus                Life in the circus isn't always easy.  Trust me.  Performing in the circus takes a lot of practice, time, skill, and talent.  We practice five days a week until 8:30 p.m.                      The circus, of course, travels all the time so we are never in the same town for more than three days.  When we travel we ride with all of the circus performers and all of the technical and stunt crew.  We have been to 35 states so far and we are not stopping now!                  When we perform we do six different acts. My stunt is walking on the tightrope.  Really fun!!!!  When I turn 16 I will move on to doing the acrobatic stunts.  The other stunts are the clowns, acrobats,jugglers,the circus horses, and then my favorite one the canon shooting.  Yes, these stunts are dangerous but, it's all worth it in the end.                   We are having a contest that anyone can enter and win a free trip and more!  So, enter, try to win, and if you win I'll see you there!!!!  Good luck!!!!!!!!!!

Item_Response: In the circus life you can't just go join the circus. You have to have a specific talent. You need to understand that at 7:00 A.M. you wake up get dressed and go to the pie car. 9:00 A.M. School time. Our one room school house travels with us. 3:00 P.M.Schools over,time for a quick break.3:30 P.M. Chores and practice.6:30 P.M. Dinnertime. 10:30 P.M. The show is over :00 A.M. In bed thinking about the end of our touring season. One of the upsides is that you get to travel all around the world. You get to work in Australia, Japan and all over North America. The circus has given me the opportunity to go to so many different places and meet so many different people. I travel on the road with 100 people who are like a circus family to me. When you're young it's the time to do it. It's the time to travel, the time to grow and experience your life. It's great to see the faces of the audience just jump alive when I make eye contact with them during a performance. Despite what many people think the life of a circus performer isn't all high flying fun its just great to see the fans.

Item_Response: One fine day a girl named Fluffleluffagus was on summer vacation. She was so bored, then on t.v she saw the circus was looking for new performers and she suddenly had an idea that just popped into her head, she could join the.................. CIRCUS!!! But how would she tell her mom, should she run away, no that would scare her mom half to death, maybe she could slip a note into her bedroom, or maybe she should tell her mom face to face, no because she would then get really MAD. So she decided to slip a note into her mom's bedroom. Then she was off to the circus.                 She finally reached the circus in Idaho. She made it into the circus because the boss was a clown, so he'd hire anybody. She did her first performance after two weeks of training but she couldn't hold on so she decided to do a trick where she tied 100 balloons to her waist in just the nick of time before she hit the ground she started floating up , everyone was amazed! Most people were so astounded that they passed out.                 She missed her mom and she asked the clown to see if she could call her and this is what the clown said, 'I can't let you do that,   because my boss will hit me with a bat'. So she just turned away and she decided it was time to go home. She missed her mom and she missed her puppy, Noodles. So she left a not near the front door near the boss's office. Then she was off to her real home.                 It took her three days and three nights before she reached her front door. She rung the doorbell and her mother was in tears and swooped her up in her arms and did not want to let go. As soon as she let her down Noodles came running and licked her face clean. They were so happy after that. And Fluffleluffagus never ran away again.

Item_Response: Anyone who thinks circus life is nonstop play is crazy.   I, Bella Castini, know differently.   I live in a big trailer with my family.   We travel 20,000 miles in seven monthes each year, visiting 150 cities.   I work from sunup to sundown.   Here's a typical day for me: 7:00 A.M I wake up, get dressed, and go to the pie car1 for pancakes and bacon.   The crews are setting up tents, lights, and music for tonight's show.   9:00 A.M. School time. Our one-room schoolhouse travels with us.   Like any school, ours has computers, tests, and report cards.   Because the circus performers are from all over the world, many of my classmates speak other languages: Franch,Russian, and Italian, like my family.   As we travel around the country, our geography lessons come alive.   3:00 P.M. School's over---time for a quick break.   The clowns let me play with their unicycle and juggling balls

Item_Response: A Wonderful Circus                     Hello! My name is Casandra the Great. I am a magican that works here in the circus. Life here is always fun, but it is also tough.Our whole family works in the circus. We each have a different act. My brother is a clown, my sisters are acrobats, and my mom and dad are animal trainers. It's a lot of fun especially when you make someone happy. People think that being in a circus is a lot of fun, and it is, but it also requires hard work. If you want to know more about the circus life, keep reading!                 The first thing I do is wake up in the morning and go to the pie cart to eat breakfast. If none of my family is up I go to wake them up to give me breakfast. Then I get ready to go to school. I know what your thinking, 'how does this girl go to school if she keeps moving', the truth is we have a trailer that looks a lot like a classroom and all the kids go there so we could learn. For our recess, We go to the horses and ride them. We also go and see what the clowns are doing like my brother. After our recess, we go back to the trailer and start learning again until lunch. For lunch, we all go to eat corndogs, hotdogs, and popcorn. This is just in the moring! Of course we get out of the classroom in the afternoon, but this is what we do in the morning! Are you starting to see that being in a circus is hard work! If you don't keep reading.                 When we get out of the classroom, I go into my trailer and just relax. I might also go and play with my brother and sisters. I would also play with my dog Coco. He is a small dog. Then I start getting ready for the show. We all start practicing for the show. Of course I always practice on my brother. I always do tricks on them to see how my tricks end up. I always need to concentrate on my tricks. If I lose my concentration I will mess up real bad! I always need to think on that day's show. Then when we are finish practicing, we go to the piecart and eat. We are not allowed to eat a lot though. This is in the afternoon! Next, is the show.                 The show is finally here! This is always the time when everybody is nervous except me. I am always the opening act. It's always a great honor when you get the opening act. It is also awesome that you get to amaze them first. We always need to worry about who goes on first and second and so on. There is especially some preformers that get sick because they are really nervous. Now you know that it is a hard job.                 Now you know! It isn't a easy job. To be a circus preformer you will need to be confident and determined. You would also have to be used to staying up late. If you have all these traits then join! you would love it!

Item_Response: Life In The Circus                        Life in the circus is really entertaining to the crowd. The circus is fun and entertaining because circus clowns are trying to make people laugh. Acrobats fly around and do backflips and frontflips to the audience. Circus jugglers maybe juggle rings, chainsaws, and other fun and dangerous things. The tightrope walker tries to balance on two feet and tries to balance on one foot. That is how life in a circus is really entertaining.            Circus clowns are funny and make people laugh. They do juggling, funny jokes, other tricks, and fun things. Clowns can make little kids cry when they show up. They can do a lot of daring tricks. They can also do magic to kids and grown ups.            Acrobats make people amazed when they do amazing stunts. They can also do backflips amd frontflips. They can also ride a motorcycle and balance it with the rope. Life in the circus is really hard for people who are in the circus show. The acrobats maybe practine in gymnastics and in gymnasiums. They can also swing each other around the circus. Item_Response: Crazy Circus Life                                     By:Sydney Cox           6:00 AM-Wake-up-Get ready for the day-Breakfast      Today I woke up, it was Saturday in New York,that means two circuses for today.I threw on my Miss Me Jeans,My hot pink Hollister T-Shirt,and put on my American Eagle Super Sparkly black Flats,Then I went to the Pie car and ate four stacks of pancakes.I was starving, we had a big day ahead of us.By the way my name is Sydney.       7:00 AM-Practice For the afternoon show        I am the oldest tight rope and trapeze artist,So, I work with Zack. Zack is the oldest (and rudest) male trapeze artist and he is only twelve!So that leaves all the other girls working with the younger boys. I'm only eleven and all the other girls and boys ten and younger.In practice we learned how to hold each other by the arms and legs while one of us are keeping us both up in the air without slipping its the hardest thing that the younger kids are allowed to do.       11:00 AM-Lunch and prep for show        At lunch I had two burgers each.Fortunately Zack and I had to stop eating to to go to our separate dressing rooms toget into our matching outfits ecept that mine was a dress and his were pants and a shirt.My dress is purple with  strips of blue on my skirt.And Zack's outfit was a purple shirt and blue pants with purple stripes on the outside of the legs.       12:20 PM-Afternoon Show       We Had a blast during the trapeze act it was sooo fun we were swinging from one side to another and forming U shapes with each-other. Our parents said that it was the best act that they had seen in years!       5:30-Snack-Practice For Late Night Show       Since we did such a great job at the afternoon performance our pernets moved us to the advanced trapeze group.So we got to just watch what the advanced group did but I have to be honest, we still did better than the advanced adults.           7:30 PM-Late Night Show        During the late night show the adults seemed to like us better than the kids earlier that day! It was an amazing event.The Adults loved us and we loved them I mean after all we are better than the adult trapeze artists.           10:00 PM-Dinner-Bed time         We had Tacos For dinner that night because of our prefomance and went to bed.Every night i go to bed thinking about our house in California, I miss it a lot sometimes, epically on nights like this.Even though I hate Zack, I had a fun time with him tonight.                                           THE END

Item_Response: In a circus, a traveling circus, I walked around to view the trainers. They were getting ready for tonight's big show. It was hard to focus. I knew I needed to practice, but my mind kept telling me not to. I was tight-rope walking over fire.      'Okay.' I was talking to myself. When did I ever talk to myself? I was nervous. Very nervous. I was aware there is going to be a net between me and the fire, but I don't trust nets. I have fell through one twice already. I was balancing two feet above the ground when Autumn walked in. Autumn was a horse trainer, and a very good one. She could persude a horse to jump through fire!         'Oww!' I fell on the ground. She startled me. 'Oh! Sorry.' Autumn helped me up. 'I need to talk to you about your act.' I was comfortly seated in a chair. 'My act? Why?' I asked. 'I know your'e nervous, everyone is. But the audience doesn't want a net to help you.' Autumn was trying to sound as calm as possible, but it was hard not to. I just stared ahead. Out to the circus tent. I could hear beyond to red and orange stripes, into the big tent with bleachers and trainers.        'Hello?' Autumn wasn't very patient. 'Oh! Sorry. I-I am afraid. Even without the net that never really works, I'm really nervous.' Now I was pacing around the caravan. I didn't know what to do. I know, I needed to be confident, but how could I? I needed balance, and when you're scared that doesn't help. But I agreed to walk on a string, anyways.        'Balance!' Autumn yelled at me from nearly thirty feet below. 'That doesn't help.' I whispered. At least there wasn't any fire yet. There would be at dress rehersal. 'What?!' Autumn couldn't hear me. 'I said,' I finished the rope. 'I said, yelling doesn't help.' Now I was climbing down the ladder. 'Okay. Dress rehersal in an hour.' Autumn walked out of the wide, open tent.          Dress rehersal was fine. I just did not look down. If I did, I would fall into flames.I survived-dress rehersal! Now for the the real show. I stood up by the tight-rope the whole time before my act, posing and pretending to be scared at dangerous stunts. It was time. I closed my eyes. 'Don't look down. Don't look.' I forced myself. Alright. There was a twist.

Item_Response: 'The Time we Went  Camping'                     It's true that here in the circus we work hard,but we never miss an opportunity to have fun. In fact,last spring,we went camping in a forest in North America. It was the best time of our lives. It was also way better than shoveling the poop off the training equipment. Although it was the only camping trip of our lives,it was still the best camping trip of our lives.                      Our day started out like any other ordinary day; wake up,eat,and go to school. After practicing our routines,we dressed for the show. After the show,instead of going to our trailers  and putting on our pajamas,the ringmaster announced that we would be going camping with the rest of the circus. I was excited of course, but my parents looked as if they had won the lottery. They were as happy as clams to take a rest from work. Naturally,there was a catch to skipping work...we had to bring food for everyone! Not even that could take away the excitment of going camping for the first time in our lives. So the next day,after the show, we packed our bags and went to the forest behind the circus tents. Since we had to bring food,my mom brought s'mores,potato salad,fried chicken,and chips & dip. Man,did we eat a lot! Within the first hour of our trip,we had already finished half of the chicken. While eating,we were telling scary stories. When it came the time for me to tell my terrifying tale,my parents didn't want me to get nightmares,so they decided it was time for me to begin going to sleep. The kids had to sleep in the tents with our names written down on them. As soon as I found the tent labled,'Carlita,' I was amazed by its level of comfort. Knowing that I would have to get up early,I fell sound asleep. In the morning,when I woke up,the adults were already packing up the leftover food and tents. We all walked back to the circus and put away our things. It was the best camping trip ever!                      After that camping trip,I never stopped asking if we could go camping again. Even though the ringmaster said,'no' constantly,I just knew that we had to go camping again. There is nothing better than going camping.

Item_Response: Anyone who thinks working at the circus is fun  they are rong.I've worked at a circus before.I just have to do chores,clean,go to school,and most boring of all I have to jump around and make pepole clap at me.Sometimes i get really scared because...well a lot of pepole are looking at me.Another reason I get scared of the circus is because there is tigers,lions,and elephants!                                                     There is one thing I do hate of the circus you have to do the same thing every day!For example I get up in the morning go eat breakfeat,go to school,practice for the show and I have to train the puppys for the show!When I am done with the day I usually go take a shower and go to sleep.                                   I have to admit there is some fun things to do here at the circus.One thing I absolutely love is when I get to see other pepole perform.It feels nice that I dont have to do anything so I can just sit down and watch them jump around.When the day is over I can finally go home.I usually go home and tell my family about the fun day I had at the circus.I really like my family because when they know that I dont like being at the circus they make me some delicious food when I get home.       I do like being at the circcus its just that i feel that it makes me look crazy.It grosses me out when i see the performers put long knives down their throat.What i do in the circus is be an acrobat.I chose to be an acrobat because i get to swing my body in mid air.                                                                          Even though the circus is not one of me most favorite things in the world it does make me happy that i have something to do and it is being an acrobat at the fun circus.

Item_Response: One cloudy day on March,5 I was In my car and I saw a sign that was put up on a wall.  It said 'Enter contest to see your skills for the ringling brothers circus, if you win you get to join the circus, every one is a winner because if you don't win you get free tickets to the ringling brothers circus, front row seats, and sweets.  Right then I new it was a win win and my destiny.                  That month I waited and waited till it was the day on March 31 wich was tomarrow. I was at my house figuring out what to do. It was typeropeing or doing flips on the trampoline, And right that second I thought of what was more fun TRAMOLINE! That night I stayed up thinking about it and thinking and thinking. When I woke up the next morning I got on sweat pants and a sweat shirt and then took off for the long trip to L.A.                  8 Hours full of  worries so when I got out of the car all I did was hope for the best! Later.   Right after every one finished the juges found out who to pick.  'every one, may you walk on to the stage they wrote the name on peice of paper, put it in a envolop then gave it to the annoucer. He took out the peice of paper out of the envolope and annouced the name that was on the peice of paper 'AJ Morelan'   I bust out into laghter and said 'Nice joke now tell me the real winner' And the annoucer said 'AJ Morelan' It was'nt a joke he was telling the truth I ,Aj  Morelan just got inculded to the ringling brothers circus                 The entire trip/ journy was the best ecperience in the world It was so fun It ony felt like a week. The circus crew said I was the best trampoliner They had ever seen so the aworded me 3,000 dollars along with free tickets for front row seates and sweets.

Item_Response: Once upon a time there was a little girl who had a dream of being in a circus when she got older. the little girls name was Sally May . Sally liked everything about the cicus and she is going to tell you a little bit about almost everything they do in the circus. the first thing she wants to tell you about is the circus clowns . The next thing she wants to tell you about is the circus arcobats that is one of the most dangerous ones. If you ever go to a circus and you see  this she advices you not to do this at home it is some times when you are hanging in mid air and maybe about to fall you are holding something in your mouth dangling below when some one else has that same thing in there mouth dangling above you. The next thing she wants to talk to you about is a circus juggler. A circus juggler can almost juggle everything or anthing from bounct balls to fire torches to sharp blade knives . But not all people can do that so she would advice not  to do that either. Here comes Sally's favorite part the tightrope walker. You defintely have to have alot of practice on a balancing beam. Item_Response: Life in a Circus       There are many responsibilities for someone in a circus. They have to do so many things to get ready. There are many types of performers in the circus.but not just anyone can go and join. You must practice many things like being a acrobat you have to train almost all day. there are also trapeze artists to perform. life in a circus is sort of hard.       Being in a cicus takes hard work you have to train all day. If you are a acrobat then you have to train gymnastics. If you are a clown you have to practice being funny and fitting in things like a clown does. A clown might also want a makup artist to perform. If you are a elephant or horse trainer then you have to make sure your animal does nothing wrong while performing.       As you can see there are many responsibilities into being a circus performer. It isn't very easy because you have to work long days. So you cant just join the circus you have to have talent and practice. You also have  to be patient so you can be good at something you like. There are a variaty things to do to be in a circus.

Item_Response: your teacher has a announced that a well know travelling circus will be stopping in your town to perform several showes she hands out this flyer for each student to take home you want to enter the contest but realized that you know nothing about the circus ! you decide to do some reseach to gather information that will help you write your story while doing your research you have found two articles and some photographs.After you have looked at these sources you will answer some questions about them Briefly scan the sources and three questions that follow.Then go back and read the sources carefully so you will have the information you will need to answer the questions and write a story.Anyone who thinks circus life is nonstop play is crazy.I bella Castini know differently.I lived in a big trailer with my family.We travel 20,000 miles in seven monthes each year visiting 150 cities.I work from sunup to sundown.Heres a typical day for me 7:00 A.M. I wake up get dressed and go to pie car for pancakes and bacon the crew are setting up tents  lights and music for tonights show. 9:00 A.M.    School time .Our one-room schooolhouse travels with us.Like any school ours has computers tests and report cards because the circus perform are from all over the world many of my classmates speak other languages French Russian and Italian like my family as we travel around the country our geography lessons come alive 3:00 P.M chores and practice.I feed water and groom the horses we use in our hourseback acts.Today my dad practice somersaulting off a running horse.I`m working with on leaping from a trampoline onto the horses back it takes balance and concentration.Other  kids are practicing juggling and acrobatics Training are working with elephents lions chimpanzees 6:00 P.M. Dinnertime. my family and i go to the pie car to eat but we dont eat much because we`re performing tonight.We do 10 shows a week :one each weekday plus a matinee on Wednesday two on Saturday and two on sunday 10:00 P.M the show is over

Item_Response: That Day at the Circus       It was a normal day here at the circus when suddenly I heard a screeching scream.   I step out of my trailer and I saw Bo Bo the clown running in circles screaming ''The horses are gone''. I looked over to the stables where the horses were suppose to be and there was still a fresh stack of hay. We feed the horses every night so who ever feed them last must of forgot to close the corral gate.           As I walk over to see the chores list I hear another scream but this time it was Jay Jay the clown. I walked over to see what was going on and there was one of the 5 horse laying on the ground. I took its pluse and it was still breathing so we called the circuses vet. She said the horse is ok it justs has a broken leg and is banned from preforming for 2 months.            We were about to keep on folowing the horseshoe tracks when we heared a thumping noise. It was the other four horse but they were running to the train tracks and the train was coming. We all got in to the nearest car which was a small clown car. Luckly I was wit the two smalls clowns so it was easy getting in. We flew over to the train tracks right when the train came 3 of the horses did not run but Lucky the daredevil horse did.             The shows about to start and we still haven't found lucky so, we decide we will call it a night and look for him tomorrow. We only had 2 horses that were usable so we did are best but the audience wasn't pleased. We ended the circus early and I went to put the horses away and there was lucky standing  in the corral.            I couldn't belive my eyes. The one place we did not look there he was. After I put the horses back a ran into the pie cart and told everyone luckys back.After that the whole group decided to put on the show tomorrowfor all the people that came tonight fio free.All the audience loved it and the horses too.

Item_Response: One day when no one was looking. I snuck out of my house, and ran away forever. Sooner or later I joined the circus figuring I had nothing better to do. So what the circus looks dumb, because I found out that the circus is not dumb the moment I first performed. My name is Max Robinson, and this is the story of my life. Being in the circus was fun and all, but it was really tough too. Every day I had to wake up at 6:00 in the morning for breakfast. Then it was straight to school. My school was only 1 room, and wasn't very big, but I got used to it. It all happened when a new kid joined the circus, and at that time I was the best. His name was John hart. He was new so he wasn't the best, but in 2-3 weeks he was the best he was better than me. It all happened so fast that I didn't believe it. Everyone was cheering for him after he did his 360 somersault off the rope onto the horse. After that performance everyone was cheering for him and not for me. I couldn't take it, and then it happened. I got too jealous, and set up a revenge plot for his next performance. He broke a leg that day. Everyone found out it was me, and asked me why did I do it. Well that was a question I couldn't answer either. So I stand corrected, this isn't the story of my life. It was the story of how I ruined my life, and how I ruined John Harts life too.

Item_Response: One day there was a girl named Paige she always wanted to be an acrobat in the circus. Paige was always watching her Dad in the circus and wanted to try it for herself. But her Dad thought it was too dangerous and if something went wrong Paige would get really hurt. But Paige did not want to give up just because of that. So that night when Paige was in bed she thought 'what if my Dad got a day of from juggiling and the circus and watched the show'. Paige could ask the top director of the acrobats if she could tryout to be on the team. After that hard thinking Paige decided to go to sleep.           In the early morning Paige went to the acrobats trailer and knocked on the door. 'Come on in the door is unlocked',it was the main coach Barbra Loantin. So Paige walked in and Barbra asked 'Hi sweetie do you need something', Paige said 'I wanted to know if I could tryout for the acrobat team'. Barbra's face was shocked but she said 'That's fine with me if it is fine with your Dad'. Then Paige gave a guilty smile and said 'It's ok, ish'. So Barbra said 'meet me in the morning hunny be ready to give it a try'.'Ok bye Barbra. So that night she knew what she was going to wear her Mom's old acrobat suit with an American flag across it and big stripes hanging down from it. So Paige went to sleep early to get a freash new start in the morning.           That morning Paige woke up really early and went down to the traning center and Barbra was waiting there for her. So first Barbra got Paige into a harness to first see what she can do. Paige was spinning and flipping everywhere. From that moment on Babra knew where Paige got those flips and turns,from her Mom. Item_Response: In a circus the is lots of fun things to do but there is also a lot of chores. You can't just join the circus, you need talent to the join it. Lots of people he met but he loved hs family to he will retire soon to but he will keep  working well there was a knew act he never preformed taming there lions in stead of one tiger. well he neededto concetrate so this time he did not look around sometmes but looked carfully well he did it. then night came and he did well aso his parents came to see and cheered the loudest. Item_Response: My name is Bryan Stewart,I ran away from home to be in the circus,because my home was boring and I wanted some action in my life.Later when I got to the circus I asked the owner,Mr.Bellini if I could join and he asked if my parents would agree and I lied and said yes.Then he asked if I had any special talents and I said yes. I told him that I was very good at gymnastics, he brought me into a huge tent with tons of different people practicing gymnastics,flips and all kinds of cool different stuff.He asked me to show him what I could do and I showed him everything I had.When I was done he said that I was amazing and that if I really wanted to I could join the circus.Then he told me it will not be all fun and games,it will be very hard.I told him that I was very happy you let me join,I will not let him down.                  He brought me to a car on the train as the train started to move,he told me this is were I will live from now on.After he let me unpack, he brought me to another car were there was a kitchen,he told me this is were    I will eat from now on.Then he showed me the rest of the train like the bathrooms,and the make up rooms.   I told him I liked everything,and that I'm going to be very happy here.He told me we were on are way to Pennsylvania,he told me that we will be riding for a couple of days.Then he told me that we will stop each day and set up some of the Trapeze stuff and take out the animals,those are the times you can practice.He left and I went back to my room and fell asleep.                  When I woke up it was morning and I decided to get some breakfast, I went to the kitchen and got bacon,scrambled eggs,and waffles.When we came to a clear field and we decided to set up and practice.Then everything went quickly by the next few days were a blur.When we finally got to Pennsylvania,we got set up, we built the tents and got all the equipment ready.That night everyone was very nervous.Then all the people came in to the tent to watch us perform.The owner got the microphone and asked me to come out.

Item_Response: Something that happens in the circus.      Circus days are very different than a normal day at home. A tipical day for a  girl that's in the circus starts out at 7:00 A.M. She gets up, gets dressed and goes to a pie car to have breakfast. At 9:00 A.M. it's time for her to go to school. 3:00 P.M. When's schools out there's a quick break before you have to go practice for the show tonight.   6:30 P.M. Dinnertime, they normaly don't eat a lot because of the show that night. 10:30 P.M. The show is over and your super tired.   12:00 A.M. Laying in bed thinking how the show went.          When your in the circus you travel to many different places. It's a fun experience in your life, but also a diffucult one to. Your always away from your family until the season is over. Plus your working with people all over the world. Like from France, Russa, Itally, and much more.          Just geting the chance to join the circus is hard. You have to practice, practice, and practice some more just to become a acrobat or trapeze. You need to have the right body type and be very determined. Like I said it takes years of practice just to get the move right. If you join the circus you to be certain that's what you want to do.          The last other thing about the circus is the jobs. If you join the circus you could be a Circus clown, Circus acrobats, Circus juggler, Circus tightrope walker, or train Circus horses.

Item_Response: Do like thrills and hard work? Performing in front of hundreds of people? If you do. then the circus life is for you. If you have a really good talent, like juggling or acrobatics, you can join the circus and show the crowd what you're made of. Of course, fame doesn't come without hard work, so you must practice and concentrate on your act.       Once you have your act done to perfection, it is now your time to shine! You will probably have several shows each week and you can impress the whole audience with your skills. Now, after a perfomance you will probably be dead tired, but you cannot sleep in the next morning. You must prepare and prctice your next act.       Now, if you are a kid travelling with your parents, life is just as hard and fun. You must wake up at 7 AM and go to school. After school you can play with the clowns or do whatever you wish. Then it is chore time. You must make sure the animals and equipment are in top shape, so you have to inspect and feed the equipment and horses. Finally you have to perform in a show they might have that night. The day starts all over again the next morning.       In conclusion, if you like thrills, hard work, and performing, the circus is for you. You can perform, play with the clowns, and help out the perfomers. I think the circus would be great, however it requires a demanding amount of work and practice.

Item_Response: Sarah on The Tight Rope   By: Gaelle Desert       As Sarah Miller stood on the tight rope she tried to concentrate on what her father had taught her, 'Remember concentrate and think of nothing else but the tight rope '. Her thought trailed off as she got to the end of the rope. As soon as she flipped in the air landed on her feet juggling the audience jumped to their feet clapping of amazement. ' I did it!' Sarah ran out to meet the rest of the circus crew.               She felt the warmth of her mother and father as she hugged them both with joy. When the audience left, Sarah and her little brother headed out to their small trailer and got ready for bed. At 12:00 p.m Sarah was wiped out and exhausted from all the excitement. Sarah knew that she had better go to sleep. Tomorrow they were going to Dallas, Texas for another performance.               The next morning, Sarah did her regular chores, grooming the horses, feeding the elephants, e.t.c. When she was done, she helped her father and brother load the animals for the next trip. After gathering the animals they boarded the trailor and drove to Texas. When they arrived at 6:00 a.m Everyone began getting ready for the upcoming performance.               When it was time, the audience gave a round of appluase and they started the show. In came the elephants balancing on a ball while holding each others trunks. Then, it was time for Sarah to perform.   As she began climbing the ladder, she thought and remembered the same routine she practiced, just like it was in the begginning.

Item_Response: Being part of the circus           Your Day       Everyday, you wake up and get ready for your school day. You will learn normal subjects and be taught like normal kids. You then prepare for your show that night. You might practice tightrope, maybe flipping, jumping, flying, etc. Being part of the circus takes dignity, agility, balance, coordination, concentration, and integrity. Preparing for the circus may take a lot of time. As you get ready for the show you may feel scared. You must overcome that fear and get ready.           Your part of the show that night may be different then some others. Your act may involve teamwork. Just do your best. Soon the show is over and you go back to your trailer. It has been a long day, but you have another big one tomorrow!       Your Traveling       You usually travel to many cities to preform, and that may take several months to go everywhere. Your geography lessons might just be where your heading. Many circus groups travel to different countries, sometimes even different continents! If you get homesick easily, the circus probably isn't for you!       The pros and cons   There are good things and bad things about being in a circus. The good thing, is you get to do many performances and visit all over the world. But you don't see your family very often. You are usually away for weeks, months, even years at a time.       Conclusion   Many people do the circus. They do all kinds of performances, travel the world, and do what they love. But being a performer can take years and a lot of practice. But if you can do it, you can be a great circus performer!

Item_Response: The day of the big night finally came. We were in Washington D.C, ready to preform for the president.            Seals were honking, clowns were busy pushing custard pie down their trousers, horses were training, and acrobats were flying.           'Alana, your turn,' the kid in front of me called.            I bravely started to climb up the ladder, my palms already starting to sweat.            Bradley, the kid who was in my performance, swung off, his feet curled tightly around the swing. Ha came closer, so I jumped off and stretched out my hands.                                                      *   *   *           The practice went flawlessly and as a reward, everyone was treated to a restaurant. The food was delicious, and I was confident we would do great.           Then it was finally time.           'LADIES AND GENTLEMEN! TO START OFF OUR PERFORMANCE, WE PRESENT TO YOU, THE HORSES AND THE ACROBATS!' announced the ring master.           There were neighs, and suddenly, a bright flash of light. I confidently strode to the middle of the ring, which beheld a the two ladders and the swings. Bradley mirrored my move.           When I finally got to the ladder, I gave myself a quick 'Don't screw up' lecture. Then I started to climb, and the act began.           Bradley swung off, and I reached down. He flipped me over, where I got a hold of my own swing. Then I swung myself on the bar two times, and at the flip of the last one, Bradley jumped off and I grabbed a hold of him. Next, Bradley flipped off and I followed him.          But something went wrong, horribly wrong. Either Bradley didn't flip fast enough to catch me, or I followed too soon, but I started falling, to the ground below. We were pros, and we didn't have a net. I wanted to scream, but I didn't want to humiliate the circus or anyone! So I just shut my mouth up, and pretended it it was part of the act.          'Pancake Alana in three... two...' I silently thought to myself.          Suddenly, out of nowhere, I heard a shrill whinny. There was a thump, and I landed on a horse.          Desert Storm! He had caught me and was now trotting at the edge of the ring. Every one was clapping, wolf whistling, cheering, and whooping.          Then, Desert Storm stopped in front of a man in a black suit. THE PRESIDENT!          'Oh jeez. Please let the president like it!' I prayed.          The president smiled and stood up.          'I LOVE IT!' he declared, in a deep booming voice. The cheers sharpened acutely in volume, and the noise made the ground shake.          I sighed. All right with the world. And hopefully, no one busts their ear drums.

Item_Response: The Circus           At the circus  I wake up at 7:30 each morning I get dress and feed the circus pet before I go-to the pie car to eat. Then I practice  my acrobat for 2 hours. I'm 20 so i don't go to school, but I do like to play with the kids at school so I wait for then in till 3:30 when I'm waiting I go to lunch in the pie  car after I  finish eating  I watch TV.               When the kids out of school I feed the circus animals again a grown sometimes I talk to them about tonight's show.Then, I go out to play the kids like basket ball, jump rope, and others group games. Then me and [sometimes] the kids check the lights for the show. Help take out the animals. After that I get in my acrobat shoes and clothes. Then, it's time for the show!After 10:30 we allgo to the pie car and I [sometimes] cook dinner. But mst of all it's a big family. At 11:00pm I take a shower and get dress then go to sleep.

Item_Response: Hi my name is Mary and i am an acrobat in a circus. My parents are also in the circus. My dad is a clown so he is always telling me jokes and my mom is an acrobat like me. I love being in the circus but it is also a lot of hard work. My favorite part is that we get to go to so many places.I have one pet dog named buddy but i also get to work with many other animals such as horses,elephants, and tigers.                                                                                                     If you want to join the circus remember that it is a lot of hard work. Today i am going to tell you about a circus that went terribly. It all started when the elephants were dancing. A little boy in the audience had some peanuts and he threw some onto the stage. All of the elephants saw and ran toward the peanut. After that the boy kept throwing more peanuts and one of the clowns riding a unicycle ran over one and slipped. it was a disaster but everyone thought it was part of the act so we kept on going. Finally after the boy ran out of peanuts all the chaos stopped and the show went on.           later that evening when it was time for my mom and I and all the other acrobats to go on i was very nervous. It was one of my first shows because i was a lot younger. i was so nervous i almost puked but i still did the show. but when i was in the air i puked. i was so embarrassed. luckily there was no one under me and it just landed on the stage. while we were doing our act a clown came out and cleaned up the puke.             that night i was scared that i wouldn't be able to be in the circus anymore but i still got to be in the circus. all of the adults said that they were scared their first show and they didn't blame me. and that is the end of my disaster circus story.

Item_Response: Living the life of a circus performer is hard. Everything is busy, and there are a lot of customers watching. since I have a first-hand account, let me tell you.           First of all, there are the customers. They never seem pleased enough. We always have to do something new to exite them. Never the old 'Clown on a unicycle throwing pies' routine. Always asking for something else.          Next, there are the acrobats. They're friendly, but everytime they talk to me, I have to bring out my phone to get Google Translate. I know they have all their time filled up with practicing, but they could at least learn English! Especially when they're swinging around on the trapeeze and we tell them to stop because it's closing time, they just look at us strangely.          Now this last paragraph is about food. I can't really explain the pie car. Somedays the food is good and it reminds me of old homecooked meals, but that just maked me homesick. Other days... Blech! It tastes like a pile of burnt McDonalds hamburger grease! Those days, well, those days I just eat an energy bar.           That was my first hand account of circus life. I hoped you like it, and notice how fun, and not fun circus life can be. I have to go clean the horses for our next act. Bye!

Item_Response: A Circus Life        A circus life can be hard, easy, fun, and boring every once and a while even for the preformers! Also did you know that a circus life isn't all easy, and fun and games. Well sometimes it is but not always. What you have to do to get in a circus is you have to have certain things like what your skills are, what you body type is, you should never give up, and you have to be very determined to reach your goals. I will list some up's and some down's about being in a circus!            Circus life isn't always fun. Because you have to learn the new life styles of a circus actor. For example, When you start off your day it is pretty normal and you still have to go to school. But the school is a one-room school house. When school is done you get a while to play but you still have to get ready for the show that you have to do tonight. As a circus preformer you have to do 10 shows a week and that can be really tiring even if you are really good at preforming in a circus.            When your in a circus you have to travel a long ways from place to place so you are always on the road going to a new place. Also you have to give everything up to be a circus preformer because you never stay in one place for about more than 1 week. Finally, you have to work long hard days practicing over and over again what you learned or what you are learning for the show.                 Also a circus life can be fun?. For example, if you are a circus preformer you can show your skills to the audiance and also before the manitee/show you can play with the things that you use during the show! Also you meet new people that are from all around the world! so you can learn new languages, and cultures.            Also you can travel all around the world to some places in Aisa, Like Japan and China. Some places in Eupope like the U.K. Also you can travel to a lot of places in North America that you havent been to. Another fun thing is you can learn new skills, tricks but you have to be very determined.  Also you can become really good friends with the new people that you meet that preform with you.           Now you know you have to work long, hard days practicing your skills, you can travel all around the world to some places you have probably never been to.

Item_Response: Dear reader's who are reading this,                  My name is Callie and my parents are in a circus, we are a circus family. We travel to a bunch of different places around the world. Most people think that circus people think that it is a fun job, and you only have to dress up into costumes and dance around. Well it's not! It is a job to entertain people and make people laugh and say 'ooh' it is suppose to look dangerous. I would really like to join gymnastics but we move all the time, my parents think that I basically am in gymnastics.             Tonight we are going to perform in front of a live crowd in Religh, North Carolina. My mom is going to tight rope and do circus acrobats. My dad is going to do stuff with a tiger and an elephant, and also juggle rings. I asked my parents and  since they know that I wants to be in gymnastics I am going to perform gymnastics tricks!And 3, 2, 1 the circus began. All of a sudden my mom goes, then my dad goes 30 minutes later, and last but not least I go on flipping in to the stage.                                                                                                                                                                       Tonight was very tiring night. Now let me call my grandparents, oh ya I remember I forgot there are no phones to use. That's what happens when you are a circus family you usually can't call any family members.  Another downside is that you can't really go to your home and visit your family, what I learned you always stay on the rode. I am going to go to my bedroom and finally go and do something I want to do, so I am going to read.            Morning! Now I have to go to the eating cart and get some eggs and bacon. I eat while my parents start packing up to go to another circus show. I am done eating I go into the car I have to quickly get dressed for the next show my mom has to sit in the back and get some of my makeup on. Since I only got to sleep for 3 hours last night, I sleep on the car ride down to Miami, Florida. We are here my mom and dad quickly rush out of the car and start training the animals and setting up.           Finally, we are done now we get to go see our family. Travel to Neenah, Wisconsin. I haven't seen my family for a year now, I am so excited to see them! Well that is what happens when you are in a circus family there are ups and downs. I hope you learned a lot in my several paragraphs of how a circus family works.                                                         Sincerely. Callie

Item_Response: When I started the circus I was really excited. I had to get used to all the steps I had to do in the morning. It was challenging to remember all the steps. After a few weeks I got the hang of all the steps there were like 7+ things I had to remember. When i forgot to do something I didn't get yelled at. That was good.               Next, I want to tell you that there were down sides to be in the circus. First, I didn't see my family for a long time I couldn't even communicate with them when I was on the road. It made me fell really bad that I couldn't talk to my family. I thought that they didn't like me when I came to visit them.              Then, when your in the circus there are also up sides. The up sides are that you can travel around the world and get paid to travel and do acts. You can do your favorite thing out in the circus. you can mess up it wont really matter but people will notice.             Now, comes my favorite part. I worked with the Magical Karlotta she only does magic but awesome magic. She flies up to the top of the tent, and spawns a rabbit with her eyes. I work with lots of people but my favorite is our own fine tightrope walker Kampiter. If you see him you think he will ask for a rope and do his thing. When we were practicing at the tent he tooke dental floose and did his thing walking across that. I think thats pretty amazing. Well I hope you will try to join the circus.

Item_Response: The circus is a dangerous place because there's wild animals such as lions, tigers, elephants, and other wild animals. Also there's tight ropers, acrobats, tiger and lion trainers, and people who ride elephants. I won't forget my birthday on September 19, 2009 when I had my first show.        It was 7:00 in the morning and I heard somebody saying wake up wake up. I instantly sprung out of bed and I screamed, 'It's my birthday, September 19.' I got dressed and went down to the pie car and had pancakes and bacon. I was taking with oldest tight roper in the circus and his name was Lyle Stuben. He was the oldest but was only 35 years old.           School was done and raced to begin to practice. I was going to feed the tigers with the tiger trainer. it was there hours till the show . the show was about to begin and my stomach started hurting. The curtains opened and I screamed.       It truly was the greatest day of my life. I feed the tigers and I did really good. At the end of the show I took a bow.

Item_Response: I am going to be telling you about the circus. I am going to tell you about the resources, how many hours it takes in one circus day, and how early you would get up. I am also telling you my opinion on the circus.         The resources you would use are stuff like animas such elephants, horses, and sometimes other mean animals like jaguars. In the story they said a lady would walk jaguars. You also need to practice a lot with the animals. In the story they would practice doing somersaults off a horse and leap off a trampoline onto a horse.         A typical day for someone that works for the circus such as a kid. The kid would get up at 7:00a.m. get ready then go to school at 9:00a.m.. At 3:00p.m. school would be over then at 3:30p.m.. you would practice. At 6:30p.m. you would have dinner then preform. At 10:30p.m. the show would be over then at 12:00a.m. you would be in bed going to sleep.         You would wake up at 7:00 and go to bed around 12:00, which in my opinion I wouldn't like. I dont think I would like the circus because I don't like getting up early. I also think I would be bad at preforming in a circus because I would be scared to ride on animals and do all of the jumping and twisting in the air. Thats my opinion on the circus.

Item_Response: At 7:00 i get dressed and go to the pie car for pancakes and bacon. Then we get ready for tonight's show tonight. Then the crew sets up the music, tents, and the lights and music.       I go to school at 9:00 A.M. Like any school we have computers, tests, and report cards. Many of mt classmates speak a lot of different languages, like French, Italian, and Russian. So its hard to communicate with other people when I don't know how to speak that language. At 3:00 school ends. Then i get to play with their unicycles and juggling ball.      At 3:30 P.M. I do chores and practice. I water, groom, and feed the horses I use in our horseback acts. I'm working on leaping from a trampoline onto the horses backs. And i also play with my tiny dog named Noodle; our trailer is way too small for a huge pet. Our neighbor walks baby leopards on a leash, and our trainers are working on elephants, lions, and chimpanzees. Me I do the specialty for the circus. I'm the one who does the walking on the rope one, and I do stunts with the animals.       For the after show we have a grand slam. We bring lions, elephants, and all kinds of animals that we train. Also we have a fire stunt seen only one in a lifetime! Plus we will even have animals doing stunts in a pool and other things. Ill be doing my finally called the swifter. I get up on stage and grab a partner from a crowd and amaze them with my magic. I will pull a a deck of cards out of my hands and levitate it to whoever I picked. Finally the last part of the show is the flaming hoop. Only I can do this I will run and try to jump the a hoop flaming with fire. When I did it the crowd was going crazy and I was then the best mannish ever.

Item_Response: A Circus Life   written by Simon Papp       When your in the circus you think it's all fun in games but acctully it's hard work. First off all not every body can be in the circus because you needthe right kind of body and skills for about half the jobs thier. But if you do get in then thiers a good and a bad side about being in the circus. Keep reading to find out what I'm talking about.       The good news about the circus is that you can be alot of stuff in the circus. You don't need to have a great body to be in the circus. If you want to be a animal trainer orclown or something else you can join the circus  if you just have the skills. But the best part is you get to travel around the world all the time. You can go to places like Moscow, New York, Canada you name it. The circus is really great and exciting but there is a downside.        But the circus and traveling around the world means your far away from home. Plus you don't get to see your family very often which stinks. And your always wondering about the show and nothing else. But worst of all it's preparing for the show and that must take like forever. So the circus isin't all fun and games like you think it is right. But mostly it is pretty cool to me and mostly fun and games like you thought it was.       So, that's a sum up of what the circus is like and that's that. But heres the quistin, do you want to run of to the circus or stay home. Item_Response: Emily in the Circus                 Crowds of people cheering, clapping, and yelling barged into Emily's head. She tried to ignore all of that so that she can achieve her concentration. Still, she had to get herself to concentrate. She knew that it was very complicated, but she tried her best anyways. She also knew that her family is supporting her even though they weren't there. Emily thought about the time when her family were encouraging and comforting her about her being afraid. One at a time, she rode her unicycle onto a shaky wire. Trying her best, she avoided looking down the ground where the dirty sand was. The dirty sand sort of looked like they were waiting for her to fall down. She tried to do it as cautious as she can, trying not to make a mistake. Slowly and carefully, she rode her unicycle on top of the wire. 'Almost there,' Emily whispered to herself. Finally, she made it to the end of the wire. When she made it, the people clapped their hands happily.                         After all of those concentration, she drank cool refreshing water to calm her fast - breathing down. Her circus mates congratulated her for doing such a complicated work in the circus. She thanked them all, but she still missed her family. Next, her circus teammates and she went to another country ( which is in U.S.A.) Her family were also there so it was very easy for them to enter the circus of where she was performing. When they were in the different circus, she saw her family waving to her and shouting her name. It was Emily's turn to juggle tiny golf balls while riding on a giant ball this time.' There is no possibility that I'm going to be harmed here because the giant ball isn't that high,' she thought to herself. So again, she did her part and finished her goal of balancing. After that, she said goodbye to her family again hugged each other.                         Finally, when they returned to their normal circus, Emily had to do acrobats. She was trained how to be flexible and how to balance more. When she was in front of the stage, many people were cheering her name and clapped their hands. So, she hanged her hands on 2 rings that were tied to a rope( while the rope was hanged on the ceiling).She spun around for about 12 seconds and stopped. While she was up there, she did the splits in the air and also made complicated tricks onto the ropes. Again, the people cheered and clapped their hands. Now that Emily was having fun in the circus, she realized that when she does fun things in the circus, she stops worrying about her family. ' Being in a circus is very fun after all...' she whispered at her mind.

Item_Response: Joining The Circus           Hi, name is May and I work in the circus. To you it may just seem like a bunch of dumb clowns running aroud but it's much more. I joined the circus when I was 12 after running away from home. I don't really remember why ran away but it must have been a pretty good reason because I don't get mad that often. The circus is buisy, very buisy. My job in the circus in being an acrobatic. Here is my story of how I got to the cirus.              I was wandering alone looking for some place to call home after running away. The sun was going down and all I could see what seemed to be a never ending road that looked like it would go on for ever, and ever,and ever. I had been going for three days and already wishing that I wou have packed more water and food. All of the sudden I hear a bunch of noise and turn around to see head lights of a car! I sick my thumb out and they stop when they do I see red writting on the side of the truck. It said circus.              'Hey you, what do you need'said the man driving. What to say, I probably shouldn't have said this but I was hungrey and needed shelter.          'I ran away from home and I'm lost.'          'Same here kid,wana join the circus? Little pay but you'll get free food and shelter.'He held out his hand and I shook it. I hoped inthe back and we drove to our destenation.               We started setting up and then went to sleep. The next day they taught me everything I now know about the circus, and here I am with the best job in the world, working in the circus.

'Kayla if you ask that one more time I will turn this car around.' Her mother said sternly looking at her through the drivers window. 'I'm sorry ma I'm just so excited!' Kayla exclaimed excitedly a grin across her face. Her mother laughs slightly. 'I understand that Kayla.' she says pulling into the parking lot of the stadium. Kayla quickly got out the car and ran to her mothers side opening the door for her then pulling her out of the black vehicle. Kayla practically skips to the opening at the side then walks in quickly. She was chosen to see what happened back stage at a circus! She looked around and saw people ran around franticlly in a hurd ready to start the circus. Everyone was feeled with nerves and excitement. Tonight would be there first circus in the town for the first time! All the circus preformers were running into each other until they heard someone yell. 'Watch Out!' then a loud boom then a high pitched cry coming from across the room everyone ran to the cry. 'Are you okay?' A tall man in a top hat asked kneeling down next to her just as soon as Kayla got there. The girl whimpered quietly. Kayla looked at ther girls swollen, bruised leg she winced in pain. 'I was just walking and then one of the unicycles fell on my leg.' She cries out. 'Well you can't do the show now Natalie.' A young women with oversized glasses said to the girl sitting on the floor. 'I can do it.' The young girl hissed trying to stand up and then almost falling and almost hit the ground then the women with the oversized glasses held her up. 'You can not Natalie! You can't face anymore injuries!' The girl who Kayla now figured out was Natalie sat with her hands to her face sobbing quite loudly. 'What act did she preform?' Kayla said building up the courage to even speak. 'She worked on the trapeze.' The man with the top hat said finally acknowledging her existence. 'Oh...' Kayla responded quietly. And then the women looked at Kayla. 'Do you want to be our trapeze artist for the night?' she asked. Kayla looked at the lady stunned then at her mother who's face was equally as stunned.Then Kayla's eyes widened in excitement once again. 'I would love to!' She exclaimed.       Kayla knew all about trapeze artist it was her favorite part of the show. She's always imagined twirling through the air being free and able to fly. It was absoulutly lovely to watch.Trapeze artists would start off swinging on a bar and then would twist through the air and there partner would catch them and they'd continue to do that.       About Thity minutes later Kayla stood on a stool with a handle above her ready to be grabbed and Kayla's hands clasped at her side were ready to grab it. She jumped up and grasped the bars tightly and swinged her legs back and forth and then let go twisting and twirling through the air. She was afraid of heights and didn't want to look but she wanted to keep on looking at the ground as she twirled elevation above it and then she did a front turn as the other trapeze artist grabbed her hands and continued swinging. Kayla smiled widely.       She would always remember this moment.

Item_Response: anyone who thinks circus life is nonstop is crazy.I,Bella Cassini,know differently.I live in a big trailer with my family we travel 20,000 miles in seven months each year, visiting 150 cities.I work from sunup to sundown.                                                             here's a typical day for me: 7:00 A.M. I wake up ,get dressed, and go to the pie car for pancakes and bacon.the crews are setting up tents, lights, and music for tonight s show.9:00 A.M. school time.            our one-room schoolhouse travels with us. like any school, ours has computers,test, and report cards.   Because the circus performers are from all over the    world, many of  my classmates speak other languages: French, Russian, and Italian, like my family. As we travel around the country,our geography lessons come alive.                 3:00 P.M. School's over--time for a quick.the clowns let me play with their unicycles and  juggling balls. I also play with my tiny dog, noodle; our trailer   is too small for a large pet. I'd like to join a soccer team, but we're never in one place long enough.

Item_Response: Hello I am Erog Sitruc the acrobat. In order to get into the circus you must have skill, flexability, and the ability to never give up. My job is to do acrobatics like flips and tightrope walking and stuff like that. When doing acrobatics you have to be precise and accurate when flipping, turning, and balancing. If you make one mistake you will have to face danger, say you slip up on a flip, you might end up across the room laying on the floor because you put your hand in the wrong spot or you flipped sideways rather than straight. Being in the circus is very, very dangerous and you have to take risks. I remember one time when i was beginning acrobatics aroung the age or 7, I slipped up on a flip and landed on my head, I was lucky I was still okay. Thats what i meant by never giving up, I almost got killed doin what I loved but i just got back up and kept trying harder and harder everyday. It takes practice every bit of free time you have, you should be practicing.

Item_Response: I, Sally Hermit, know how to work in the circus and be a circus actor i have been doing that for 4 years it is a struggle at first. Here is a typical day for me:       7:00 A.M. I got to wake up, get dressed, and go to the concession stand and order some pancakes, bacon, and sausage. The crews are setting up the stands and tents so we will be ready for tonight's show. 9:00 A.M. Time for us students to go get lessons for tonight's show. We have animals we have to train we have unicycles to ride for us too train with and sometime it is a big struggle. 3:00 P.M. Training is over. I got to go do my chores, feed, and water all of the animals. 6:30 P.M. Dinnertime. My family and i go to the supper concession stand and order some supper we go back to the cart and eat then get ready for the show right now the crew is getting the camera ready to set us on T.V..  10:00 P.M. I am wore out from all of the tricks that was a struggle, now my family is heading back to the cart to get our pajamas on and get ready for bed now we are in bed hope to speak to you guys at the next show. see you then.

Item_Response: A lot of people think that working at a circus is all fun and games.               Circus performers practice,perform,and move every single day.Every morning they wake up and go to the pie cart for breakfest.Then they start unloading the tents for the night's performance.The performers work on their act,they work long and hard until its time for the show.Before the people come,the performers go to the pie cart and have a small dinner and then its time for the show!Each performer does their act until the show is over.The performers get the rest of their dinner at the pie cart and then go to bed. Item_Response: You may have heard of the circus or big top and you may think that it must be horible to work in acircus but really it's not so bad as long as you have the right body type, your family is in the same circus as you, you have the ability to sleep short hours, and determination. In the following paragraphs I will tell you about circus life.        Heres some of the many upsides: you travel the world for free, you get to do fun stuff (doing the trapeeze, walking on the type rope, and much more), and you get paid for doing it! Now there is some downsides: you HAVE to travel the world, usualy you dont have a lot of freinds outside the circus if any, you work all day, and eat what you get or don't eat at all. But dont let that stuff get you down.        This paragraph is a usual scedule for our circus. 6:00 am: get up, get dressed, eat, get ready to go to shcool, and go to shcool. 1:00 pm: shcool is over and I go train animals. 1:30 pm: first show of the day starts. 2:30 pm: first show ends and I practice trick arrow shots. 3:00 pm: go to pie car and eat lunch. 3:45 pm: time for a break. 4:00 pm: trapeeze practice. 4:30 pm: clean animals and animal pens. 5:00 pm: second show starts. 6:00 pm: second show ends, eat, and practice anything I already haven't. 10:00 pm: get ready for bed, go to bed.

Item_Response: Mallorie and Rose                      One day, far away pass Boston lives a tiny circus and its crew.The circus was ready to take off when a girl wanted to join them.'Can I join you?I think I have what it takes.' said the little girl.          The crew and there leader looked at each other.Then they huddled in a circle and talked.'What will we do with the child?What act can she do?'asked a trapeze women.          'I think I know what to do with her,she can tame the lions!She'll be great!'said the leader,and the group broke up.They all gathered around the girl and sat her down on a stool.'Child, you can join the circus, but only if your brave enough to tame the lions!'           The girl thought about it.Why not? I'm brave! I can do it! She considered the offer and nodded.She was going to join a circus!           'Well then, let's get you started by letting you meet the lions.' said the leader.                        The lions were so cute!I don't think I saw anything cuter. I just joined the circus a few minutes ago, and so far it's not as bad as I thought it was.Right now the crew is showing me the lions so I can know who they are.           'Here we have Lisa, she's very shy and she'll grow attached to her trainer quickly.This one here is Roger.He can be very stubborn so watch your back.The last one is Rose. we call her that because she is very sweet and lovable.I think Rose will go perfect with you child.'           'My name is Mallorie by the way.' I should have told them my name when I first got here.It sounds so weird calling me child.It sounds like  I'm there kid or something.           'Mallorie come here and see which lion will chose you.Here's what you do:First put your hand out to each lion,then the lion will sniff it, and if the lion didn't want you it backs away.Now if the lion does chose you it presses it's face against your side.Now chose your lion.'            I walked up to Lisa and put my hand out as I was told.The lion came up and sniffed my hand thoughtfully.It tipped its head to one side then backed away.           Roger was a different story.The crew had to hold him down for me.I was cautious as I put my hand out, but nothing fatal happened. Roger sniffed my hand quietly then growled.Wow, he really needs some training he's a beast!           Rose was nice and quiet.She rose to her paws and sniffed my hand.She walked up closer and pressed her face to my side as the leader said one of them would.I stroked her fur and backed away.The leader was right!She was perfect for me!

Item_Response: The Circus Mystery               One day at the Amazing Kalamazoo Circus that my father owns,  I was walking around the clown cabin, when I saw a glass eye, at least that's what I thought it was. I thought they were playing a prank on me like they always do, so I went inside their cabin and said 'guys this isn't funny it's gotten really old', and when they saw me they said we didn't pull a prank today. I stared at them like they were maniacs and said 'then why is there an eyeball on the ground outside?' They didn't know, so when I went back outside and picked up the eyeball, right as something caught my eye I looked up and they were gone.            As I walked to the pie car I  was thinking so hard that I guess I wasn't looking at where I was going and I ran into Mack, the groomer, and I saw him holding his eye and asked him what had happened to it, but he just ran off. That was very unusual for Mack to do, he was usually very talkative and spunky. That's when it hit me mabye Mack somehow lost his eye. Instead of goig to the pie car I ran to our own cabin, grabbed my journal, and locked myself in the room.  I noted everything that had happened today about finding the eye, seeing mack holding his eye, and the clowns, usually very honest, saying it wasn't a prank.                        When It was time for the show, my dad was frantically looking in his pockets, and saying where did I put it?
