Item_Response: I wake up in the morning still tired from yesterdays performance It is 7:00 A.M. I get out of bed slowly. Then I go over to my dresser inside our camper and take out some clothes for the day. After I get done getting dressed I meet up with rest of the performers at the pie car for breakfeast. As we eat breakfeast we watch the crews set up the tents, lights and, music for tonights performance.                At 9:00 A.M. we take our breakfeast and dump it into the trash and head to the one room schoolhouse that travels along with us on the road. Like any school we have computers, tests and, report cards. Many of my classmates speak different languages such as French, Russian or, Italian like my family. When we travel through the country its like our geography lessons come alive. Today we have a writting assignment we have to write a 5 page story on the american revolution. As the bell for school rings I finish my story turn it in and head down to the break area.                3:00P.M. We are at the break area. The clowns let me play with their unicycles and juggling balls. I can almost ride the unicycle without falling off but it is too hard. Allthough the unicycle is too hard i can juggle pretty well. I thank the clowns for them lending me their things and go play with my dog Noodle. He is so small Our trailer is too small for a big dog.                3:30 is chores and practice. I go do my first chore wich is to feed, groom and, water the horses. We use these horses in our horseback acts. I finish up my chores and head down to the practice field. As my father practices somersalting off a running horse I practice jumping from a trampoline on to a horses back. To do this stunt takes balance and a lot of concentration. I see other kids practicing juggling and acrobatics. Our neighbor walks baby leapords on a leash. Trainers are also working with elephants, lions, and chimpanzees.                6:30 is Dinnertime. My family and I go to the pie car to eat, wile we are there we dont eat much because we have our big performance. We do 10 shows each week: one show for each weekday plus a matinee on Wednesday, two on saturday, and two on Sunday.           At 8:00 we are getting ready for the show that starts at 8:30.           8:30 it is time for the show my father and I are the opening act. My dad takes the lead on his horse. I follow ten paces behind running. He sommersalts off the horse and the horse keeps running. I sprint for the trampoline and jumpoff of it doing a flip in midair landing on the horse. I let one hand off the saddle and wave to the crowd as they cheer for us.           10:30 The show is over and i am so tired. As my family walks back to our trailer we passd the circus office, conssession stands, stables, and trailers. Two days from now we will be set up in another town.

Item_Response: The Missouri State Fair   We have a big show at the Missouri State    Fair. There are lots of other people here. I'm not the only kid here, either.   There are lots of kids walking to a ride or going into a building. But I'll bet you hardly any of the kids here are in a show. But I am. I'm in the circus.       Now before you ask, no, I did not run away from home and join the circus. It has been in my family for a long time.        I do an act in the show. What I do is several things. I work with the horses. I can make then jump through a hoop. I can also make them jump over obstacles, too.       I also do a bit of acrobatics. I have been working on doing a flip in the air while on the bars.        I love it when the advanced acrobatics do this trick. What they do is first, they need a partner.  Then, they both go out and link arms. One person falls onto the floor then jumps on a trampoline onto a horse. It is AMAZING!!!!!!        There are lots of other acts in the show. There are ones with lions and tigers and bears. Also there are ones with monkeys. My sister actually walks Suzie (her favorite monkey) on a leash to the trainer during the show. (Since she is small, we only have her do little thinks.)       The show is starting!!! Shhhhhh!!!!!        'Ladies and Gentlemen, children of all ages, welcome to the Krazey Circus!!!' Then the lights go out and the first act starts.        It's an act I'm in. Suddenly, a hoop is set on fire!!!!! Then the lights come on and you can see a chestnut brown horse jump through the flaming hoop. You can see a golden hoop and a white and black-speckled horse jump through that hoop with a rider with a pink suit on. Then we do the course. We both jump over lots of obstacles. Then our act is over, and another one starts.       In this one, bears with bow ties dance. Then it is over.       In this one, monkeys and lions look like they are having a conversation.       So the show goes on.       That day through all of the acts I'm not really sure how the rest of our day went. But before I knew it, we were on our way to a county fair, ready to start another day of circus fun.

Item_Response: Niki sighed.     'Why does this have to happen to me?' asked Niki     'What is the matter with you? Why do you always complain about your job?asked the ringmaster.     'Oh, sir, I didn't see you here!Ur?What did you say again?I am so sorry that I did not hear you.'replied Niki.     'Niki, I do know that this is hard work, but you have got to understand that your parents are counting on you. I think you should take a break and think about what I just said to you.'     Niki nodded and went to her tent. She sat down on her bed and began thinking about her parents.     'Gosh, I think the ringmaster is right, Ishould know how hard it is for my parents to see me go I should work hard and think for my parents'said Niki to herself.     The next day, Niki was grooming her horse, she needed water so she went to her tent to grab her water bottle,when she came back the ring master was standing there admiring her horse.     'Sir, are you alright?I do not hope my horse has a problem!     'Oh Niki, I didn't know that this was your horse, I think you have groomed it well!'answered the ringmaster.     'Why, thank you! I thought about the words you said to me yesterday, I think you are absolutely right. I agree to what you said to me.'     'Very well, I am sure that your parents are going to be very proud of you!'said the ringmaster.     Niki blushed at the compliment. The ringmaster walked away and Niki went back to grooming her horse. The day went by quickly. The next day was Wednesdy the show is coming.     'Oh, I know that I have done this many times, but I have a friend that lives here, and she is going to see me working in a circus and laugh at me!' said Niki freaking out.     'It is all right Niki. This means that you are a string girl! A circus is hard work and you are a sucess!'said the ringmaster.     'I owe you too much. You have helped me come this far. THANK YOU!'said Niki.     'Now go on out and show every one how speacial you are!' said the ringmaster.     Niki stepped out onto the ring and performed beautifully. Everyone clapped at her amazing performance.     Niki smiled and bowed to everyone.    'This is the happiest day of my life!'

Item_Response: My Circus Life       Hello my friends. I am the famous Mustache Walker. If you   didn't know, I am a tight rope walker and the manager of the Circular Circus. You must be thinking that life in a circus is very hard because of all the practice and acts that are done. Well that kind of is true, but working in the circus is also very fun. Here are a reason few reasons why.   First, we get to meet a lot of new people. There is a diversity of   people: French, Russian, and Italian. They can be beneficial. Suppose there is a French kid, and he is learning about Venice, Italy. He may not understand something about Venice. He can learn about the place from an Italian kid. The school geography lessons come alive because we go almost everywhere.   Next, we get to do a lot of stunts. Some of them are using   unicycles, juggling balls, somersaulting off a running horse, leaping from a trampoline onto the horse's back, acrobatics, walking baby leopards on a leash, and trainers working with elephants, lions, and chimpanzees. I am a tight rope walker; it takes a lot of balance and concentration. This is not a stunt, but I am also the manager of Circular Circus. This helps because I get to schedule the performances according to the performers convenience.   Now you should be thinking, that life in the circus is not boring   at all, but instead very exciting.

Item_Response: Life At The Circus                                                                        By:Christian Martinez              A lot can happen at the circus, for an example there's lots of things you don't normally see every day. You can see different cities like: Ontario, Boston, and Philadelphia. You can also see new states like New York, Massachusetts, Canada, California, Main, Florida,  Idaho, and Maryland.        You can also see cool people doing cool things like: Acrobats, Jugglers, Tightrope Walking, Ringmasters, and Clowns. You can meet new kinds of people who like: the circus, art, juggling, anyone with the same interest as you.        Also you can see what your learning in school in person like: if you learn about the Statue Of Liberty, you pass new your in your circus trailer and you can actually see it, like it said in the story, 'It makes geography come alive.'        There is a lot of animals you can see to like: Lions, horses, elephants, chimpanzee's, giraffes, some really talented dogs and cats, and sometimes (a) bear(s). A lot of animals are part of the circus.       A circus life is a busy life and you need to do a lot in order to make through some dangerous acts. If your an Acrobat, if you miss the target you have to grab you fall either onto a net or on the hard ground. If your a Tightrope Walker and you lose your balance then you also fall to a net or the hard ground. If your a Lion tamer and your trying to tame a lion but happen to get to close, you c an be eaten alive. If your a stilts walker and a stilt breaks you can break your leg. Also if your a juggler and you miss and hit your head.        Life at the circus is fun, hard, dangerous, and filled with learning.

Item_Response: Circus life                                                                                            by Carlo Jauregui                   In a circus not just anyone can join the circus. New York time spoke with Carlos Cortez.Carlos said that he lives in a trailer with his papa.        Every morning he wakes up feeds the animals after that he goes to the pie cart to eat pancakes and bacon. Then he start's warming up with circus people.       Carlo's gets a thrill when he performs in a live audience.Its great to see the audience jump alive when you make eye contact.       The downside is that you don't get to see your family.We work long hours and spend a lot of time away from home.Carlos said that ''on tour that you really have anywhere to call home.       The upside is that you travel around the world.Carlos has worked in China Australia,and all over North America. Carlos says that its giving me many  opportunity to meet many different people.       At 12:oo A.M. In bed. im thinking about going home.It will be nice to go back to my home in spain.           Late at midnight I think about the tour finishing.It would be nice to go back home in Barcelona Spain.So i can see my mama and my family.

Item_Response: If i was in a circus this would be my routine,get up,eat breakfast,and get ready.First  i would have to practice the stunts im going to do.The stunt im going to do is acrobatics.I would like to do acrobatics because it seems fun to do.Finally it is Monday morning,7:00 o'clock. Next is mine and Annete's stunt.Annete and i were already up in the air waiting for our music to come on,then our music came on Annete was hanging on to the swinnging bar waiting for me to come so i swung down grabbed Annetes hands and we swithched sides so that Annete was on the left side and i was on the right.                                                                                                                                     Finally the show was over my whole family did their stunts then it was over.I think it was a very fun day.I hope oneday  we will come to a city near you.!!!!!!!

Item_Response: Hi my name is Rose,the trainer for the circus horses. Being a part of the circus might be tough but it is so much fun. When I was a little girl, my mother and I used to always pretend we  were in the circus . But, my father never approved of the circus . He said the circus was childish and silly, you see he was a lawyer and didn't like childish things. One day I told him that I wanted to be in the circus, he got so mad he lighted the fire place went upstairs and got all my circus things and there them in the fire place and said ''Rose you will never go to  the circus. That same day  my parents got divoreced.                                                                                                                                                                                                                                   But enough about me let's talk about the circus. The circus owner is my best friend's dad and my best friend Grace is the other trainer.The circus life is nonstop work  but , the funnest part is when we perform . I sometimes feel that they only come for the horses.Other than the horses my favorite part is the clowns.They make me laugh so much even thinking about them makes me laugh. Being part of the circus makes life a little more fun.                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                       Finally I must tell you about behind the circus curtains.People are all sweating even they have done this a bunch of times. Sometimes the coustumes are so bright they almost blind me.The trainer coustumes are very simple skirts with a with a simple shirt that macthes my skirt. That is my life in the circus.

Item_Response: What happens at the circus               At the circus you can see clowns and horse riders,and acrobats,jugglers, and tightrope people. Some people think clowns are scary but they aren't they are very nice. Tightrope people face a lot of danger. Like falling of the rope and land on the cold hard ground. Riders face of falling off .May also be trampled to death.   The jugglers don't have any thing to fear. If you juggle something heavy you could really hurt you self or get a black eye.   These  people do a lot where they get hurt very easily. Hallow they make it look very easy. But it is not.   I would like to try it some time.  I could walk a leopard.Ride a elephant. Be a lion tamer. Also be a acrobat.   All that stuff may be fun but very dangerous.Also it would be fun to be up in the air.It would be fun to ride a elephant. I just don't under stand how the people cannot be hurt. They do all this stuff and not get hurt it weird.   Nothing is impossible they say so I take there word for it. It would be nice to see a clown once in a while.  See people shot out of a canon. Also little clown cars. Also see how they are so cute.       Seeing tightrope walkers walk it would be scary and good at the same time. You would never want that person to fall and die. taming a lion. That would be scary and hair raising.Standing on a horse and jumping off would be spectacular to see.       You may even see water shoot out of the flowers  on the clowns shirt and get wet. That would be funny. Seeing them fight.Calling each other names. Also a lion tamer who would make every body nervous. That is what happens at the circus.

Item_Response: Hi my name is Sarah im in the circus.It might sound a little odd but i just like performing.Tonight is my big perfomince and im so excited,and a little nervous.Im an acrobat my cousen James is going to be in the act with me he's my acrobating partner.Today i had to wake up early to help set up for my big show.While we were setting up i kept thinking in my head'what if i mess up and someone laughs at me'.I told James and he said 'if you mess up just keep on going with the act'.I felt a little better but i was still worried.Then it was time for James and i to practice.I thought i did good during practice and so did James.It was time for lunch and i ate some salad and some fruit because i always eat healthey before a show.After that i put on my costume for rehersal.When rehersal was done it was 4:00pm so i had to mke the entrence sign so people know where to enter.When i was done i had to get ready for the show,and i was still really nervous but i was ready.It was time for the show James went out to speak ,and then it was time for me to come out.when i went out i felt really good and then me and james did this dance on the ropes together and it felt like i was flying it was fun.Then it was time for the big finaley so James picked me up and through me up in the air and i did a spin and then James caught me and i landed safley on the rope. After the show my dad told me we made $200,000 and that i did a great job and so did James.It was 10:00 and i was tired so i went to my trailer and got in my night clothes and turned out the lights and went to bed.               THE END

Item_Response: Flying Free: Trapeez Girl               When I was little, I always wanted to go to the circus. I, Andrea Smith, will tell you how I made my dream turn into reality.                   I lived with my older brother, mom, and dad at the time. I liked my older brother, but everyone always told me how I should follow in his footsteps. I wanted to live my own life, not be my brother's shadow. My brother was skilled at many things, but I knew no matter how hard I tried, I would never be like him.                    So, on one fine day in August, when I was ten years old, I decided I would run away. My parents actually allowed me to do it, and I believe it was because they thought I would come back. I do visit them sometimes now. I remember packing a large suitcase with food, water, clothes, and all other neccessities. I also remember trying to to stuff my oversized tent into my bulging suitcase. I had forgotten to think of one small detail: If I ever did run away, where would I go?                     I had no relatives in America. So, I stayed at my best friend's house for a week. I didn't tell her that I had run away. I just told her I had come over for an extra-long sleepover. Then, I left and roamed the streets, looking for a job. I saw a poster advertising a circus. It said: Come one, come all! Come to our circus-extraordinaire! Cloony Clown's Club auditioning for talented clowns! I remembered my long-forgotten dream of joining the circus. I quickly noted down the address and, dragging my heavy suitcase behind me, ran through the thick crowd, shoving people this way and that.                     I reached the circus tent and rushed inside. The words I had failed to notice on the flyer earlier were etched on a large poster on the wall in front of me, plain as day: For talented performers, ages 11 and up!                       I couldn't believe it! I had come this close to achieving my goal and now it had slipped from my fingers! But that's when I remembered something: My birthday was on June 12, and today was June 11! I ran outside and sat down next to the large red and white polka-dotted tent. At exactly 11:59 PM, I rushed back inside and said 'I'm auditioning for Cloony Clown's Club. I've heard that you need a trapeze artist.' as fast as I could. 'Well lucky you, there's only one more spot left.',the lady at the counter replied. As she said this, I watched the clock above her head. It read 11: 59 59 sec. 'How many years old are you?',the lady asked. And then putting on a big, broad smile, all the while watching the clock, I replied,'Eleven, ma'am, I'm eleven!' 'Well then, welcome aboard!' I couldn't have been happier to hear better words!                         And that is the story of how I became the best trapeze artist in Cloony Clown's Club!

Item_Response: I woke up at 7:00 AM. Today was the biggest day of my life, to day there was going to be a circus show. I would show everyone what a great animal trainer I was. It took cooperation for me and my animal. Suddenly, there was a crash. I looked outside, they were setting up the tents.         My name is George Gates and I am an animal trainer at this circus. I have been training since I was 8. Like I said earlier, today was a big day for me. At 7:01 I go down to the pie tent(where I eat breakfeast), then I go back to my tent to change into my circus clothes. At 8:00 the big circus tent is set up and I do a rehearsal. Then at 9:00 we all relax after our rehearsal. I am100% sure I won't make mistake. Then the clock ticks 9:00, We got down to the circus tent and then a bus full of people arrive.        Although my heart is in my throat, I walk straight up to them to greet and welcome them. I can tell by their faces they are eager to watch the circus show. Soon more and more people arrive and soon there are more than an 100 people. We take them toward the circus tent.        My heart is still in my throat. They seat themselves and I perform to them. Showing my circus love I perform without making a mistake.       Then it is soon evening I ahve performed all lot. My circus love has been here since I was 8.

Item_Response: My circus group and I were going into the huge tent to perform. It was Monday and we were in Africa doing a normal performance. I was having fun waiting for Joe's and my part came. The clown went out and did his magic tricks. The acrobats did their long performance. Then it was our turn to perform.       We were doing the fire act where we had to juggle juggle three thick  sticks with fire on their edges. Then we anccidently dropped one stick and there was a enormous fire. 'Run!' I screamed. Everyone evacuated. I tried to call the firefighters with my cellphone but they didn't understand me because they spoke a different language.       I decided to go to nearest city and get water. My crew helped me do that. We got water and got rid of the fire. Our tent was ruined but we were safe and that was the important thing.

Item_Response: My Day at the Circus   I got up from bed at 7:00 A.M. and ate my breakfast in the pie car. There, the crew   was setting up for today's show.   At 9:00 A.M., I went to school. It was just like a normal school with computers,   tests, and report cards. Since the circus performers are from all over the world, my classmates speak many different languages.   After school is over, I take a 30-minute break. I play with the clowns' unicycles   and juggling balls.   Next, I do my chores and practice for the circus. I take care of our horses', the ones   we use in our horseback acts. My dad practiced jumping off a running horse and somersaulting on the ground. I practice jumping through a hula-hoop just a little bit bigger than me. Other kids like me are practicing the tightrope. Trainers are working with many different kinds of animals.   I eat dinner at 6:00 P.M. in the pie car, but don't eat to much since we have a show   coming up.   In the show, we start off with a live band riding on unicycles dressed as clowns.   Next, trainers walk leopards on a leash, while the leopaords juggle three five-pound balls. After that, kids cartwheel up a ladder and dive into a pool of water. Then, a tiger leaps up to the top of a ladder and does monkey bars. Finally, my part and my dad's part comes. My dad starts the horse while I started charging towards the hula-hoop. I jump through the hoop and jump onto the running horse. Meanwhile, my dad jumps off the horse and does two backwards canon-balls in mid-air and a backwards and forwards flip on the ground. After all this, I drive the horse through an obstacle course where dad holds the obstacles.   After the show, everyone claps and applauses for us. We are exhausted and go to   bed late at night. The whole circus crew was ready to travel to another place after a good night's sleep.

Item_Response: Neverlasting Circus                                        Once there was a        boy that loved to do trapeze.  His name was Lloyd.  He lived in San Bernidino.  He's been dreaming of being in a circus one day.  Lloyd watches his favorite circus on tv everyday.  Then an announcment came on after the show.  They said they needed a new   trapeze artist so , they were having a contest and whoever was the best could be            Lloyd thought about it and he decided he needed to talk to his parents first.  They discussed and they agreed for him to enter.  His parents were very supportive and confident in him. So was Lloyd.  He told him self he needed to train really hard to become part of that circus.  He promised himself he would.                                                 Lloyd trained extra hard for the contest.  His parents but him a trapeze set for him to pmudractice on.  He fell a few times but there was a safety net on the bottom.  Then he decided to use the net in his act.  He got the idea from a movie he saw by the name of Madagascar 3.  he ate healthy so he could be fit and he also  exercised doing push-ups, curl-ups, and pull-ups to make sure he had the perfect body for trapeze.            The next day he showed up to the auditions for the circus.  But he was the only one there.  Therefore he got the job.  after his first few shows he started to feel like a stick in the mud.  He wondered what his parents were doing while he was gone.  He wanted to stay in the circus but, really wanted to see his parents.  So, the other members of the circus came to an agreement of how Lloyd can stay in the circus and still see his parents.  They said he can stay with his parents but, when the circus is in San Bernidino he can do his act.                                                                                                      The circus took Lloyd home. When he arrived his parents were on the couch crying.  Lloyd asked what was wrong.  They said they missed him.  Lloyd told them that he's only going to the circus in this city and that any other cities the circus is in he's not going there.

Item_Response: A DAY IN THE CIRCUS                  One day Pablo decided to write a story of how his life is. He choose to express himself through an essay.                For Pablo a typical day is a very interesting day because it all falls perfectly in order. First Pablo has to wake up get dressed and take a shower all before 7:00 A.M. Next he goes to eat at a car called, ' Pie car.  In the pie car a perfect breakfast of pancakes with bacon. After he`s done he goes to school at 9:00AM and finises at 3:30PM. Next he does his chores and practices his circus act. At 6:30 PM it`s diner time,and his meal is at the pie car. He can` eat much because he`s about to preform.                 It preforming time for Pablo and he has the butterflies! First the ring master goes out on stage and welcomes everyone on stage. He announces all the acts to the stage. then the time comes when he says,'Pablo.'  Pablo was so nervous his palms were sweating. Pablo was an acrobat and his partner was a girl. He was afraid because at practice he dropped her doing a  triple  back flip double back twist spine breaker. From that day on Pablo was terrified of dropping her. Pablo went in to the stage and climbed a ladder to get the swing and prayed to the heavens to give him power to carry his partner. After he did that he felt stronger and he carried Susan. The crowd went wild.               After the circus Pablo was so tired and was happy he did n`t drop Susan. Pablo's whole family told him he did a great job.

Item_Response: My Treasure           I wake up and get dressed, ready to work a long day in the   circus. Although some days I feel that I never should of joined the circus, I like being around my friends and fellow animals. The first thing I do when I get up is to get dressed and go to the pie car for breakfast,get the tents ready for tonights show, then start practicing for my acrobatics.             My partner and I practiced long and hard for our first show. We had watched other performers before and had thought, 'how do they do this'. Since then I have never gave up my dream to become an acrobate. The show started and I was full of excitement but with nervisment too. I had swung from the bar handle and was off. My partner had caught me and crowd had roared with excitment. I had done it once more and it finally happenend. The day I had been waiting for had come. I was the star of the show.         After that I watched the other performers like the animal trainer, clowns, jugglers,tightrope walker, and much more! The the trainer made the lion jump through a cicle of fire, the jugglers switched balls and even juggles up to 8 balls. I realized that my treasure eas the circus the whole time.

Item_Response: A Trainer's Life                 'Now Changhao, be a good monkey,' I told my chimpanzee. 'Let's try that front snap kick again.' Changhao nodded obediently and performed it, this time executing it perfectly. 'Great!' I said and gave him a ripe banana. Just then I felt something nudging gently into my leg. I turned around to face a fully grown king cobra!             'C'mon Triss,' I frowned. 'You know you can't get attention by interrupting. I'll be with you in a minute. Triss made a face, but slithered away quietly. I worked with Changhao on his lunges and then turned to Triss. After the day was over, I lay in bed thinking. My name is Keith, Keith Reyes. I am an animal trainer at the Classic Carnival, a very successful circus that has thier last show of the American tour coming up in a week. It's a big deal, and the circus promoter will be there. My animals and I are a big part of it and that puts a lot of pressure on me. Best not to worry about it, I thought and fell asleep.             I woke up early, at 5:00, and made my way to the pie car. The cook there, Zachary, was an early morning person, and knew I was too. 'Hey there,' he said. 'I got some pancakes for both of us to eat. And I also got some tidbits for your animals.' By the way, Zach loves my animals, and they love him back. I chuckled and we made our way to my cart to eat. After that, I set about teaching my newest animal, a bald eagle, some tricks. In all, I have only three animals, but they are the best three animals one could have. Soon my eagle, which I named Leatho, could do a rolling dive, a barrel flip, and had been trained only to bite people who hurt him first. I looked at my watch. It was already lunch! Zachary and I headed to the pie car and Zachary immediately whipped up an all-you-can-eat buffet.             This time, when I lay in bed, I was content with my training.             It was the day before the circus! Everybody was rushing, but not me. I had trained my animals well, and we had already rehearsed our performance several times in front of the stage crew. But late in the night, while I was giving my animals their dinner. I saw a darkened shape out of the corner of my eye. I did not sleep well that night.              I woke up even earlier to do some last minute practice. But when Zachary and I came in, we found the pet yard empty! Just then I noticed some footprints. I followed them into a large tent, while Zach alerted the others. I had never seen that tent before. I quietly slipped into the folding of the tent and saw two men talking. Animal smugglers! With my animals in cages. Rage welled up inside me but I forced myself to stay calm. Those men had guns. I slipped out and found the rest of the circus actors.              I told them where my animals were and what I was going to do. It was showtime!              I slipped int the folds of the tent again and chirped like a cricket. Leatho knew that signal and began banging on the cage. The men came over to quiet it while Triss stretched and stretched, and made herself thinner and thinner and got out! Triss, however, went to the bottom of Changhao's cage. Changhao started hooting like a madman and the men grouched over. Changhao immediatley layed them flat with a cross chop while Leatho picked his lock. Leatho them barrel rolled into the men and started pecking them. After doing them justice, he went and picked Changhao's lock. The men saw this and started getting up. But then Triss slithered over, with his hood spread wide. The men, their eyes wide with terror, freaked out and ran out of the tent as fast as the could, where they met the rest of my crew along with the police.            The police, who had been called by my crew, disarmed and handcuffed the men.            That night, my animals performed the same trick beautifully on two able-bodied men. The crowd went wild and the circus promoter signed us on another American tour. I went to sleep that night felling happer than ever before.

Item_Response: :)The Circus(:                                                                                    >By:Jenny Kim<                   Hello, I Jenny Kim am going to tell you about 'THE CIRCUS.' In the circus there are several jobs you can do, Like: Trapezze, Juggling, Acrobatics, Ring Master, Clown,training animals, and the stage hands.These jobs at the circus are fun.So please keep reading!So here is my story of the circus jobs.                 Hello!Have you ever wanted to be on a trappeze or wanted to know about it?Well you are reading the right pargraph!Well The people who go on trappeze's are pretty scared but look like they are not because they practiced several times.If you know trappeze people fly off ropes! It is so cool! It looks so scary when they fly off and then go to the next bar!But when they were new and they were practing they would always fall of and be depressed but they sty strong and say 'I will achieve this goal!After years or months passed they are great!That is what is like being a person on a trappeze!                 This Paragraph is about juggling.Have you ever tried to juggle? Well if you haven't try now!   It is hard?Ehh?You juggle balls or pie or anything!As Like swords (WOW) or chain saws (DANGER) These jugglers have hard times. They have to practice WAY  more then any others.That is why maybe jugglers have so much fun.That is my paragraph about juggling.                 This is about acrobats.Those acrobats you proabably have seen looks so cool!Did you know that they do somersaults?They also launch from cannons, And tight rope walk? So scary!You are up so tall when you are looking down there probably isn't any safety when you fall down and you can break probably your body bones.That is what it is like being in a acrobat.                 Now, I Jenny Kim shall be telling you about the ring masters.The ring masters are the hosts of the circus. Then they announce who is going to come out next.The ring master shouts all day.TIRING!He has a special costume that is more natural then the rest of the acts.Then at the end of the show the ring master puts on an amazing show with the horses!Wouldnt that be exciting?That is what the ring masters dresses and does.                 Now, this is what most of the kids know from all the circuses.The clowns! The clowns entertain every audience.They ride in tiny little cars and always act silly! hehe The clowns throw pies and wear big pants!they wear so much make-up you don't even know whos who!?But guess what the clowns actaully learn they dont do whatever they want because that would create a mess.So that is why they practice how they should do it and not how to do it. That is what clowns do and what goes on clowns.               Next, I shall tell you about the animal trainers.These animal trainers are lucky but their job is risky.The animal trainers train animals.Of course! The animals train  monkeys,seals,elephants,leopards, snakes, lions, annd horses.They have danger hazard so they have to have medicine or someone who cures people like doctors. The animals have fun jumping through hoops and jumping very high.They sometimes make the tigers jump in the hoop of fire!Wow~!That is what  the animals do and what the trainers do.               Finally, the stage hands you can never forget!If you never had them you would have no circus and you need help putting up the tent. They also help by just calling saying 'you are almost next.' or 'you are next, Hurry!'They get the animals ready for the show and sometmes they have to clean the animals poop.eww~They also groom the animals and get their manes or hair ready for the nights show. Those are reasons why we need to have stage hands in the circus for help.              Well, I hope you had a nice time reading my essay because this may help you on a report.I hope you had fun reading the ones in the circus you like by the way did you like my essay?I hope this helps you because it would be a honor to me.Thank you and Goodbye~                                                                              ~The End~

Item_Response: Life In The Circus                  Life in the circus is busy and tough. It's busy because you have to get dressed, eat, go to school, have a quick break, you have chores to do, practice your performance, and finally perform. See how busy you can get if your in the circus. Well now for the tough part you don't get to visit your family! Yes i know it's depressing. Well that's how it's gonna be if you were in the circus. See there's a lot of things you have to do.              Okay so now you have to learn to get ready if you were in the circus. Now your getting ready to become a performer if you were in a real circus. First, you have to make sure your concentrating in school. Second, You have to be determinate to do this because there a lot of dangerous things you have to do if you were in the circus. Third, you have to be flexible and work hard. Fourth, you have to have eye contact with the audience. When you grow up you can be a circus person.                  If your sure you want to be a circus person you can be a:              Clown if your funny and like to joke around An acrobat hanging and swinging A juggler were you an juggle anything but you have to concentrate if it's going to hit you A tightrope walker to concentrate on balancing A tamer to tame animals. But there are other jobs, but those are extra work like cleaning up dropping from the animals and grooming the animals.                Remember you get to barley see your family because you have to concentrate at the circus because its like a job. But there are things you need to do at the circus because you can get paid because your performing for the crowd because people like to get entertained. People like to get scared to like if your going to fall off and than people (gasp).  But some times you get to thrilled with performing then suddenly you get to nervous because of the crowd. Than the performers that are not scared go on with there act and go on with you. There's a lot of things you need to do remember to concentrate, balance, and be confidant to get ready for the show.               You dont get to see your family because you have to concentrate on the job you have as a circus performer. You dont get to call from home because there's no service on the train their on. But if your going to perform in the state your family is in you might get to see them.               Atleast your making money to go to your family when you retire and go fly all the way to where your family lives. There is always a way to get to them.When your finished with the circus thing you get to go with your family and enjoy your life with them.               Then you have kids that want to follow your foot steps and they will have there own kids and they will follow them and go on.                                                                                                   THE END

Item_Response: Once there was a little boy named Timmy. Timmy lived in the circus but one day Timmy started to act sad and gloomy. It really got to his family and they wanted to help. So one day they sat him down in the pie car and started to talk. 'Now Timmy, you have been acting, how do I say this? Well, lets say different,' Said Timmys mom, Lily.                  'What do you meen?' Said Timmy with  a grim look on his face. 'Now son, can you tell us what is going on?' Quetioned Timmy's dad, Tom. 'Well, there is just no place to call home. I feel everyday that there is no home so whats the point of being here,'             Then Timmy got up and went to his room. His parents then fallowed to cheer him up a little. 'Honey? Can we come in? We want to talk to you,' Said Lily but right after You could hear Timmy say a faint ' Sure, Whatever.'                  Lily and Tom walked in and sat down on his bed. 'Timmy, I now it's not the glamorous life you want but this is where we belong. It may just be an old, rusty train to you but we grew up here and this is what we call home and someday I hope you call it home to because this  is where you are going to grow up. Timmy sat up and looked at his parents and finelly said ' This is home. I may not have realized it, but this is home.                                                                           THE END

Item_Response: Plan:       Introduction-   Name Job- Traing the animals Circus Name Favorite thing to train are the leopards   Body paragraph #1: Favorite thing to train     Train the leopards Why?  because they are cute, they are unique and its's not like training a dog   Body paragraph #2: Least favorite things:   How late and early you get up and go to bed Not being by my home and family Working from sun-up to sun-down Eating out of a pie car No real friends or sports   Body Paragraph #3: leopards names and about them:   Names of the leopards What each one does Leopards in training   Body paragraph #4 Everything else:   People I travel with My closest friend I travel with About the trailer   Conclusion:   Similar to the introduction              Hello, my name is Khloe. I work at the circus named Lots 'o' Fun. I work as an animal trainer, but my favorite animal to train are the leopards.          My favorite animals to train are the lepards, because they are adorable. Also, because they are very unique and it's not like training a dog. However, you need to help them practice enough so they don't forget what they are doing in the middle of a performance.          There are many leopards, but here are some of their names, Lola, Daisy, Dotty, and Smarty. The trick that the audience loves the most is when they jump through hoops. Right now we have 3 leopards in training. Their names are Sky, Rolo, and Taliver.          Some of the people I travel with are Carl and Anne, the Circus clowns. Also, there is Terri, Carla, Andrew, Patty, and Carrie, our acrobats. My closest friend I travel with is Tonya, a fellow animal trainer. Sometimes the trailer can be very tight with everybody in there.           My least favorite things to do are working from sun-up to sun-down, so, you only get a little sleep. Also, it's hard being away from my family for so long and not having friends for a long time because you keep moving to different cities. Then, there is also having to eat out of a pie car every night.          So, sometimes the circus life can be great, but sometimes it can be very rough. That is about my life traveling with the Lots 'o' Fun Circus, many fun people, and the best animals!

Item_Response: What Happens At A Circus       Have you ever been to a Circus?  Well, If you have'nt I'm going to tell you all about one!  The circus is a fun colorful place full of  interesting people and animals.  A circus is where people come from different states to perform a show for  you.  A circus is also a place where you can enjoy watching unusual acts and laugh at different things.  A circus also has animals that preform tricks for you such as, Jumping through hoops, Standing on two feet, And danceing.  Also there are acrobats who preform different stunts hanging on ropes.       First, Circus clowns, Circus clowns are funny people wearing makeup and big floppy shoes.  You may have seen a clown at your circus and if you have'nt here are some common details a clown has, Big floppy shoes, Curly fluffy hair, Silly makeup, And a funny outfit.  Clowns are nice and often play jokes on other clowns.  Jokes are funny to clowns here are some common jokes they play, Pie in the face, water in the face, and loud music in their ears.  Clowns are funny but scary at times to me.       Second, Circus acrobats, Circus acrobats are cool interesting people.  They preform tricks on ropes and flip in the air.  Acrobats are like professional ballet dancers but on ropes.  They twirl and slide on ropes to make people think they are going to fall wich leaves them in suspence.  Also, Acrobats have to trust their partner or they might put the partner's life in danger.       Third, Circus juggler,  Circus jugglers throw different objects it the air and toss them in a circular motion makeing them come into each hand evenly and the cycle continues on.  Circus jugglers toss things such as, Rings, Sticks, Animals, And balls.  Juggling  requires only one person but you can have at least four in a group.  Jugglers usualy wear puffy red, White, Or blue shirts to make them look interesting.  Also, Jugglers may do tricks while juggling they might flip or ride on a unicycle while they are juggling.       Fourth, Circus tightrope walker, Tightrope walkers walk on ropes that are conected to two platforms one is where the walk begins and one is where the walk finishes.  The tightrope walker has a very dangerous job in the circus they walk on a rope several feet above the ground.  Even though the rope is high up they usualy have a net hoisted above the ground just incase they fall.  Tightrope walkers can also do more stunts with their job to make it more interesting and dangerous.  Tightrope walkers can ride motorcycles on a rope, Jump on the rope, And sometimes spin on the rope.       Now, Circus horses, Circus horses are fun animals that usualy jump up and down.  Circus horses have to listen to their trainer or they will be excused from the circus.  If the horses are not trained they might go crazy and hurt somebody.  The people who preform with the horses might jump on their backs or stand on their backs as a trick.  The horses are usualy black or white to make them stand out.       Later, The circus tent, The circus tent is where everything goes on, the entire show depends on the tent.  The circus tent is the basic traveling home of the circus people.  The circus tent is wide and tall like a small house.  The tents are usualy white and red or white and blue depending on the type of circus.  The circus tent takes a while to put up if you do not have the right kind of help with you.           Next, The circus lifestyle, The circus life isnt all fun and games all the time.  You have to work all day and all night all the time even on weekends!  Circus performers don't get alot of sleep either they have to be up around six or seven A.M. and the noght before they were up until like twelve P.M. so the few hours they get to sleep is pure gold to them.  How their day starts is go to the pie car to get food for breakfast, Get dressed, Practice for a while, Go to the morning show, Then practice for the matinee.  Pretty harsh living style but the preformers say its all worth it!       After that,  Chores a young circus performer has to do, First, they clean animal stables I think that job would be disgusting becaus the animals use the bathroom there.  Then they groom the animals to prepare them for the show.  Next, they feed the animals so they don't get hungry during the show and eat the straw scattered on the ground.  After that, they practice for the upcoming show so they can do a perfect job and please the audience.  Later, They let the animals rest so they will be well rested for the show.       Then, Traveling school,  Their school is like no other it travels with them on their trips to different countrys.  It may get hard at times becaus other kids on the school trailer speak different languages and you can not understand what they are saying.  Also when they travel all around the world they see the different cultures that the states have and that makes the lessons come alive.  The school isn't much different from regular schools it's just on wheels.  The school makes it to where the circus children have education while they are on the road.       Last,  Circuses are fun at times and hard living at times to.  Would you ever give up seeing your family for the circus life?  I would never do that becaus without my family I would be upset.  Circus life is different from a regular life it has its up sides its down sides and the sides that are just right.  This concludes my report about the circus.

Circus schedule:                    6:00 A.M They wake up, get dressed and eat at the pie car for breakfast. Now the are setting up the tents,lights,music for the show. At 6:30 it's dinner time, time to go to the pie car. And back to the show. Circus workers do 2 show every week day.? 2 on saturday 2 on sunday. Then it starts all over again

Item_Response: Life In  The Circus                 ????I would want to work at a circus because you can see new stuff.We can travel to lots of cities and see ancient bones. We can also see famous people that we haven't seen before.Russian,Mexican, and french people can teach us new languages. We can show our skills and talents to other people.                                                                                                    The part that I hate is you have to wake up at 7:00 A.M get dressed eat breakfast.The crews have to set up the lights,tents, and the music for tonight's show. You have to feed the animals,you have to clean them. You have to train them that's the hard part.                 The show is about to start everybody is ready. The acrobats are jumping in the air. The tightrope walker is steady. The horses are walking. The trains are going fast. The show is over people are clapping the acrobats are bowling.Everybody is going home cars are leaving.We eat dinner relax.We have 10 shows a week,Its the same thing again.We will end up in another citie.

Item_Response: My Debut in The Circus            It is 1/7/2002, when I just joined a job as a circus performer. I was trying to be and acrobat, but it was hard. My partner Manuel is helpng me how to be a good acrobat. Manuel taught me 24/7 until I was ready for my debut.           Finally, my debut came I was so nervous about my first circus show. I was also afraid that I was going to mess up. All the pressure came to me. I waited, waited, and waited until it was Manuel and me. It was our turn to go on next. The clown introduced me to the crowd.            The crowd went wild when they heared that it was my debut. when I went on my stage, I did what I needed to do, which was to entertain the crowd.There were so many people watching the circus, more pressure came. When I went on my first jump I swinged and jumped off. Then, Manuel caught me and put me back on my swing.I couldn't belive I made my first jump.            When I saw my boss smiling at me, I was happy. Happy enough to do my second jump with confidence. So I went off. Good thing there was a net underneath me because i fell, good thing that nothing was hurt. When I was on the net, I springed up and went on my swing and tried my 360 jump again. I did it and Manuel caught me. Everybody was amazed that I made my second jump. They don't know that i have 4 jumps.            When I got back from my ledge, Manuel and I jumped at the same time and did our frontflips off our swings. All of the crowd loved us. Finally, it was my 4th jump. I have to do a backflip while doing a 360. My last jump was hard I missed my first try and my second try. You know what they say third time is the charm. I swinged off my edge and looked at the crowd. They were amazed what Manuel and I were doing. We jumped off the same time, and did our 360 backflip. We got each other's swings and landed on the ledge.            When we got down, we ave each other a high five. We went to our boss and wanted to know how we did. He said great. We were so happy we gave each other another high five. Oh man I can't wait to go back and do the same thing what we did at the end.            While we waited to jump again before the crowd goes home.We needed to get water so we will not be thirsty. After an hour, all of the member went on. We did our acts again all at once. It was so cool and there was confetti. We all bowed to the crowd and said goodnight. I was so sad that the crowd was not here, but couldn't wait for the other crowd for next week.            I couldn't believe that the crowd rated the shoe 5 out of 5 stars. My debut was a success and I did a really good job on my debut day. After this month I have to go to Florida. I can't wait to go in the beach and have fun. Everybody couldn't believe that I only had 6 months to get ready for today and all that work payed off.

Item_Response: My name is Cassandra. I live in a trailer with my family in the circus. My family consists of my brother Eric, my sister Mile y, my parents and me. My day starts with breakfast in the pie cart and then school starts. My brother is in the high school class and my sister is in preschool. I am in middle school in 6th grade. I go to a special trailer every morning to the sixth grade class which consists of 3 boys and 4 girls, including me. After school I play with my cat Sunny and do my homework. Next I practice my craft.       I am a trapeze artist and right now I am practicing flipping off a trapeze and into another trapeze. It requires a lot of skill and patience. My dad is working on his clowning skills and my mom is working on the tightrope. She is preforming a difficult trick in  which she must ride two unicycles stacked on top of each other while on a string tight rope suspended 50 feet in the air. My brother is working on a trick in which he is thrown out of a cannon and my sister is working on doing a flip off a trampoline. My friends do acrobatics and trapeze. Then we have dinner and get into costumes. Mine is a sparkly green costume.       The show begins! I do a trick which I learned a long time ago: doing a handstand on my friend'ss head while she is sitting on a trapeze holding a pole which my other friend walks on to get to our trapeze. She then hangs on the seat of the trapeze while it lowers and I get off.   The show ends and I walk back with my family, tired as a sloth.       It'ss midnight and I am in bed. I wonder what it is like to be a regular kid, about to see me preform tomorrow.

Her parents told her if she doesn't come up with a act in two days. Ashley's going to have to work with the tigers and is not going to have the choice.    The next morning she woke with her clown pajamas on ate a bowl of cereal bacon and four pancakes. When your in the circus you have to be full so you don't get so hungry. Also make sure have a good breakfast. Then she went to the gym in her pajamas the clowns were laughing at her. Ashley worked out for a while then got ready. When they got to the circus they set up the tents and decorations. Ashley ran to her parents and told them what she wanted to perform. She wanted to perform on the trapedes her parnets agreed. Ashley's mother brought in a real live tiger and told Ashley to get on top of it. Ashley was nervouse she got on the tiger she wasn't scared anymore. Her mother siad your going to have to do two acts.    Ashley agreed with her mother then it was showtime she did excellent with the tigers her parents were so proud of her . It was the last show and she performed great. It was time to leave for the summer and Ashley misses the circus so much.

Item_Response: The things you need to have to get in a circus is a talent and the right body shape and be very determined.If you think circus life is easy  your wrong its tough its hard to do all of that stuff like bicycling or being a acrobat or a juggler you half to practice for all of that.       Its not easy to do all of theses things when your away from home.But its fun to see all of the people that come to the circus and watch all of the animals and acrobats,jugglers and tightrope walkers.       At 3:30 P.M. I have chores and practice.I feed,water, and groom the animals like horses we use in our horseback act.I'm working on a leaping from a trampoline into the horses back;it takes balance and concentration.At 10:30 P.M. the show is over . I'm wiped out from all of that work.       One of the upsides of being in the circus that you get to go everywhere.Philippa has worked all over the world including Australia,Japan and all over North America.The circus has given me the opportunity to go to so many different places and meet so many different people.       I miss my home and  and where i live at and i miss my family.You have a lot of practice a lot of hours of working and then you show it off in front of a big crowd.THE END.

Item_Response: When I Was In the Circus                                                                                       by Justin Mata                                                                                                                                                                                                       It was 7:00 A.M.  it was a cold morning.  I  had  just woken up in my circus trailer .   I got  ready  and went to the pie car for eggs and  bacon . They were are ready setting up the tents for tonight's show .                                                                                                    After I eat I go to school at 9:00 A.M. We have are own schoolhouse . We had computer testing  and report cards. Many of my classmates speak  other languages like :   French, Russian , Italian. 3:00 P.M. schools over and time for a quick break .The clowns lets  me juggling balls with them.I also play with my to dogs Raider and Browne.                     At 3:30 P.M. its my chores  and practice .I feed ,water, and groom the horse we use in our horseback act . I'm working on leaping  from  trampoline onto the  horse .6:30        dinnertime.  My family  and I go to the pie car but don't eat much because we performing  tonight. 10:30 P.M. the show is over. I'm wiped out .Walking back to are trailer . 12:00 A.M. In bed . thinking about the end of are touring season.It will be nice to be back in our real home in California.

Item_Response: LIFE IN THE CIRCUS            Life in the circus isn't just fun and games it's hard work.Despite what many people think,the life of a circus performer isn't all high-flying fun and games and clowning around.          To begin with,you have to drive 20,000 miles in seven months each year.Visiting 150 cities from sunup to sundown.First,you wake up at 7:00 A.M to eat and get dressed.Then at 9:00 A.M its school time.Like every school ours has computers,test,and report cards.Many people in the school and circus speak other languages like:French,Russian,and Italian.At 3:30 P.M.Chores and practice.We feed the animals and water them.Then we groom the horses in our horseback acts.At 6:30 P.M.Dinnertime.We go to the pie car to eat,but we dont eat much because we're performing tonight.We do 10 shows a week:one each weekday,plus a matinee on wednesday,two on Saturday,and two on Sunday.10:30 P.M.The show is over.At 12:00 A.M.Its time to go to asleep.           Next,you have to have to have specific talent.You have to be like a acrobat,trapeze artist,circus clown,juggler,tight rope walker,and know how to train animals.You also have to have the right body type and be determined.If your determined you can start at a young age.Like Philippa started when she was 5 years old.She did musical theatre and ballet and all kinds of music,singing,acting and everthing to hone my craft'says Philippa,who also trained in rhythmic gymnastics for years.There are so many people out there who want to do what you do,that you have to go for it.You have to put your heart into it and be certain that's what you want to do           Finally,theres always gonna be bad days or good days.Sometimes theres not always gonna be happy and perfect days as you think circus are.The good part about being in the circus is that you get to travel across the world.The girl that started when she was 5,Phillippa has worked all over the planet,including Australia,Japan and all over North America.'The circus has given me the opportunity to go to so many different places and meet so many new people said Phillippa.Now the bad days or downside days.Circus perfomers work long days and spend a lot of time away from home. You have to work a lot of long hours and weekends as well.              As you can see,these are all the things circus have and all the things people have to do to have a good circus.

Item_Response: Here's what a daily basis in the circus is like.       At 7:00 a.m, I have to eat breakfast in the pie car and have food like pancakes and bacon, and eggs. The crew is setting up for the show tonight.       9:00 a.m., School time, I go to school for six hours each day. Like any school, there is modern technology, tests, and report cards. Since we perform all over the world, many of my classmates speak other languages, so it is sort of a bilingual school. As we travel all over the world, our geography lessons are great help.       3:00 p.m. School has just got out. It is sort of like playtime for me because the clowns' let us play with their stuff like riding unicycles and juggling, and we also have a dog and we play with hom afterschool too. I sometimes get bored, but I can always entertain myself.       3:30 p.m. We practice what we are going to do tonight for the circus and do chores. The chores can be really boring like I have to pick up the elephants' poop and feed the elephants. I have to practice my acts like riding on the unicycle and juggling. Trainers are doing training with the animals.       6:30 p.m. Dinnertime. We eat a small meal before we perform our show because we could get cramps and we are performing tonight. We do 8 shows a week. One eack weekday, and two on each Saturday and one on sunday.       10:30 p.m. The show is over. I am exhausted after a big show.We pass the circus offices, concession stands, stables, and trailers. WEe will set up in another town in two days.        12:00 a.m. I am in bed and thinking about the end of our season. It will be very nice to go back to our real home in California. I might be a circus performer, or maybe not. Who Knoes? The circus is fun, but it is a very fun part of the year.

Item_Response: CIRCUS                                     By:Alex Solorzano                                                One day my mom got really mad at me for having a bad attitude. So that night I squeezed out my window and headed towards the circus to see if I could get a job.I tried to talk to one of the clowns but he kept shooting me with a water flower.So I went to another clown and he used a hand buzzer on me!The instructor asked me where my mother was and I told him I was an orphan.He asked me if I had any special talent and I said 'NO.'         Then the next day the instructor came and woke me up and started training me.I learned some pranks and things like that.My favorite part was when he taught me to throw pies and that was fun but hard.now the other clowns are working with me and are showing me tricks with money and hanker chiefs.                                      10 YEARS LATER        Now I am 20 years old and life is horrible because I get hardly any sleep and I have to drive one of the semi trucks because we are short on drivers.Every day is the same as the next and we eat the same thing everyday.I wish I never would have run away.

Item_Response: The Circus Life                                                                    It would be fun to join the circus.The reasons are I can still go to school when I'm at the circus and have computers,tests, and report cards. The other reason is that I can do different acts.Some of the acts are doing somersaults off of horses backs and leaping off a trampoline onto a horses back.The other acts are being a circus clown, acrobats, a circus juggler, and a tightrope walker.               The circus act that I would do would be able to train the animals.Like the leperods,  elephants, lions, tigers, chimpanzees and monkeys.I think it might be fun to train those animals.Also I would  want to be a trapeze artist.I would want to be a trapeze artist because it would be very cool to be stretchy.Another reason I would want to be a trapeze artist is that it would be awesome to able be swing from high places.               Those are the reasons why I would want to be in the circus.It would be fun because I could do a lot of acts.The act that i would want to do the most is to train the animals.Like the lions, tigers, elephants, chimpanzees, and the monkeys.The last act that i would ever want to be is a juggler.I wouldn't want to be a juggler because it probably wouldn't be any fun.

Item_Response: One day my friend Maria and I went to see the big circus on main street I heard it was going to have the best performance ever.So while me and my friends were sitting on the first row we met this very nice clown Edd he was a first starter.He was giving every body flyer to join the circus and he told us that if we wanted to join we would have to go to the back of the tent after the show.So after the show me and my friend went to the back and there was no line so we talked to the man about the big tour there going to have.So we said we would be back tomorrow after we asked are moms when we asked them they surprised us and said yes but we would have to call them every day or they will come pick us up.So me and my friend were so excited that we couldn't wait for the next day.So the next day we went back to the circus when they were packing up and we told them we can go so they said they leave this Friday to London we were so happy that we were really going.                       They told us we were going to have a lot of practice so on Friday me and my friend said are good bye's to are family's and left on the train.That next morning we did a lot of practice and i had learned how to go across a long rope with out falling it was really fun and that clown Edd was very good at everything for a beginner.Well after a week me and my friend really missed are family's but my friend said she was going to leave so she called her mom and she got picked up in New York the next day.So that means im by my self know but after she left me and Edd were having so much fun we learned how to do so many thing i even learned how to walk a leopard on a leash it is very hard.So after a couple of performances i really got use to the circus life it was really fun.When we went to Las Vegas it was the fun we got this big hotel and we got to get new clothes for this big act were going to do in Circus Circus.After 3 months i got to know everybody and i felt like i was part of the family.                         So its December now and i only have one month left until this tour ends i had lots of fun meeting everyone and learning all the tricks.But this last performance im going to try my best and take some risk because i want to remember this life.So tonites the performance and i cant wait im going to do all types of tricks like learn how to jump on the trampoline while  juggle and how to teach a tiger how to jump into a fire ring with out burning himself and many more.after the big performance at the circus people gathered and ate a big dinner we all had a good time but we were all leaving the next morning we were all sad but we told each other that we were going to do this next year.Then the next day the train dropped every body off and i was so happy to see my family but i missed everyone.But certainly a year later we all did what we told each other and we all were back to the circus life.

Item_Response: Life in the Circus          Hello my name is Beth T. Lewis and i'm going to teLl you about life in a Circus. Life in a Circus is very difficult, but not for me because I have been in the Circus for 15 years. I started when I was 7 years old, I wanted to do it because my parents has their own circus, so once I saw them doing acrobats I knew from the beginning that's what I wanted to do. I trained for 3 years and when I turned 10 it was my first performance. The performance I had to do was walking on a horse back while it was running. At first I was very scared but then I saw my father show me what I had to do before showtime  to refresh my memory and then I noticed it wasn't that scary after all. It was 5 minutes before show, I was next. Before I went on my father wished me good luck and it was time for me to go on. As I walked onto the platform I noticed how many people came just to watch the Circus, then I said to myself I can't mess up or my parents reputation will be ruined. So, after all I performed my act and I landed it it was perfect everyone loved it. I have been doing the Circus every since.        Now, I've told my story so it's time for me to tell you the types of training you wil have to do for your entrance in your life in the Circus.        If you want to be in the Circus you will have to be fit and in shape. You will have to take contortionist and acrobat lessons. Most of all you will have to be determined to do it and not quit and that's how you will get the performing act. I'm gonna tell you only a fewjobs they are gonna have there just incase you will want to do one and I will tell you what types of trainings you will have to do with them.       The first job I am going to tell you about is acrobats. In order to do acrobats you will have to have great balance and posture. Next, you will have to be in shape and have lots of flexability. The types of training you will have to do is just learnong how to do certain moves and how to hold your self in the air with nothing holding you. Then, you will have to learn how to flip and spin in the air and that's how you do acrobats in the air without nothing holding you but a rubber-band like object that you will have to hold on to in order not to fall out of the air and this will take lots of strength.       The next job I am going to tell you is about traing lions. To train lions you have to be very brave and have the animals to like you. Warning: If the animals do not like you stay away from them and try to stay calm. The type of training you will have to take is only classes on how to get the animals to do what you say and it will take lots of practice to get the animals to like you. Tip: Give the animal treats after they do what you tell them to do.      That's all the Tips I have for you today until next time GOOD LUCK! I have a show to do. Good Bye!

Item_Response: The circous                                                                                               Once appon a time there was a little girl about six years old who's name was Cindy. Cindy always loved going to the circus with her parents but she wondered why they always left before the show began and came back when it ended. So she went to investigate what her parents where doing one thursday night and this is what happend.                     One thursday night Cindy went with her parents to a circus and her parents went somewhere elese so Cindy folowed her mom, Terissa, to a funky room where ladies were getting in funky costumes. But then her mom grabed one out of a familier bag and put it on. So Cindy found another bag and put the costome on witch fit and followed her mom witch looked like she was waiting in a long line for something then heard her mom call out,'Millie, where are you.' Then someone replied in the dreeing room, be there in a minute.' But no one came and her mom said,'Oh, i didnt realize you got here Milie,' and grabed her hand and pulled her out in the show ring. Then she said ,'run and jump high,' so she did what her mother said. Item_Response: Life at a Circus             One day Margret and her parents decided that they wanted to go to the circus.When they arrived at the circus they paid for their tickets and bought refreshments.             Once the show began they saw acrobats swinging off of the ropes.'Mommy I want to be an acrobat when I grow up,' said Margret.'Margret you have to have the right body type and be very determined. Now watch the show,' said Mrs. Robinson.Next they saw people standing and doing tricks off of their horses. The crowd cheered as someone did a somersault off of his horse.              Then they saw the tight rope walkers one man almost fell off the rope. Several people were cheering at this point. One by one the tight ropers walked on the ropes and none of them fell off. Finally they showed the clowns and the jugglers. The jugglers could juggle five bowling pins at once. The clowns really scared Margret.              At about ten o'clock the circus show was over. Margret was really tired so when she got home she went straight to bed. That night Margret wished she could  have stayed longer. She hopes that she can go back another time.

Item_Response: Circus Raiders       In the circus, lots of things go on, and i would like to tell you about some of that.       In the tent, Hudson the clown was getting ready for the big circus. He was inside the helicopter which would take them to the circus. They put the elephants inside the back of a train which takes them to the circus as well. Many other things were put in the train. As well as costumes, baloons, food and water supplies and many other things. The helicopter would take them to the circus. Beginning now the rotors began to spin, and the train's engine was steaming.       Both of the transports took off, with 120 miles to travel. once in paris, the helicopter landed. The train came up the slope to a stop 20 minuets later. Everyone got ready for the big day at the paris national circus, which was tommarow. The people got out and trained for their' acting postions. Hudson, getting out of the helicopter, welcomed the others that had arrived in the train. Hudson was nervous as they enter The giant tent, filled with many people. Over 17,000 People filled the seats. The actors got ready as chinook helicopters dropped supplies from a rope. Hudson picked up the clown suit from the care package. They all walked inside the tent as the helicopters flew away.           An hour later...       The acts were very good. Everybody clapped and cheered. Then hudson's act started. Hudson didn't show up. The crowd grew silent. Dead silence filled the Tent. Hudson was on his computer. But the time was fast on his computer. The crowd, booing, yelling and waiting for hudson's act was angry. Hudson then remembered he forgot to change the time! It wasn't 5:00, it was 6:00! Hudson then ran for the door to the stage. The clown was rushing to the acting grounds. But the crowds were throwing Tomatoes!  It was like a battlefield out there. The poor clowns had tomatoe splatters all over their expensive suits! Then, the lion cage opened and the scary lions ran wild! It was a disaster! The clowns Ran to the dressing room and yelled at hudson. The clowns then grabbed throwing pies and headed for the stage. But the crowd was gone. Just gone. They had left! But there were still two people. He said he wanted to see an act. So now was their time. They got ready. They put Woods in a container and hudson got a saw. He cut the box. Woods was seperated! The two people liked the act and asked if they could do a few more tricks. They said yes.           The next month...       The circus called 'Pieday' was a hit! They were famous!  All the people wanted to win front row seats to see them. They were going to Russia To perform next. They all loaded up in the helicopter as they took off. They were gonna be a great group! The chinook landed in russia and everybody liked them! This was very good! People of all over the world cheered and clapped for pieday circus group. And one day Woods the clown got called to go to a famous child's birthday! This was great! Woods was a tightrope walker. Hudson was a clown, an acrobat and a great juggler. He could perform multiple things. Thousands of circus Chinooks flooded the skies on the day of the birthday. Trucks that were red carried supplies on the streets. This was a big thing. The mansion was about 36 floors high. THAT'S BIG. Once there the clowns got all the supplies and the whole day went well. Pieday was the most famous circus in the world.
