Item_Response: The Time I Saved the Circus       This day started out like any other summer day. I could here birds chirping outside and my mom cooking breakfast downstairs. I had been anticipating this day for months now. I couldn't wait to go to the circus.       I lived far out in a small country town and the circus hadn't come in a long time. My family had a farm and we had many animals but my favorites were horses. My mom once said to our neighbor that I had a real gift with the horses. I knew every thing about them. I had once heard that the circus that was coming had the most amazing horses in the world.       Later at the circus we bought our tickets and walked in. The tent was ginormous! It was red and white striped and seemed to go on forever. We quickly took our seats and waited for the show to start. Suddenly a man in stilts walked onto the stage and started speaking in a  low voice.' I am sorry but our opening act, the horses, has been canceled due to our sick horse master'       I was filled with disappointment and wanted to cry. I could see the horses back in the other room stamping impatiently and wondering where their master was. Suddenly the man on the stilts seemed to remember that this was not in a big city and that most people would own farms and know how to command a horse.  So the man said,  'Although, if anyone knows how to work with a horse we could have them train for a day and you could come back tomorrow.' No one was very happy about the fact that they would have to come back tomorrow, not even the performers. They knew it would set back the scheduling for the tour. But they didn't want to disappoint anyone who had paid to see their show.       I wasn't even listening to the announcer because I was too sad and lost in thought. But my mom suddenly stood up and said, 'My daughter has a wonderful talent with horses, she could do it!' Every one started laughing. The thought of a little girl tending the horses in a circus was just absurd. Despite all the laughter, no one else volunteered. I was going to work in the circus with one of the most amazing horses in the world! I was so excited.       Later that afternoon, I started to work with the horses. It was very easy in the beginning but then I learned how to orchestrate much more complex tricks with the horses. I learned that I wouldn't actually be on the horse but that I would just be giving the horses commands.       The next day at the show, I got very nervous. Although I had been training non-stop yesterday I still had butterflies in my stomach. Before I knew it, I was walking onstage with the magnificent white horses. The lights started to dim and it seemed like all eyes were on me. I started my first trick. The show was simple at first but throughout my act the tricks got harder and harder. Finally I was finished. I turned and took a bow. I thought I saw out of the corner of my eye the horses bow their long graceful necks too. Everyone started applauding. I was filled with energy and happiness. That was the day I saved the circus.

Item_Response: Ropes To Hopes                   Katleen is the best gymnastics girl in her class.She is well built and even knows how to work her way into anything. She can balance on a balance beam and even and straight with books on her head (I think that is only a plus though).Katleen is someone that can really be the best at anything.           One day she was walking in the park with three other friends that were dear to her heart.They stopped by a refreshments stand to get some ice cold water when there it was.The poster for the  new opening in the Cirque Du Soleil.They had heard about it on the news but didn't know they could have a chance.All three girls tore a slip off with the information on it.Katleen really wanted this job as a kid she was always watching the circus with her mom and dad but today she has a shot at being in the circus and having kids watching her perform.She was so excited but then she read that each entry needs to have a opposite gender partner to be able to try out.She automatically thought of her friend Devin.He was her best friend and they would be a perfect pair.Devin was also her crush.She really thought that he was cute but everyone thought she was silly.Right then and there she pulled out her phone and called Devin.He picked up in excitement. He said, 'You'll never guess what!I just found a sign up sheet for the Cirque Du Soliel today when i was in the park walking Sally.Do you wanna be my partner.' 'Yes Devin I'll be your partner.That's exactly what I wanted to ask you too so i guess you beat me to it.' said Katleen in a happy voice.The two met up in the park and started to practice right away doing back flips,side aerials,and cartwheels.They looked lovely together let's just hope they can pull it off in three days or all that work is just trash.        Three days passed and today is the day.Devin and Katleen both met up in the parking lot of the try outs and walked in together as a pair.The two went to the bathrooms and got on their leotards and Katleen got on her tutu.They came back out and got someone to go and take a picture of them in their outfits so that they remember this day forever.About an hour later the pair was called up to get onto the ladder to get on the  rope for acrobats.They both were very nervous.They stepped out on the stage and the music started.Their piece was titled 'Butterfly'They got back down the ladder and hugged each other to death.They really did do their best and they both knew it.They were the tenth to last couple to perform.After the end the judge called out  the top three.'Kevin and Destiny in third place.Niall and Hailee in second place.Finally Katleen and Devin in first place.'The couple jumped up and started screaming at once that means that they won the competition.        Devin and Katleen both woke up extra early the next Monday to get ready to get on the bus to go to the circus. When they got there everyone was so welcoming to them. They fit straight in with the crowd everyone accepted that they were the new people to their team.When Devin and Katleen got there they ran their routine with all the other people in the circus.Katleen thought that it would be all fun and games until she actually got there    and experienced what it was like to be in the circus.Devin wasn't getting off at the right foot.Everyone loved and hated him for all the wrong reasons.His father was the person that was going to stop the circus from performing.One clown said that her was told that  he  was banished from the earth along with his descendents.Devin was hurt that they thought that he was going to stop them and ruin their chances of being the best.Katleen was sad for Devin.He had always had this problem since people knew who his dad was.         That night Devin wrote to his mom and said he was thinking of leaving the circus forever.When Katleen heard of this she was disappointed that he didn't want to go through with his promise to never leave her alone.Secretly Katleen wanted him to leave so she can stop worrying about their friendship. She told Devin how she felt and the next day he was gone.'What did I do?!' thought Katleen when she read the letter.Her new partner was a guy named Niall.He was at the competition.He said that he loved her performance in the competition.        Katleen finally got over Devin and just in time because her show was in three days.She and Niall looked awesome together.He loved to be an acrobat with her.She started to practice in her hotel room just so she would be perfect.She didn't even go to her own party because she was practicing.She never wanted to miss over twelve minutes of practice time.This time was very important to her.She was determined to show everyone how graceful she can be. But like every good circus performer she started to miss home.She miss her family and her dog Pepper.She could stand being away for so long.One day she decided that she wanted to leave and get a better job then being in the circus.Niall finally talked her out of it and made her think if she really wanted to sacrifice something so precise to just o she can get a better job.He said,'I understand how you feel.I felt like that when i came to be with you but as you can see I'm as fine as fine can be I'm even better.' Niall did have a point  thought Katleen.I can't away something that I've worked very hard for to go to waste.She decided to buckle down and get focused on what she wanted to do and why she wanted to do it.         Katleen knew that her dad and mom would not approve for her to not get focused and be ready for something as big as this.The big day came the day she wanted to come all her life is finally here.The circus came and now she wanted it to be the very most special day of her career.They didn't think that Niall could perform because he was getting really sick.They were sxcared.So Kateen had to work with an unexperienced guy by the name of Gaert.He was handsome but his acrobatic skills sucked.He never knew which way to turn her but it pulled off and lolooked so unique and special that they had to love him.He brought a good experience to the show it was unique and special in a way that was also very funny.The  Cirque Du Soliel did pretty good thanks to Katleen and her strong courage.

Item_Response: I think that liveing in a circus would be fun because you get to do abunch of cool stuff. One cool thing is that you get to proform with people from all over the world. Another cool thing is you get to around the country. One realy cool thing is that you get to live with all sorts of cool people.       But being a circus proformer dose have its ups and downs. One down side is you have to practice all day. Another down side is you have to clean up after the animals in youre show. One really bad down side is if you get hurt during your act you could be put in a hospital.       Its not all games but its still fun to be in a cricus. One up side is durring the show you get the admeration of the entire croud. Another up side is evetually you get at least a little bit famos. The best part is you get to see places like washintonDC.       Their are some ups and downs and some things have a nutral feeling to them. One thing that has anutal feeling to me is horse bace rideing. One ofthe very best part is you dont have to pay to get in. You can get free food at the stands.       Once youre finised with your act you can mess around with the animals. After youre finised with youre act you can watch the rest of the show. Their are alot of things to do in a cicus like acrobatics and jugleing. So in con conlushonthir are some up s and downs to liveing in a cricus but its still fun.

Item_Response: LIFE AT THE CIRCUS       To day I woke up and I ate breakfast in the food kart I ate waffles with sirup then I got dressed for the day then I practiced juggling when I was done I trained a tiger named BOB. BOB was going to ride a bike on a tightrope and juggle at the same time.    It was lunch it was a ham sandwich with root beer. It is almost time for the show and my team and I were doing a show tonight. The clowns will give out bullunes and ride horses the acrobats will fly the tightrope walker well walk on a tightrope. Time for the show   it is packed in hear we love the show that is my day.

Item_Response: What the story is about is a man named Jo. Jo wanted to be in the circus all his life, so Jo practiced being a clown. Then when he was old enough, he went to find a circus,and he found one! He went inside, there were clowns juggling pies and riding unicycles, acrobats on the high-wire everything was there to see! Jo went inside and asked to be a clown and the owner said 'Yes'. Jo was in the circus! he dressed up as a clown and went inside, and there was more things inside then outside! There were people grooming the elephants and horses, and acrobats jumping from horse to horse when they were moving! Jo's act was to  juggle with pies and jump on the trampoline! After the circus they all got paid and went home. Jo went home and fell asleep.       The next day was the same but they were going to Italy! So, every body went home and packed their things and came back in a few minutes, with things, but some people lived in Italy, most of them lived in Italy. Jo and the others went to the plane and went of to Italy! it took a day to get there because they missed a flight, but they got to Italy the next day. everybody was exited to do the circus with new people! But every body was hungry after the trip, so everybody went into the pie-car and had breakfast. then the people who lived in Italy went to there house and went to get there things.       Jo was amassed at what he saw in Italy! he saw different food and different cars. he bought a few different things and he looked at the museum paintings, then it was time to go back to the plane and go to China to perform they went to the plane station, but they missed there flight! it wasn't supposed to come back in a month! they went by car and went to China, but then they found another plane station and then went inside and was just in time to get there plane flight! the plane had to stop for fuel. then they went to China!       Jo and everybody else could see China! They landed at an airport and got out, they went to the grassy area and seted up the circus tent and they started the circus and so many people came! Jo had to sleep and ride a unicycle around the tent! So they did the act and then they went inside a SUV and went to sleep. the next morning and went to the plane station to get a ride to Seadle! They were just in time to catch the flight to Seadle!       They made it to Seadle and they put up the tent and they went to the piecar to eat. Jo was going to the tent to say 'Can I get paid?' The owner said 'Yes'. Jo got paid and he was going to take a break from the circus and go home. Jo said 'Goodbye everyone!' They said 'Goodbye Jo!' and he bought a car and went home. Jo said 'Im going back to the circus to be with my friend's'.

Item_Response: Well in the circus you have to practice for hours a day to get ready for the big show. You need to make sure that you are ready enough so you do not mess up. Even if they work at the circus they still have to go to school in order to learn. Their life is much different from ours but they still sleep eat breath they are still human beings. Circus performers have a hard life as i said they eat they dont have a dinner table exactly they eat in the pie car. To answer yur question no its not filled with pies. (trust me I thought the same thing). They cant eat alot because they have a show right after they eat. After their performes they get two days then they are off to another town.                          In the circus the performe alot of different things. It kinda matters who you are on what you do during the performess. Well we are going to take about the tightrope walker. His job is to practice walking on a rope up really high in the air. If that was me i would probly faint. He must really have to work hard so he doesnt fall or mess up. His job as a tightrope walker is very danerous but it does might people show up to watch. That sure can give him a nice pay check for sure.

Item_Response: Mary Rose Babolone                    Do you want to hear about an amazing woman !!! If so read on   Mary is a circus acrobat.  She does lots of shows with her husband Harry. they perform shows all over the countrie. It's really fun to see how many people come to see her and watch the show. Mary swings high up in the air just by a rope. If you dont know what an acrobat is it's someone who can do tricks just by holding someone's hand or by hanging onto a rope. Mary has at least done over 100 shows. Mary and her husband do tricks that are amazing. Mary can hold onto Harry's foot and do a back flip. Her husband can do tricks in the air or off of things. For example he can do flips off an elephants back !! Mary told her husband 'You know circus life isn't so fun.' Item_Response: My Day At The Circus                        Today my mom and I are going to the circus. She bought us backstage passes so we could see all of the animals and performers. I've never been to a circus before but they sound like lots of fun. My dad would have come but he's sick so we sold his ticket, but I still have to tell him what happened.                         It's 6:00 time to go to the circus it started at 6:30 ,but we went early to see the performers getting ready to perform it was really fun watching them get ready because we got to see the animals do a bunch of tricks like a tiger roll over and sit down all on command. Once they were done more people started to show up that's when I realized that wasn't the real show and that was just practice.                        When the real show started I was really excited because the first thing you could see on the stage was a man and a woman swinging through the air doing flips and catching each other in mid air.then under them were two clowns riding on the backs of two enormous elephants. Then a man on stilts walked right through the space in-between both elephants then a man riding horseback did a cartwheel on the horses back while the horse was running. Then all of the performers went backstage then the stage was empty, but that wasn't the end even though I thought it was it wasn't because a man with a lion came out and then another man with a tiger then they both started jumping through hoops and sitting and rolling over then they left too it was over.                         Then we went backstage and met all of the performers even though most of them didn't speak English it was still fun i even got to feed and pet a lion. When my mom told me we had to go I didn't want to, but I knew we had to get home before it got to late so I left. When we got home I told my dad everything we did then went to bed so I could dream about it.

When he arrived men and woman fled inside the tent so did the young boy. Inside his eyes lit up, a circus! 'ooss' and 'aaghs.' Filled the whole tent, as a man walked across a tightrope while balancing an umbrella on his nose.  After hordes of performances it began to get dark. The boy began to run home. Just then he ran into a big muscular man with narrow eyes and a rather large mustache. He picked up the boy and with a gruff voice said 'Watt'ar-ya doin' ramm'n intu' peoples like d'at?' He dropped the boy and the man paced off. On the long walk home he could still hear the croud cheering. What a

Item_Response: 'Ahhhh!' a scream came from the tent.  I rushed over to see what happened.  I really hoped it was not somebody from an important act, or anybody.  Everyone in the circus is like a family to me and I would really hate to see them go away.  I ran like the wind over to the tent, my feet were a blur.                 I am the fastest runner in the circus that is why I do my special act.  I practice everyday to perfect my skills.  My act is I run as fast as I can and then jump onto a swing and do a flip over the fulcrum.  I love seeing the kids faces once I finish because over my experience as a kid I know that kids love fast runners, and people who do flips.  They LOVE seeing someone go head over heels.  I think I have the best act in the circus because I please the kids.  Also I love doing my job.  I love to run and do flips.  Every performer feels that way about their act because they love to do it.  You are not a true performer if you do not like to do what you do.                I sped past the animal stalls and my horse named bullzeye, named after my lacrosse stick that I will never forget, whinnied and I replied 'Not now bullzeye I have to get to this accident.  Here have an apple.'  I grabbed an apple from my backpack and threw it to him quickly.  Something else fell out of my pocket and hit my ankle but I kept running.  Bullzeye is my partner in 2 acts : jumping on a trampoline then doing a flip and jumping on a trampoline then landing on him.  The second one takes a lot of balance and concentration.                I burst into the tent and saw a small crowd huddled around someone.  I ran over to him and asked what happened.  He replied 'I was on my unicycle and then I fell and hit the rack of knives.  It was the clown.  My best friend, he was like a father to me.                I, Bill Gasten, am 23 and just graduated college.  People call me Billy.  My parents worked here until a fatal car accident during the off-season when I was 6.  Instead of going to an orphanage I insisted on staying with the circus.  I really wanted to stay and travel the world and meet new people.  Right now we are in Japan.  The clown, Ron Smith, acted as a father to me.  He is in his later years and had no kids or wife.  I really hoped he was not a goner, he was all I had.             A bunch more people came to look.  'Ha-ha, I got you good' Ron said.  Nobody laughed.  'Ron its not funny, you really scared us.' the manager said.  'Yeah' I added 'Its not funny'.   'All right everybody go back to work, the red stuff on the floor is ketchup mixed with water and red food coloring.' Ron said.  'What, Ron?  Tonight is hot dog night and you know I need a lot of ketchup on my hot dog.'  I said.  He must have stolen it from the pie car I thought.  'Actually, I found this over here' Ron said as if reading my mind.  Everybody walked away. The manager shook his head in disgust as he stormed into his office mad that he had to be interrupted reading his emails.             I went back to practice and had a regular day.                   'C'mon fast get everything ready, Billy' someone yelled at me.  I could not find my special safety hook for tonights performance.  Somehow it had fell out of my pocket.  It was hand made for me when I was young and it had my parents names on it with mine.  I needed it. I just could not remember where I had put it.  I had it in my pocket before school but it is nowhere to be seen now.  I had searched everywhere - even in the bathroom and I could not find it.  Good thing I only needed the hook for the last act that I had so maybe I could find it on the stage during one of my other acts.   'And now, we have our very own... Billy Gasten!' I heard being announced.  I got my things and hurried out onto the stage.                 The crowd roared and I waved to everyone.  Then the music started to play.  I waited for my cue.  Bullzeye charged out of the curtains and towards me.  I pretended to be scared and this was not supposed to happen and once bullzeye got close enough I jumped up and onto his back the did a front flip off.  We had practiced this many times and the crowd loved it.  I pretended to wipe sweat off my forehead just exaggerating a lot and actually I did wipe some sweat off my forehead.  Bullzeye turned and charged again.  This time he jumped up and I slid under him.  I noticed a glint in his teeth.  Wow I though, the dentists have been doing a good job.  We did that a few times until the music ended.                 Then the curtains closed and I hurried to find the hook.  I ran out and looked again.  I went over to the stalls first because I had been there for a while today after practice.  I found an imprint of the hook in the grass by bullzeye's stall.  Somebody had picked it up, but who?  The I realized that was what had hit my ankle when I ran to Ron.               I checked my watch and it read 7:03.  Time for my second act because it took about 5 minutes for the stage crew to clean up.              I hurried back to the tent and got to the stage in my position.  Bullzeye and I did our act.  Again I noticed a glint in bullzeye's teeth, but I thought it was only the golden tooth in the back of bullzeye's mouth.   After I realized that it was hopeless, I would never get the hook in time unless there was a miracle.                Time for the hook act.  I waited 5 minutes and then when I was about to go out when bullzeye nudged me.  I turned and said 'Not now, bullzeye'.  I turned back and started out the door but bullzeye kicked me lightly with his foot.  I turned back and looked at bullzeye in an annoyed way. 'Not now bullzeye, I am not in a good mood.' I said in an angry tone.  Bullzeye spit something from its mouth.  I looked down at the gooey thing on the ground.  I gasped.  'Thank you bullzeye, you are the best' I said happily.  I picked the object up and wiped the saliva off.  'To Billy' it read 'From mom and dad'.  The metal with wood reflected all the fun moments I had with my parents.  I ran out onto the stage ready to do anything.                  When the crowd quieted down I announced 'Everybody, there will be one change in the show tonight.  Give us 5 minutes and we will be ready again.  I walked back and pulled the curtains shut.  I called to the stage crew and told them specific orders.  'Get the swing fulcrum raised 20 feet without changing the length of the rope and put the trampoline near it.  Get this done in five minutes.'  Nobody objected and they all hurried off to get the tools required.                                   Life for a circus man is always challenging.                                   I went over to bullzeye.  'All right bud, we are changing the plans.' I said aloud and whispered the rest to him so it would be a suprize for everybody.   I placed something on his neck and left.  I gathered everyone up next 'Everybody there has been a change of plans.  You might want to go out to the bleachers and watch this.'  I informed.  Everyone did as told.  I stretched my body out to get ready.                    Bullzeye came over to me and we walked onto the stage.  Everything was in place.  The curtains opened, the music started to play.  I hopped on bullzeye and we set off.  You know how I said I was the fastest in the company, well, correction, Bullzeye is the fastest in the company.  We ran like the wind to the trampoline and as we got 5 feet away I yelled 'JUMP!'  Bullzeye jumped and landed perfectly in the center of the trampoline.  We flew diagonally upwards and I closed my eyes and thought.                   Why did I use bullzeye, if we fall we both die.  Bullzeye does not deserve to die.  I said firmly to myself.  Then I thought back.  I remember the time bullzeye was born and my parents said he could be mine.  I remember the dinner before my parents drove away to a place I am not going to now.                  I opened my eyes and looked into the crowd and saw everybody watch in amazement.  I was born to amaze.  And bullzeye was born to amaze,                                                        and be on target.                       Click.                       The hook got on the swing.                      The crowd roared.

Item_Response: Circus Performing               You first have to get up at 7:00 am.Then you have to get dress and go to the pie car. 9:00 am If you are a child under 18 it is school time in a one room school house. They sometimes speak French,Russian,and Italian. 3:00 pm School is over and we can play around. 3:00 pm You have to do chores and the circus performers are praticing for the show. 6:30 pm It is dinner time and you have to go to the pie car.10:00 pm Show is over you have to walk back to the trailer.12:00 pm It is time for bed some times you want to go to your real home for an example Florida.               Becoming a Circus Performer some times you run away from home. Getting started is alot of work and practice to be a good show. The upside is you can travel all around the world. It is also very fun to do. The downside is you miss out on friends and family. You can't call home or anyhing like that.           See being a circus performer has some upsides and downsides.It also takes alot of work.And sometimes it can be fun.So,if you want to become a circus entertainer think about it long and hard.

Item_Response: The day is bright and warm and the birds are chirping aloud. There in a house a man hurrying up to drive to the market says to himself 'Alright lets see I need milk, eggs, and a new horn.' His name is Tom Hiller. Tom is an unmarried man who works at a circus and is a clown. As Tom was in the market he met a freind who also worked with him. They met and were saying 'Hi' to each other.Tom was finally leaving and the day was turning to night. So Tom was getting ready for the circus.                                               Tom was putting on the white make-up and some red lipstick around and on his lips. Tom was getting used to the idea of wearing this stuff on at first he felt like a woman with a white face. As he was driving to the circus he stopped for lunch then he got back to driving. He saw a place with a huge tent with the colors of red and white. He put on his suit and got ready to work.                                                    Tom was riding a tiger and a small unicycle. After that Tom went home and took off everything on his face. Item_Response: The Story of a Girl Named Hope           One day a girl named Hope was born into this world.As she grew up and learned to talk,Hope became fascinated with the circus life.By the age of 9 her parents agreed that she could go join the circus.For months she practiced her skills.Hope had wish to be a acrobat.She would do gymnastics for hours a day.Finally the day came when she had to leave her family to join the circus.       As hope boarded the circus train she was greeted by clowns and animal trainers.She walked through the train carts.At last she had reached the acrobats cart.Hope was surprised to see people hanging of the roof and beds.'Hello!' everyone had shouted.She was smiling with joy as she found her bunk.She was bunking with a acrobat from Russia.The Russian girl was 10,only a year older than Hope.'Hi I'm Hope' a silent moment paused between the two girls.'Hi I'm Rachel, I am guessing your the new acrobat?'. Hope nodded her head right then she knew they would be best friends.       The next morning Hope woke up with the rest of the acrobats, at 6:30 A.M.Training started today.Rachel and Hope had been put to work on rope acts.Hope watched Rachel dance between the ropes,back and forth.It was as if Rachel was a professional with the ropes.When Hope got on the ropes, she wasn't to bad for a rookie.Time had flown through the day as Rachel and Hope worked on the ropes.'I like you,your my new best friend,' Rachel had said with a bright smile to Hope.       A few weeks later it had been opening night.It was Hope's first night.Rachel and her watched as the other performers did there act perfectly.All the animals did their act and obeyed their masters/trainers.To Hope the most beautiful act was the horses.They danced and pranced around the ring,coats shining bright in the circus lights.Finally, Hope and Rachel had heard their names being called for their act.'This is it!' yelled Rachel over the noise of the crowd.'Uh i don't know if i can do this' Hope shakes as she says this.They slowly walked towards their acting spot.'The ropes,the ropes' Hope said in her mind.'I can do this!!!' shouted Hope over the noise of the crowd and the animals.As Rachel and Hope got on the ropes the crowd went silent.Each grabbed a rope and the gliding above the crowd went smooth as possible.The crowd yelled and shouted their names.       Once they got back to their bunks everyone congratulated them 'Way to go!' 'Nice job!' 'Hope you guys do that again' all of theses comments came from professionals.'Don't worry we will be doing that again soon' yelled Rachel and Hope from their bunks.'I can't wait for tomorrow' said Hope as she yawned.'Same, good night Hope' 'Good night Rachel'.They both turned on their sides and fell asleep as silence fell over the other bunks in the carts.And that is the wonderful story of Hope and Rachel,her new best friend.

Item_Response: Circus Life           'Neigh', the horse neighed very loudly.  The crowd shrieks at the horse. John the man who is scaring the horse with a fake gun laughs. Its my turn to go in and tell john to stop that. I'm supposed to be his older sister.        I shake my finger at him because we aren't aloud to talk in a circus. He puts his head down like a little boy who couldn't go to his friends house. Then he shakes his head and lets the horse be.  I do a back flip to the horse and the crowd cheers. I pet the horse then we skip off behind the curtains. We have to move very fast.        Soon enough were all out in front of the crowd and holding hands and bowing. Huge smiles are on our faces even though we are extremely tired. Then we skip back behind the curtains and take off all our make up and take our hair out of the amazing design it had.        My hair is a reddish brownish color. People say it is beautiful. I think it is too. I'm only 12 years old and I'm in the circus. My parents travel with me, other wise I'll get a little home sick if there not with me.        I slip on my pajamas and have a bed time snack. An apple. I love apples very much. We can only have healthy snacks so I pick apples. They rock.  I have to get a good nights rest for tomorrow. I have a big day coming up on my heels. Good night!!!!

Item_Response: 'Circus Life'                                                                                                                      by Zoei Bristol                                                                             Hi I'm Harper Waldo and I'm a circus performer. I bet you think that being in a circus means that you can have fun all the time. Well, if you thought that you are wrong. I have to work hard every day practicing skills. I'm always busy.                                                 I go to school with all the other kids in the circus. We only have one classroom, but I'm okay with that. Some of the kids speak  different languages, so I know four languages. I know how to speak French, German, Spanish, and English. After school I have to groom.                                                                                                                                         I have to groom the horses for tonight's big show. I also have to groom a elephant! It is the smallest elephant in the world. Her name is Tiny. It's time to start practicing.                  I am watching my sister, Ella, fly through the air. She is a trapeze artist. It is my turn to practice. I am working with Tiny. I do handstands while she is walking I can hold a handstand for two minutes without falling! I did it perfectly. Yay! Now I'm watching my dad. He's a tightrope walker. He walks on a rope fifty feet in the air. He is so good. Now it's my mom's turn to practice then the show will start. My mom is a circus acrobat. She is so flexible it is unbelievable. We also have a human pretzel and a dancing bear! It took years to train him.                                                                                                                        There is only five minutes until the show starts and I'm getting butterflies. I peek out to see the crowd and I faint. When I wake up I see mom.                                                            'Mom is the show over?'                                                                                                    'No, you woke up just in time to do your act.' I almost scream. I ran to get ready. Then I realized that I was already ready. I got Tiny and walked out to the stage.                        'Ladies and gentlemen for your next act we have Harper Waldo.' I heard the announcer say. I got on Tiny's back and did a handstand for two minutes then I picked up one hand and held it for another two minutes! Then all of the sudden I was swinging through the air with Ella.                                                                                                             After the show we went out side and everyone wanted my autograph. I was so shocked that I said 'Me.' Then the fans said 'Ya, you were awesome.' So I had to sign two hundred pictures.                                                                                                                   So my family went to our trailer and the gave me a huge bear hug.                                     'We're so proud of you.'they all said at once.           'Thank you. Ella I didn't know you were going to do that, but it was pretty cool.' I said.           'I thought I'd give the show a twist. Everyone loved it. I think we should do that for every show.' said Ella.                                                                                                               'So do we.' said mom and dad. So we did that every show and everyone loved it.

Item_Response: Life for a Circus Performer            I, as an acrobat, must work very hard everyday to please the audience. Life as a circus performer can be both hard and fun at the same time. In the mornings I have to wake up early to get dressed and eat breakfast. Then after that I have to start practicing for the night's show. It's not easy for me to do the tricks though. I have to have balance, concentration, and skill. This hard work is very rewarding when the crowd goes wild when I perform my tricks.        The good parts of being a circus performer is great. You get to travel all over the world for circus performances and you can meet new people. To me the best part of all is when you astound the crowd. When you are break you can explore the place that you are at, learn the people who lives there's cultures, and try new food.        The bad part of being a circus performer is when you have to work super hard to perform at performances and basically there are performances at least once everyday from Monday to Sunday. You also have to be far away from your family for a long time. You can't call your family too because you don't have anywhere to call.

Item_Response: The Circus Life                                               By:Kennadi Dykstra        Have you ever been to a circus? It isn't just nonstop play, in the circus you work from sunup to sundown. Busy right?        Lets see what a typical day looks like for Bella Castini: 7:00 Wake up, get dressed, go to the pie cart to eat, 9:00 school time, 3:00 school's over---time for a quick break, 3:30 chores and practice, 6:30 dinnertime,7:00 SHOWTIME 10:30 the show is over and finally I am in bed at 12:00.        There are some upsides of being a circus performers you know like you get to travel all over the world and you get to preform in front of a live audience every time you preform endless people are watching on a TV. I think the upsides are kind of cool.        In the circus there are some downsides too like circus performers work long and tiring days and they send ALONG TIME away from home (i think they get home sick a lot.)I don't think that sounds very fun.        But  before you get to do all this you need to know a few things, first: not just anyone can join the circus you need to have the right body type, second: have a specific talent for some it is Circus acrobats for others it is a juggler and for some it is tightrope walking        Some of the words I used you might not under stand like:   pie car: where circus performers,   unicycle: a bike with only one wheel,   groom: clean and brush,   matinee: afternoon show, and   wiped out: very tired, those were circus terms so unless you want to be a circus performer or you are a circus performer you don't have to know those terms unless you want to. Item_Response: The Uninvited Performer                       We were all so excited when we figured out we were going to the circus! Everybody was going crazy! Some people wanted to see the elephants, some the clowns, and some the Trapeze artists. When we were lining up to get on the bus, i was thinking. This is my first time going to circus. It felt like forever getting there, but when we saw that big red tent when knew we were there.                  After we got our snacks we got our seats. I had probably about three slushies! So now i really had to go to the bathroom. So I went and asked my teacher , Mrs. Johnson, if i could go. I had to hurry because it was getting ready to start.                  When I was looking for a bathroom i got lost. I found a door that I thought led to the bathroom but then I saw all these bright lights! ' where am I? ' I asked my self. A huge elephant passed by me, then a clown! Then I knew where I was. Backstage where the performers stand before they go on stage! A tall man with a mustache came up to me and asked, 'why aren't you changed yet!! We go out in 5 minutes! ' He handedd me a colorful sparkly costume to wear. So i went back and changed and it fit! Did you know how fast circus people can do your makeup and hair. It's crazy! I looked in the mirror and said to myself, 'wow! I look good! '                   Then , I thought, Mrs.Johnson is probably looking for me! She doesn't know that im going to be in the circus. Now, im in big trouble.                     The 5 minutes went by and i was on the stage. People were screaming and those lights were really bright! I was looking for the class and Mrs.Johnson but couldn't find them. I had no idea what i was so supposed to do until i looked up and so people on these ropes doing tricks, hanging upside down. I thought, don't tell me I have to do that! Then that man with the mustache was telling me with his hands to go on that empty rope.                       Here we go. They pulled the rope higher and higher! It was like I was flying! I was doing flips, twirling all sorts of stuff. It was so exciting! Then our act was over. We waited until everybody was done then we went out and bowed. People were screaming as loud as they could! It felt great.                       After the bow I had to go change and find my class quick! I finally found them. I was going up the stairs to my seat and they were going down the stairs. Mrs.Johnson wasn't that mad. All my classmates were saying how good I was and how it was like to be in the circus.                       I never thought I would do it but I did. I was in the circus!

Item_Response: Life at the circus is pretty hard.  I have to get up early in the morning and do lots of stuff such as going around the world almost everyday. My schedules are so not necessary. All I do every day is just go around the world and do crazy things that doesn't really matter in life. I'm in Europe getting ready to perform the most crazy and not necessary things and the only human beings the only likes it are mostly kids. The grownups just thinks that it is just fake things that we do and its not the exciting to them as its exciting to the kids them selves. So what i think is what the circus clowns should do is just retire and find a job at a fast food restaurant like McDonald's. People are so UN-grateful these days with entertainment and food. Sometimes I just think of myself as an old dumb,stupid circus clown that just belongs in the circus and needs to stay.   Today I have to walk on a tight rope and ride on a lion with fire on it.  I'm going on now I'll be right back. I'm back that was a show. I stand myself corrected because i seen a lot of adults excited and enjoying the show. So i guess its just some adults who just aren't into those circus things. When i was out there I had so much fun and I was happy that almost everyone was cheering for our circus. The tight rope was really hard but i concentrated and did the best i could do and i didn't fall. The lion was a wild one but i rode on it and i was scared because i thought the lion was going to try to eat me but the lion was tamed and it learned not to eat people.  Today at the circus was really good if the circus keeps going like this i would stay here until the day I die.  Im super tired of all the things we did its time for me to go to sleep. Good night.   Good morning. I just found out the i graduated from the circus and im going back to California. Im super happy. I think yesterday was meant to happen. Im super happy to be going home but imsad becasue im not being in the curcus anymore. I have to say goodbye to everybodty and thank them for all they did to help me be in this circus.   Im back home in Calfornia. I really miss getting up early in the morning and travling places. But im happy to be back home.

Item_Response: The day of a circus performer            The day of a circus performer is not a simple thing it is a hard working day.   During the day you have school, chores, breakfast, lunch, dinner, and practicing your circus talent. Your day starts about 6:00 and ends at 12:00 this is how your day would go if you were a circus performer.              6:00 wake up and get ready     In the morning I wake up, and go to the pie car with my family we eat a big breakfast to get lots of energy, and we talk a little. Its usually a slow start for me in the morning because i don't want to use all my energy.         2.     8:00 time for school!   After breakfast i go to a one room school house it has many people in it i learn the same stuff every other kid does. I have test, essays, and i get a report card. There are many other people in the school house, and they speak many other languages like French, Russian, and Italian.         3.     2:00 time for a quick break    On break you can play with unicycles and juggling balls. You live in trailers and u cant have big animals because if their to big then you will have no room in your trailer.        4.      2:30 Chores and practice   I do my chores i have to take care of the horses that we use in horseback acts. I am trying to do some more tricks with animals and its working out very good.        5.       5:30 Time to EAT!   At dinner time me and my family go to the pie cart, we don't eat much because we don't want to get sick wile performing.        6.       9:30 time to sleep   The show is over I am tired and sleepy no more work for today its not time for me, and my family to go to sleep.                                         This is the life of a circus performer.

Item_Response: TAKING CARE OF CIRCUS HORSES                          My name is Julia and I am 15. My Dad owns a circus and I am a big help with the horses. I help put them in thier trailers when we travel on the road, and I brush and groom them. I also train them to do very cool tricks for the shows!                     Usually, I wake up around 7:00 A.M. When I get dressed, grab some breakfast from the pie car, and go to horses while everyone sets up tents, lights, etc. By 8:30 I've fed all the horses, and now it's time to go brush my teeth and hair. At 9:00 school starts, and I am very excited to get back to the horses. Finally school's over by around 3:00. I get to the horses, and begin cleaning them up. I first fill up all their water buckets, though. I then start brushing them with a more stiff brush, and next move on to a soft brush that shines their fur a bit. I finish by putting some fly spray on them.                  I take a break from the horses, and complete some homework and chores. I make my small bed and make myself a little snack. While I eat, I review with myself the steps of my horseback act. Then I stop by my friends bed.'Hey Jenna!' I say. 'Want to come help me with the horses?' 'Sorry, I can't right now, I've got to practice my quadrupel back hand spring. But I'll stop by later!' She says. So I get my helmet and boots, then tell my dad to meet me in 5 minutes by the riding area, and head down.                         Once we're both ready to practice,I put a big, white, square pad on my horse Lily, a snow white horse, with long eye lashes, and a white mane and tail, then I slip on her bridle, and hop on. 'Okay, lets warm up with a hand stand with Lily standing still.' My dad says. I do it fine, then for about a half hour practice my back flip off her and landing it on the ground perfectly.                        At 6:30, we eat a small dinner, because we have a show. The makeup and hair artists apply sparkly makeup, and bright lipstick. I wait about a half hour before my part comes in. I walk out on Lily and I stand up on her. I stay determined and confident, something I will always need to do here. Then I slowly swing my and back... And PUSH OFF! I curve my body back like a rainbow, then I slowly bend my knees as I land. The crowd goes wild. Every time I do this, I always smile big. Then do it again but with a double back flip. If I thought they were cheering before, well they were screaming this time! I smiled at everyone, and then walked out, the noise fading.                        I was wiped out, I put Lily back, took of her saddle pad, and headed 'home'.   I put my two piece rainbow pajamas on, and waited for my dad to come home. i finished my homework, then put it in my backpack, to go to school in the morning. When i returned to the small table in our trailer cabins living room, my dad came in. 'Who wants hot coacoa!?' he asked as he set down four cups for all the girls staying in the trailer we all gathered aroud the cups, grabbed on and sat down slurping our hot chocolate. Then we all crawled into bed, falling asleep right away.                   Every morning I go through the same routine. I never get tired of being with horses all day. When we are done at one destination, we drive to another, and always have a blast att the shows. I am so glad to have such a cool life. I get get to meet kids all around the world! And make new friens, every year.

Item_Response: Sally has been in the circus for three. She was very excited about  joining the circus and still is. She woke up at 7:00 a.m. got dressed and went to school there are 12 other kids that go to school some seek French others Russian but Sally she spoke English. School in the circus was like any other school it had desks and testes. After school she ate lunch at the pie car had a little break then did some chores( feeding the horses and brushing them). Dinnertime she could not eat a lot of food because of the show. The show was always fun being on stage and after seeing the people and telling us what a great job we did. In bed she thinks about home and counting the dyes until she gets to go home life in the circus was fun but at the same time sad.            A few months later Sally found out the next stop was her home town she could not wate to see her friends. When she got up the next morning she was in her home town, she jested wanted to run to her home but she knew she could not. At school she did not treat it as a normal day she rushed through about every thing she did that day her friends tried to slow her down but she was to excited.            That night she saw some of her friends and there family. After the show her mother said she can go with hang out with her friends. They had so much to say but they knew they did not have long so the talked and talked until there mothers called them away. sally was in bed thinking about how much things her friends and she would do when she is off tour.               Before she knew it it was time to go back home. Right when she got home she called her friends. As they did before they talked until they could not. they hung out all summer until Sally had to go on tour again. That was the best summer she had ever sean.

Item_Response: A DAY AT THE CIRCUS                                                BY: BRYAN G.R            You might think that the circus is a rampage in side,but it isn't.I Leon S.Kenndy,know difrently.I live in a huge treailer with my companianes.They travel day and night.We travel 20,000miles in seven months.They visit over 150 cities.We work day and night.From sun up to sun down.                   *Hear's my terrifing day*         6:30 a.m.I wake up,get breakfast from the pie car.I eat bacon and eggs.I go see the crue and set up tents for to nights show. 8:26 a.m.It's school time for me.I take out all my homework.School time is the same thing like a regular school.You have tests computers and even homework.Must of our circus performers are from all over the world so many of them speak other languages like French,Russian,and Mexican.The more we learn we improve. 2:16 p.m.House chores and practice.I feed,groom,water the horses that we use our horseback acts.My mom practices on leaping from trampoline onto the horse's back.Other kids are practicing acrobatics and juggling.A lady is walking panthers,and trainers are training chimpanzees,lamas,lions. 5:31 p.m Dinnertime.My companiens and I go eat at the pie car,but we don't eat much because we have to perform tonight.We do 10 shows a week,one each weekday,plus a afternoon show. 11:26 p.m.The show is over. I'm pooped.Walking back to our trailer,we pass the circus offices.Two days from now ,we're back to our home town. 1:00 a.m. Im in bed.I think that what on earth did I do.It would be nice to go back home to Racoon city.When I grow up do I still want to be a circus performer.Who even knows.The circus might be fun,buts a torcher.It's a tough life to put on with.

Item_Response: One day I was at the circus. When it was over, I went backstage and suddenly the animals started talking. I was about to run but the lion started talking to me. The lion said, they were friendly and they didn't want to harm me. They told me that they wanted to leave and not perform tricks. I told them that if they left, then  people will be sad. They decided not to leave. The next day the animals were not there everyone was sad. The next day people didn't go to the circus because they wanted the animals performing. The owner saw the animals gone and he called the animal control to try and find the animals . The owner didn't even care about the animals he only cared about the money. I tried to tell them that they just want to live in the wild and not in the circus. The owner just ignored me.                  Secondly, the animal control found the animals and now they are back in the circus. I felt bad because they told me they wanted to live in the wild and not in the circus. When the circus was done I went backstage and I saw the animals. They told me that their dream is to stay in the circus. I told them that they said they wanted to be in the wild. They said they changed their mind because in the wild they are not proud. In the circus they are proud, lots of people are watching them and smiling. I just thought they wanted to be in the wild. So, the animals did really wanted to live in the wild . The next day the animals were in the circus preforming and having fun.

Item_Response: THE CIRCUS                                by:Finn         One wet and soggy night I was on my to the big tent when I heard a noise coming from the animal pens it was like the scream of a man! I rushed over to the animal pens and the sight I saw was horrifying. The ringmasters body lay mangled on the ground I quickly called for help but no buddy   came 'DANG!' the circus must of started. so as quick as possible I hid the body and put on the cloths.It was good that I did because at that second one of the clowns came in,'Boss we need you on. NOW!' I was hustled out onto the stage I did my best acting,'Lady's and Gents the moment you've all been waiting for,,,,,TIPSY TURVY CIRCUS!!! '. I hope that was right and by Davy Jones it was!   The clowns came out in their funny car and stopped right in the middle the door slowly opened then,,,,,,,a whole bunch of clowns came out i was laughing so hard my sides felt like they were going to split open, but wait one of them had some hesitation in what he was doing. Oh well I disided to keep watching and see if anything else was weird. The show continued on with nothing weird but the fire breathing, when I could of sworn he tried to toast a man or it was just me.Finally the circus was over I was so happy to have the circus over that forgot about the body. 'AAAAAAAAAHHHHHHHHHHH' their was a young woman at the body of the ring master. She looked at me then at the body  she was speechless. As quick as a flash I calmed her down and told her everything. She looked puzzled but then she seemed to get it. 'My name is Joan I'm the ring masters helper once I knew you said tipsy not Topsy I knew something was wrong so I tried to find the real ring master but all I found was a mangled body.' So me and Joan hunted for hours on end for the murderer but we found nothing we were about to give up when I saw the man that tried to toast the other man 'AH HA' we followed him to his tent 1,,,2,,,3,,, we ran in and caught the man red handed!   later that evening the police came and took him away 'Thanks to you folks we'll put this man behind bars again.

Item_Response: Life in the circus           To Cassidy Knoll, Life in the circus is very hard, but what she loves to do most. Here is      her story.                    Hello, My name is Cassidy Knoll. 4 years ago I joined the amazing life as an acrobat in the circus. My talent kind of runs in my family. I always have been proud of my family and how I live my life. Alot of people dont have the opportunities I do in life and so that makes me feel special about who I am. My entire family has these amazing talents and we are all very lucky!                The bad part about being in the circus is that you are never in one place long enough to make any friends or anything like that. I enjoy making new friends and because I cant stay long enough to really make any, it isn't very good. We also dont hae many chances to really get to stay at our real house. We are always traveling. Which actually isn't a bad thing.          We get up really early in the morning to go to our one-room school. But, before we do that, we have to head to our pie car, were we eat. I enjoy getting to see all the different places while we are on tour and I have alot of storys to share to people I know who aren't in the circus buissiness. I am sure that anyone who isn't in the circus would love it! But also find it very tough.         I also suggest reaching for your dreams. What do you want to be? Go for it. If you think you have what it takes, you should definently try to be who you want to be. Don't let anyone change your mind!

Item_Response: I've been to a circus so I know what happens at one. I will write a paragraph about each thing I saw at the circus. I will be writing about the color of a circus, acrobats, circus jugglers, tightrope walkers,and circus horses.        The circus I went to was painted red and white. The circus was only in town for two weeks. It was carried in by trailers. They had lots of plays to watch and some rides.         I saw people on strings doing acrobats. They were really high up in the air. They were also twisting so much I thought they were going to  fall on to the audience. They were grabbing the rope with their hands, their feet, and even their teeth.       I also saw people juggling sharp wooden sticks. I have no idea how their hands were moving so fast. The sticks were so sharp if they messed up the sticks would have injured them badly. I got really scared when one of the sticks went flying through the air. It might have been part of the act, it might not have been part of the act.I will probably never know.         The next thing I saw was three tightrope walkers. They were even higher up then the people doing acrobats. The ropes were so thin it looked like he was floating. I wonder how the tightrope walkers got so much balance. I think the tightrope walkers got their balance by walking on brick walls. Maybe even just walking on the side of a curb.         The best thing was the circus horses. They were standing on their hind legs, and jumping very high. They were also catching apples in their mouth. the circus horses even did exactly what their masters told them to do.   `      This is what happens in a circus if you are interested in going to one anytime soon.

Item_Response: There once was a circus girl, who lived with her father in a circus because her mother had died when she was very young.            The circus girl loved the circus, it was all she could think about. She wished that one day she would be as good as Dougie, her favorite acrobat. Dougie looked as beautiful as a supermodel when she performed. She was as graceful as a swan. She had such elegance that you couldn't take your eyes off her. She was MESMERIZING!             She worked day after day practicing Dougie's every move, making sure every little movement was perfect. She would work from dawn to dust, giving everything she had to the moves. Intill she had almost every move down, there was just one more left, the hardest one of all, the Falcon.             The circus girl worked on it for years, she just couldn't get it. She sometimes never went home at night. She wanted to be Dougie so much for so long that she just couldn't give up. She evenally she got so angry with it she went home and just cried in her father arms screming, ' I can't do it!!! I CAN'T DO IT!!! I'll never be like Dougie!!!!!' Her father coforted her all night in she finally stoped crying.            Then he said, ' But your not Dougie your The Circus Girl!!!' and then she reizied that he was right, she wasn't Dougie, she was THE CIRCUS GIRL!!!!!!                                 THE END!!!

Item_Response: forien smiles              I wake up in the morning and watch the suns light hit my car.  Today was the big day.   All our practice in acrobatics  will finally come to use.  My name is  Bella Lindini.  Otherwise know to the croud 'The Beauty of Italy ' I work in an Italian traveling circus with my parents.  I am 11 years old . Today we were going to do the biggest show we had ever put on in my life time.  I had never done this big of an act.  Today we were going to go to america. I had never been to america in my life though my parents had been many times.  I started getting dressed slowly in to my outfit for the show we had practiced many times for this show.  we were performing in Los Angeles, California.  It was not at all like home. There were no forests just palm trees every where to be seen. there were no big neighborhoods just streets and big glass buildings.  The time change really got to me but I had been traveling in america for 6 months so i had gotten used to it.         I got out of the car and went down to the pie car for some pasta with sauce.  ' well you are up earily' said my mother behind me.  'Hello mama' i said. I could hear the tiredness in my voice.  I saw my mother was tired to.        I finished my pasta and went down to the big top to pracitice my act. I did my flips onto the trapize and shaped my self into God knows what.  flipped myself off landed in the net bowed and jumped off.  I had anthor act to but i needed my partner who was not awake or was still at the pie car so I practiced that again. When I finished I turned to the floor and saw my partner. Item_Response: The Amazing Circus                                                                                        I wake up in the morning at 7:00 A.M. and get dressed and I walk all the way to the pie car to eat pancakes and delicious bacon. I walk outside after eating and all the crews are setting up the tents, lights, and music for tonight's show.       9:00 A.M. is school time. Our schoolhouse travels with us. Like any other school ours has computers, tests, and report cards with grades. Because many of the performers are from all different places in the world many of my classmates speak different languages:French, Russian, and Italian like my family. As we travel around the different states in the country our geography becomes more and more alive.                After those we have to do many,many more things throughout the hole entire rest of the day. After I groom my dog, feed, water, and groom the horses we use in our acts we take a break. The clowns let me play with their unicycles and and juggling balls. After all the rest of the jobs are done we get dressed and ready for tonight's show. After the show is over we all eat dinner then go to bed excited for tomorrow's show.

Item_Response: Hi my name is Ron and this is my life as a juggler in the circus. I was 4 years old when i started my life as a juggler.  For my birthday I got a juggling set and I was off juggling.  By the time I was 8 I was already juggling knifes.  One day I saw a sign on the door of a pub, new employees for the circus.  It said March 24, 2:00 at my local amusement park, Magic Mountain.  I told my mom and on that day she took me.  I performed last so I had a lot of pressure.  I went home very nervous and weeks later I got a letter that said I got the part.         I had met all my performers that I would be working with and they told me I came right in time.  They said that we have a circus in a month.  I said great lets get practicing.  We had practiced and practiced until it was a week before. We had to drive to Maine so we needed to get going.  We got to Mine and got some sleep.  The next day was the performance.  We practiced all day until it was time for the show.         We got to the theatre.  I was so nervous that I would mess up because it was my first show. The host announced now performing Ron Gooding.  It was gonna be my first time juggling with knifes on fire.  I got out there and the music started.  I started juggling.  I then walked on top of the tight rope and started walking on it and juggling the knifes.  But then I fell.  Luckily there was a net but the knife went in to my eye.       I got rushed to the hospital but it was to lated the docter had told me that i needed a glass eye.

Item_Response: My name is Lucas and I joined the circus 5 years ago. It is very hard work. I have been working all day preparing for the show. First I ate breakfast, then I had to feed the animals, and then I had to practice.        It's almost time for the show to start and we have been practicing for the past 2 hours. I will be doing a trapeze act. The announcer is getting ready to say my name. 'Now, for our trapeze act!' I step out and start to climb the ladder. At the top start to feel nervous.   I feel like I'm going to fall. I grab my swing. My partner grabs theirs and we both jump. I did a flip and my partner grabbed me. The crowd is cheering when we get to the other side!        After the show my parents come and congradulate me. After a long days work I go to the pie car for dinner. Back at my car I get ready for bed. I think about today's show and feel happy. But tomorrow I'll have to do it all again.

Item_Response: The life of the circus is a lot of fun, but is also a lot of hard work. They have to wake up at 7:00 and go eat breakfast then if your a kid you have to go to school from 9:00 to 3:00 Then you have to get ready for the show and eat dinner then you perform. The circus is very tiring because you have wake up early and you don't go to bed till around 12:00 but it is also a lot of fun because you get to travel the world and go to so many amazing places.You also get to meet so many people.                 There are so many things about the circus that really cool but in order to do those cool things you have to work hard to join the circus. You have to be determined, you have to now you want to be in the circus. You also have to study hard to get into the circus but not like study in school, you have to study acting and do a bunch of performances when your a kid. You also have to be funny and not be scared in front of hundreds of people. Item_Response: 'Ready.Set.Go!' Yelled my trainer. You see, I am a trapeze artist who is practicing for the big show tonight. I work hard for every show to make sure I do it just right. As I am back stage practicing my act, I can see all of the other circus performers practicing their act. Being in the circus is fun, but it's lots of hard work. You always need to practice, know what you're doing, and you have to have a certain talent. You can't just learn it! So, if you keep on reading you'll find out I what mean.                      When you are practicing you have to know what your doing and how you are going to perform it. Are you going to  have a partner? Or are you doing a solo act? These may soud like easy questions but when you're a circus performer these are very inportant questions. Then when you have it figured out you have to practice for hours a day. You have to keep going over and over and over your routine until you know it's perfect. Then when you are positive you're ready you wait until the everyone else ready then you put on the show.                  Now that you know what it means to practice for the show, let's talk about the fun part. As soon as you step foot on stage you get this amazing feeling inside. It's definitely a rush! You see all of those cheerful faces in the fantastic audience and you know they're all watching you and know you'll put on a great show. You want to have a great show too. But in order to do that you have to remember every step of your act. You are for going to feel nervous but then the music starts and when you do the first move of your act it comes to naturally and are no longer nervous about doing it. In fact you feel like your just at home messing around with equipment. You hardly notice the crowd. but when you finish your act, you see all the smiles and you put a smile on your face, take a bow, and make room for the next performer.              Now that you've heard about the hard work and the fun it's about time you know the schedule. At 8:00.a.m. you go the pie car. That's where all of us circus performers eat. At around 9:00 we head over to the circus arena. We all practice there until about 12:00. Soon after that we put on our costumes, get hair and make-up done, then practice some more until it's our turn to go up. Soon after we put on new costumes and give the crowd a grand finally. After the show is over we wait until  the next show and are to do it all over again.                  So that's what's it like to be a circus performer. It's lot's of hard work but it all pays off in the end. Lot's of people may think it's we just figure it out and have fun with it but it's not. Even professionals need training. So next time you go see a circus think about how hard they worked to make it perfect. Then ask yourself this question,'Do I really want to become a circus performer?'

Item_Response: People who think life in a circus is awsome and fun well your right but this is how much you need to do in order to become a real  circus member. You have to get up bright and early to get dressed and go to the pie car for pancakes and bacon while the others set up the tents,lights,and music for tonights show.Then the kids go to school.Our one-room schoolhouse travels with us. Like any other school, ours has computers,tests,and report cards and because some circus preformers are from all over the world many of them speak other languages: French, Russian,and Italian.After school is over it's time for a quick break. The clowns let us play with their unicycles and juggling balls.Also we play with a tiny dog its name is Noodle.Saddly our trailer is too small for such a big dog.Next we do chores and practice for tonights show

Item_Response: The Circus Surprise                My parents left me a farmers market when I was two. I had no where to go I kept calling for them, but they would never come. Then the unspeakable happened, Some one found me! He nursed me to a three year old baby, then he explained to me the way I was saved and told me his name(Voric Oglar). As I got older Voric noticed my muscles starting to grow. By the time I was eight I could lift a horse.               Then Voric mentioned the circus, I knew what it was because my old parents used to work their. I said I would love to go to the circus, so we did. When we got their I saw tall people, short people, hairy people, and magic people. We got to the end of the line to sign up, and he said,'State you talent and your name'. I said my talent is strength, and my name is George Wringling. The man stopped and said,'hold on just a little bit' and left the booth and entered the circus tent.               The man from the booth came back and said,'George meet Mr. and Mrs. Wringling.   Then everything went silent so quiet you could hear a pin drop a pin in confusion, and hatered all circling around that one day they left me. Then it went back to normal. 'We're sorry', the Wringling's said. 'Their's nothing to be sorry about. You left me that day I don't know why but you did, and you can't be forgiven,' I said.              'We can explain', they said. It all started the day at that farmers market. We put you in your baby stroller. Before we left, you fell out, but we didn't know you did until we left and got back to our tent. We came back as soon as possible but then you were gone. 'I guess it's resolved then,' I said. 'Now we're a family,' The Wringlings said? 'Now we're a family,'I said!

Item_Response: There was a boy named Timmy Bottomburn. He was a 10 year old boy his height was 4 feet. He  was a rather small child. Bullies mostly targeted him. He went to Hawthorne Elementary school In San Luis Obispo,CA. His school went up to kindergarten through 7th grade. Timmy was in the 5th grade he mostly got bullied by the 6th and 7th graders. The kids in his class always picked him last to be on there team in P.E. And most of the kids  made fun of his last name. They called him Butt burn and worst names like buttsnifer. Timmy usually ignored these dreadful names and thought about his dream which is being a magician in a circus. So Timmy was walking home one night and he saw a poster that said LITTLE MAGICIANS NOW HIRING. Timmy was happy to see this poster, he already new a lot of magic tricks. He had a lot of magic kits and he watched videos on YouTube on how to do magic tricks all the time. So the next day Timmy's parents drove him to the performing arts center. There they signed a lot of papers.             A couple hours after that Timmy's parents packed his bags and they left. 'Bye honey' his mom said. 'Bye son his dad said.  Timmy was starting  To Feel a little homesick now that his parents were gone and he was with some of the administrators on a private jet. When the plane landed, the administrators guided him to a Funny looking trailor with a couple of other kids. When he walked in the administrator greeted Timmy to the kids he said, 'Hey kids this is our new magician  ,Timmy bottomburn. Everyone lafted . Timmy was feeling sad about his weird name. He thought, 'why did my stupid parents name me this'.In about a couple of minutes  everyone stoped lafting. Then everyone told him that they were sorry for laffing. It turns that they have wierd names to. There were 2 girls and 2 boys. There names were Sally pukeeater, wendy Slimeball, Jhonn Bighead and Amari blood face. A few Days past and next thing you they were h   is best friends. They Would always practice their magic tricks together.              The next day they were performing in of 700,000 people at the staples center in L.A. Timmy was happy, he had performed the (Saw the lady in half trick). The crowd roared so much that it sounded like  12,000,000 freight trains roaring through. The administrators cheered too and everyone was happy                     THE END

Red was very sad, everyone was sad. So Red went home and took a very long nap and dreamed of the disaster. Then he woke up and herd a knock on the door so he opened it and it was the directer. Item_Response: Circus Life                          Jane and I walked  down the sidewalk when something caught my eye. It was a Circus banner being pasted on a brick wall by a youge boy, the poster had two elephants and a person on each one then a clown was trying to get on to one of the elephants. '' Circus To-Day'' I read aloud, Jane had an excited look on her face '' We should go.'' '' After all we just got done with school, we could go ask our parents on the way.''I looked at her, not saying a word because she was the onlt one in the whole shcool who knew that I wanted to be in the Circus. She said it would be a good job for me. So the time we got home our parents already put us on the list to go to the Circus.                            ''We won't be able to go to the Cicus so you will have to take care of Jane while you are there'', ''okay Bill''. Bill was my great grandfathers name so I thought she got my name from him. Jane started to pout about going with me instead of going alone. Jane is 10 and I am 12 she says since she is almost as old as me she should go alone. Dad lay on the chair yet awaken be the sound of her pouting.'' You won't go anyhwere if you don't stpo pouting''. He said in a earitated voice.                               ''Bill is  your older brother and you should respect that''. Mom said. As we went to go to the Cicus we were very queit untill we were on a bathroom brake.When we got back in to the car we were tired so we took a nap, by the time we got there we were so excited that we could hardly wait to go inside. While we were inside I bought us some pop and popcorn for the show. When we were there Jane was talking the whole show but then it was the grande fanally with the loin tammer.                                 '' That is the best part'' I said,when we got home I knew what my dream was it was to become a performer in the Cicus and when i got older I had  to do it and I did I had lived my dream and it was amazing. Just always follow your dreams.

Item_Response: Being in the Circus       by: Taja Moore                When you go to the Circus you are there to enjoy yourself and have fun while your doing this have you ever thought to yourself if the acrobats,clowns, ringmaster, and plenty more have fun. You probally think that their jod isn't hard at all and that you can do all the tricks they can. Well these people risk there lives everyday doing dangerous stunts tricks and more to entertain the crowd. They have to work every minute of the day and they have have to be determined.       Part of being part of the circus is that you have to work hard at your trick and you have to be good at your talent you have to practice on your craft every single day because you can't go out there and be sloppy. As part of the Circus you also have to do chores like groom the horses, give them water, and also have to give them alot of care.     You have to balance out the time of your act with the ending of your act and you also have to own your act you must practice, practice, practice till your act is perfect. You must pay attention to what you do and more. You also have to make sacrafices like giving up your family time and more. You have to work alot of long hours and weekends as well.
