Item_Response: Hi my name is Jeffery Lienes. I am a elephant traner for the Salt Lake City circus. I am the traner for an elephant named Bungo. One day there was a terible accident that happend. This accedint involved Bungo and a very rude citizen. It was my first day on the job and I was out practicing when I was hit straight in the face.            It was a peanut! a peanut, then I heard some laughing in the stands. I looked up and saw a dad and a kid sitting there and laughing at me. The next thing I know the security comes and takes them away. I think to my self how rude that was.            then I hear some yelling coming from the security. next thing I know the dad and kid are in the same spot doing the same thing. Throwing peanuts at me and laughing. then I yelled and said security get these people out of here. The next thing I know I hear what sonds like a gun shot. Boom!             The kid has just been shot! what the heck is going on shouts another person whating for the show to start. Then Bungo starts getting scared. It is not good when Bungo gets scared because as you may know elephants are 20 times bigger than humans, and can do a lot of damage to a helpless citezen. then some of the other elephants start to get scared. the next thing I know Bungo is charging full speed at the stands.            Then the worst thing possible happens the rest of the crowd starts going bonkers. They are screaming, yelling, and shouting at each other to move out of the way. Then I hear it. CRASH!! The whole group of people over by the stands where the dad and kid were start screaming and crying in pain. The police come and they are forced to tranculize the elephant so that no one else gets heart.             And that my freinds is my story.                                                                                                     The End

Item_Response: Hi my name is Angela, I am a trapeze artist in the Wonder Circus. Right now myself and the rest of the crews and performers are pulling into our next location for our show!   When, we come to a stop the animals are unloaded right away by the trainers and the muscle men. Next, the tent is unloaded along with the stilts for the stilt/juggleing act. Lastly, the performers get to start getting ready for the show that night.     Now, that I can start my fun I get out my leatard and big box of makeup. First,I need to of course get on my outfit so later I won't mess up my makeup. Then, when I finish with my outfit I first need to put on my powder pink blush and my aqua mascera. Next, I put on the purple eyeliner, navy eyeshadow, and best of all my favroite light pink lipstick.     Once, I'm done I head to the pie car for a light dinner. So, once I reach the car everybody is already there talking and eating dinner. Then, when I get my food and start chowing down the food everybody is gone.     When, I finish and leave the cart the circus is about to begin so I rush to the tent and open the flaps just when they call my name to introduce me to the crowd. So, in I went to meet the anxious crowd!

Item_Response: Circus Life          My name is Aaron Rodgers. My family and I travel 20,000 miles in 7 months each year, visiting 150 cities. We work from sunup to sundown. Circus life is fun.          I wake up at 7:00 A.M.I go to the pie car for pancakes and bacon.Then we get ready for tonight's show by setting up tents, lights, and music. I schedule my day out. I go to school at 9:00 A.M. School ends at 3:00 P.M. From 3:00 to 3:30 I have a break.At 3:30 I do chores and practice. One of the things I am trying to master is leaping from a trampoline onto a horse's back.          Then, at 6:30 P.M. it's dinnertime.Our family does 10 shows a week. The show ends at 10:30. I get to bed at midnight. I am exhausted from the hard days work.           If you want to join the circus you need to have a specific talent, the right body type, and be very determined. You have to concentrate on dancing and performing. One good thing about being in the circus is that you get to travel around the world. One bad thing about it is that you miss your family.

Item_Response: A Wish Come True                                                                      by Nerveen Gerges         There is an eleven year old girl named Crystal Levine. She was very flexible and nice she also had a kind of spark to her face that made her look both pretty and mysterious at the same time. She has always wanted to visit the circus but her parents never let her because they didnt want her to be influenced and grow up to be a circus clown. They wanted her to have a nice and educated life so she could grow up to be a doctor.                  One day on her way home from school she saw a flyer taped to a post lamp. She couldn't believe her  eyes . It was a flyer that said there was a circus coming to the town of Buckross. That was the town she lived in . Right away ideas started flowing to her mind and she began thinking of ways she could go to the circus without her parents knowing . She ripped the flyer off the lamp and read the words printed in a small font at the bottom: Saturday October 18. Five dollars to get in she had 15 in savings.Later that day she went up to her room and started writing down the possibilities. That's it! She finally figured it out after after almost an hour. She looked at the flyer one more time it starts at 2:30. She would tell her parents that she had to go to study at that time until 7:30.                   Saturday morning finally came she told her parents at 1:45 until  that she was going to meet her friend at the library for a study session. They agreed and asked if she needed a ride. She reasoned with them until they agreed to let her ride her bike there. She almost forgot her back pack because if she went without it her parents would become suspicous  so she emptied out her back pack and got out her water bottle and some snacks. When she got there,there was a big man at the trailer door . She gave him 5 dollars and he let her in. She saw amazing stunts , acrobats, silly clowns, crazy jugglers, and even circus horses . The time got away from her as she watched with all her interest.          When she looked at her watch it was 6:45. Oh no! She told her parents that she would be home at 6:15 . She rushed home and and when she walked in her parents were sitting in the guest room waiting for her. They were very upset that she was late. They sent her to her room in anger. When she got to her room the guilt was eating at her gut. She went  downstairs and spilled her guts to her parents . She apologized as they stared at her in dissapointment and surprise. She felt terrible but better that she had told them everything. They gave her the same old speach and sent her up . She felt bad . But when she went to bed that night she dreamed that she was one of those acrobats swinging by ropes feeling as if she was flying happily.

Item_Response: One day, a person named  Saul found out that he wanted to be in the circus.  Saul knew that he had to go to circus school  and travel world wide and wake up early. So, he trained himself as hard as he could and when he went to join the circus of his dreams.They rejected him. Saul was sad, but then a person got fired from the circus and left mad. Saul heard the news and went to try it out to see if they wanted him. And they did. Saul was so happy and said'This is the happiest day of my life'! And so, Saul became famous and  more people started coming to see him more than the one that didn't except him.          They walked over to him and begged for him and Saul said 'You rejected me thought I was garbage and you think that I'm gonna go with  you guys?  How pathetic.  Noway I'm going with you guys.And so, they left all sad.' Saul was feeling great that he told  the people  that didn't except him.He knew that his dream has come true and that  he must've been the greatest entertainer in the world. This was  his time and knew that he had to take a break.             Now, Saul is retired from the circus, but now owns the one he used to work for.  He still makes a lot of money today and lives in Ontario, California. People still enjoy the circus even though Saul doesn't work as a entertainer.But they are glad that he took over as the owner of the circus he used to work for.  The circus though go nationwide it just stays in Ontario.  He might even make other circus's look cheap around the world.             Saul has inspired other people to join the circus.  Everybody around the world has been inspired by him. In Japan, China, Russia, Europe, Spain, and Germany. Saul, was so famous that when he was a  entertainer they showed it on tv everywhere. Thats why people know him around the world.  Saul, still to people everywhere around the world  is the best entertainer in the world.

Item_Response: There once was a boy called George who wanted to be in the circus but his parents wouldn't let him so he asked again and again but they said no every time.So the next day he packed his things and he ran away.When he was running away he went to the store to get food he got a lot and the store clerk asked why he got so much and he said that he was getting food for a party and then he went back outside and went walking down the street.                                                                                                                                                                                                                               Then he went to the train tracks and looked for a train to go on.Then he saw a train and he juped on and he was of but then it started to rain and he couldn't close the door so he went to the very back corner of the little train car.Then he fell asleep.Then he woke up and it was morning.Then the train stopped with a halt and he jumped off before he was seen by anyone.Then when he was done he started to walk away from the trains.         Then he walked over a hill and saw a big red and white tent and started to walk down the hill.When he got to the tent he asked a man who walked by if he could sign up.Then he got signed up and a couple of days he missed his mom and dad so he quit and walked back home and his mom and dad were so they never let him out of thier sight again.

Item_Response: This circus is great. I just saw Bob the clown juggle 8 balls. The horses just jumped up in the air, right before the elephants walked in. The elephants were dark gray and they had enormous ears. Then all of a sudden some of the acrobats swung across each other and they did the most amazing tricks. Some of the tricks were spinning in mid air and doing flips.        Then Bob the clown started juggling 10 balls. The acrobats caught them then started juggling them then they would grab the rope again. Then one man started walking on a tight rope. He was wearing a suit and he had a top hat. There were trains going around the building. This was an amazing circus.

Item_Response: Life as a circus performer is very hard work. I have to wake up at seven in the morning and go to school at nine and it ends at three. At three thirty I have to do chores and thakr care of the horses. I am in the progress of learning new tricks. My family is in the circus too. It is a family buisiness.         The show starts at seven and ends at ten. I am always tired after shows. I go to bed at twelve and think about the circus life. I think to myself, 'Why is this life to hard? It is a fun life and I'm tired so I am going to go to sleep.'. So i went to sleep.         I never thought I would be a circus performer. I was always the normal kid in school. How did this happen?I have always loved the circus that came to town twice a year. I just found out my uncle was a performer so I asked if i could join it, he asked his boss. After a day of waiting he said I could be in it! That was a long time ago though.         The good thing about the circus is that I get to travel around the world and sometimes see my friends at shows! I love how people look at me and say I am good at my job. I have learne to tell when people are impressed.         The bad thing about being in the circus is that it is very hard work! I travel alot and I am never home to see my other family. I work long days and I cant take a break or I won't be ready to perform. I have to work on weekends too, but this life is fun because some people do funny acts and it makes me laugh!

Item_Response: 'Get up everyone!', that is the normal sound I hear every morning. Life in the circus can have the upsides and its downsides. My trailor is medium size and its taken good care of. I get up each morning throw on some sweat and a t-shirt and head down to the pie car where we all eat. I sit at the table with all of my friends and watch the crew all set up for tonights performance. Me and my friends all talk about tonights performance. We get two hours to eat then we have to go to the schoolhouse. It's like any other school, we have computers, tests, and report cards. All through class I was thinking about tonights performance. We are in Austrailia tonight and it has been my dream to perform here ever since I joined the circus. As soon as I knew it class was over and we all left the schoolhouse. This is the time where me and mt friends have a fun time.            Sam, Emily, and me all run out and go play with the performers before we have to practice. We play with the juggling balls, the unicycle, which I am terrible at, and we play with the elephants. We all run over to the horses and feed them. I am in all the horse acts with Emily. Sam gets to go on the high blance beam. We all say goodbye and go practice. We all had to get ready for the big performance tonight.                Me and Emily are on the trampolines practicing our flips when the horses come over. We jump fromm the trampoline onto the horses back, we have to be concentrated and worry about our balance. We all tired after that! Me and Emily walk over to Sam where she is practicing her acrobatics. She is the best at them. We all decided that we should eat dinner together and get pumped up for the big show.                We all had to rush back to our trailors after dinner and get ready. The show was getting ready to start, this is my dream coming true. I knew my family was out in the crowd supporting me. The time came is was out performing. The best part is I get to perform with my best friend. I just feel like I am in a different world. That was the best feeling ever.           Tonights show was the best! I am wiped out though. I walked back to my trailor slowly. I took off my costumes and got on my pjs. I sat there thinking about the performance and how it was the best! I sat there thinking about my family until sleep came over me.

Item_Response: Hello, my name is Leah Stalwarts. I am in the circus, and it vary fun and exciting. The crew is like my family, my family lives in Idaho. I see them every few mouths and sometimes they will come and watch me preform. I am 21 years old, I finished school and went to collage for about 2 and a half years. Then i found out that I could do so much more. I bet your wondering why I just dident finish collage right? Well that's because my best friends uncle was in the circus and we went to see him pro forum. I was amazed at what i had just saw. I asked him if I could join but he said it wasent that easy. He made me train for 2 years before he would let me preform. So I worked long and hard before I could do what I really wanted and thats the tightrope. One of the haredset things known to man, walking on a thin long line was just as bout as close to impossible as you can get. After three long years I was able to pro forum.         As a circus prefourmer there's not a time that im not busy. Hers my morning routine-       feed lions at 6:00 am. practice from 6:30 to 7:30 am. clean cages at 8:30am  hang and make posters for are next show at 9:00am.   give all 5 show dogs a bath at 10:00 am       Every has there part. You have to do your chores like every other house hold only ares are a little bit more extreme.         We have a show every other mouth and in every mouth is a different place. We travel all across the world finding good spots to hold are circus.        Well that's just a small part of my big everyday life. As you can see we do a lot around here. We are always busy but we always have fun.                                                                                          -the end                       by-McKenzie L. Moore

Item_Response: Once,there was a guy named Micheal and he was in a circus group called ''The Funny Team'' and he liked his job at the circus,but one day,something unexpected happened while he was training  for tightrope walking.           When Micheal was training for tightrope walking,there was an earthquake and he lost his balanced and fell down really far and broke his right leg! He said that he needed for someone to take over while he was in the hospital.Then,his best friend Cody told him he would take over and then Cody sprung into action.           Cody was really worried. He didn't know a thing or two about circus acts or tightrope walking! Sarah,really perfect circus performer,taught him the basics.First,she taught him how to juggle bowling pins and other objects.He kept failling and failling and failling but then pretty soon he got the hang of it. Second, she taught him how to tame a lion and it was a piece of cake for him.Finally,she taught him how to balnce how to do tightrope walking and he was really worried on this part. After 3 tries, he finally manage to do it and then the circus was a sucsess and Micheal recovered from is injury an told Cody he did a great job and thanked him for filling in.               THE END

Item_Response: My Trip To The Circus                    By   Amareon Lucas                                                                                                                                                                          One Day I went to the circus.When I got to the circus went I got to choose a trailer and a circus act.The trailer I picked was a very cool trailer it had awosome things in it.Like a t.v., it had games.The circus act I picked was juggling.Also I practiced my act over and over again in tell I had it down.Then it was 10:30 pm I went to sleep. Then at 6:30 I woke back up and got dressed and eat breakfast.Then some people took me to get circus clothes.The clothes colors were red and black.                        Then, we had to go and practice or act.We were practicing for the show in five days.When we were done I went to my trailer and went to sleep.The next morning I took a shower.Also I got dressed brushed my teeth.And eat breakfast I ate cereal.Then I watched a little t.v.Also I played a game with a clown I met named gigles.In then he left later on to his trailer.Then I ate dinner and went to sleep.                         Last, I woke up it was the show today. I jumped in my clothes ate food and got ready for the day.Also I practiced today in tell it was almost time to go meet with the show.Everyone was there the first act was the clowns.After them it was the lion tamer.Then it was a  seal on a beach ball.Next it was my act I juggled balls.Also I juggled alot of steel horse shoes. my act was over.When my act was over the show was to.       To conclude, my trip to the circus was over.I went home I said goodbye to everyone and left I made it home.And that the end of my trip to the circus.

Item_Response: Life as a circus actor isn't all playing around and fun there are many things you have to do. Just like sports you have to pratice over and over and do the same thing in the circus. You start off with eating breakfest while your crew sets up things such as lights, and music for the upcoming show.                          After finishing up eating breakfest you will go to school, like any other school you have test, computers, and report cards. Many of your classmates may speak different languages you haven't heard because people come from all over the world. Your classmates may speak languages such as Italian, German, French, and spanish.                                            When school is over you get a quick break many people may start doing differnt things like juggle balls. Clowns might even ride their unicycles.                            Once it's almost time to start people practice or do chores. The trainer will feed, water, and groom all the animals for the act. While the trainer does that everyone else will be practicing what they will do at the act.                              Just a few hours away from the act people go to the pie car to eat dinner, since they are going to preforming that night most of them don't eat much. Some circuses will do usually 10 shows in one single week.                              Finally when the show is over everyone is tired and start to walk toward their trailer to go to sleep as they pass by they see the circus offices, concession stands, and stables.                               While this must sound fun they must continue on their tour without their family with them to support them and talk to them. So life as a circus actor isn't as easy as you think.

Item_Response: A Circus Life                                             by: Aaron Chavez               Hi my name is Maison, and I am going to tell you everything I know about the circus. First thing you should know is that your going to wake up at 7:00 A.M.,and get ready for breakfest.After breakfest your going to go help the crew set up the tents,lights, and music for tonight's show. 9:00 A.M. is school time. Theirs a one-room schoolhouse travels with you. Like any school, it has computers, test,and report cards.   Because the circus performers are from all over the world, many of the classmates speak other languages: French, Russian, and Italian.As you travel around the country, the geography lessons come alive. 3:00 P.M. school is over time for quik break. 3:30 P.M. dinnertime. your also going to do 10 shows a week: one each weekend , plus afternoon show on Wednesday, two on Saturday, and two on Sunday.10:30 P.M. The show is over.12:00 A.M. In bed.       As you can see, that the circus is fun, but it's a busy and tough life.

Item_Response: The  Circus                                                                                                                                                                  At 7: 00 A.M my alarm clock rings.I get dressed and go with my sister Elizabeth to the pie car. we get eggs,pancakes, and bacon.We sit down and talk to the performers in the circus.                   At 9:30 A.M we go to school, I see my friend Emily she's known as Glitter Girl beacuse she loves glitter and always throws it up in the air after her act. We are learning geography.                  At 3:00 P.M we get to do are own stuff. I play with my new born dog Teddy, play with Emily, and play with the clowns.We eat lunch I  get a sandwitch and a glass of water.                 At 3:30 P.M we start practicing are act. I'm  teaching Teddy to jump in a hula hoop.Emilyis a tightrope walker.The clowns are  practicing how to juggle and ride a unicycles.the acrobats are practicing thier flips.                 At 6:00 P.M is dinertime, we don't eat much beacuse of the show. We get fried chicken and baked patatos.I eat with Emily at the pie car when it's   dinertime.               At 10:00 P.M  it's time for the show the clowns are juggling on there unicycles, the trainers are working with their animals, the acrobats are doing their flips,the tightrope walker are spinning on their rope, and then it's me.Teddy is scared of all the people but he had to face his fears.Teddy looked at the hula hoop and he jump in the hula hoop,everyone cheered but teddy got more scared.                  At  12:00 A.M the show is over. I'm proud Teddy faced his fear but im so tired to do something special for him.He'll just have to wait till 7:00 A.M.

Item_Response: 'The Circus'                                                                                Its this time of year to go to the Bellini Circus!You can go and have tons of fun.If you go you can see the amazing clowns and there silly little cars and unicycles.And the acrobats and trapeze.They all love to perform and see the audience.But they spend alot of time away from home because they have to practice an get ready for there big shows.They also do ten shows a week one each weekday,and a maintime on Wednesday two on Saturday and two on Sunday.The circus is fun but is hard for them to do ten shows a week thats a tough life. Item_Response: The Big Circus Night                                                                                                                                    Hello,my name is Rob the Clown.I am the most funniest clown in town and in the circus.I live and work in the circus with Joe,he walks on the tight rope.Then there are the arcrobat brothers,Jhonny and Justin.They are professionals.They are very hard workers.Ethan is the circus juggler.Teddy has a magic act.Anyway, there is going to be a cricus show tonight.So we have to practice for opening night.Mary and Martin set up the tent.Jeff and Tony set up all the equipment that everybody needs for their acts.Casey has to guid all the animals out of the pen for his act.I am working on some funny jokes for my act.And i have to get used to my new mini car.Joe has to work n his balence on the rope.Jhonny and justin are planning and practicing some super high and crazy stunts in the air.Ethan is going to juggle torches,I tell him to be careful.Teddy is going to try to make two one headed bunnies in to one big two headed bunny.Casey is going to wrestle a tiger with a wodden chair.                       Everything is ready.We are now just making final adjustments to all of our acts.The ticket both is sold out.3...2...1...people start to come in the tent.Everyone is seated.All the seats are full.Everyone is ready to perform.                                    It looks like I am first.Istart to tell some funny jokes.Everyone starts to laugh.I start to drive my little car around.On purpose,I crash my car.I say ''looks like I have to take the unicycle''.''HA HA HA'' the crowd yells.The next act is from the acrobat brothers.The crowd was amazed of all the flips and tricks.''OOO,AHH'' the crowd yelled.The next act was Ethan on my unicycle juggling torches.''WOW'' the crowd yelled.Teddy was next.He did it,he acually turned two one headed bunnies into one big two headed bunny.''HOW DID HE DO THAT'' the crowd yelled.The last act was Casey wrestling a tiger with a wooden chair.The tiger obviously won the fight.''ENCORE,ENCORE''.the crowd cherred.That was the end of the opening cricus night. Item_Response: My Life in the Circus                    8:30 am I wake up, get dressed, and then go to my kitchen and make myself something to eat like: eggs, pancakes, or sometimes bacon. Next, I will go to the circus and get things ready so the circus crew can practice all their routines for the show.               10:00 am I will go to school. The school I go to is not a regular school. This school that travels with us for everyone who needs to be at school and is in the circus. Many of my classmates speak a lot of different languages like: Italian, Russian, and Spanish like my family.                3:30 pm School is over. Then, I will start heading to the circus and start practicing my juggling and acrobats. I really like my routines. They are so fun. But sometimes they are scary because I feel like I am going to fall.                 5:00 pm I will come home and eat dinner. I eat dinner with my family. Sometimes my family and I eat food like: hamburgers, tacos, and chicken. But we do not eat so much because we are performing. If we eat a lot on the night we are performing we might have an accident during the show. We do 5 shows a week: one Monday, Wednesday, Friday, Saturday, and Sunday.                 9:30 pm The show is over. I`m really tired. My family and I are going home. Two days from now we will have another show. Now I am home. I`m in bed thinking about my next show. I can`t wait until my next show. I really like my shows. They are really fun because I like to practice my juggling and acrobats.             10:00 pm I`m trying to go to sleep. But still thinking about when the tour is over. When our tour is over we will go back to our regular home in Hemet CA. When I grow up, will I still be a circus performer? Who knows? The circus is fun but tough.

After all, that was all over and it was another week to chang and we said we hope that natalie dose not act like that.When she came over here she said hi and we said hi back to her.She apolagiz and we acepted it.This time it was sofis turn to be the tightrop walker she said ooo no I am not doing that are you crazy then we got in anoter bid fight and we did not talk to each outher.Then when i got home i texed them and they texed me and they said I am not your friend any more and i sended that back to each of them. The last thing we all quit ower jobs we all ended up going to the seame job.The place was called the SPARCALING CIRCUS.We all had to work witheach outher nobody said a word.Natalie said hey gise i just wanted to say i am super sorry of what i did .Then all of us just said we are sorry to then we all huged it out. Item_Response: The life of a circus preformer                                                     By: Byron J. Guillot                                  George was 11 years old, and wanted to be a circus preformer when he grew up. He had talent and confidence, and knew he could do it some day. George could do flips and jumps like never before. He was simply a dare-devil. He was a very brave boy with very good reflexes. He saw a flier that read, ' We are looking for people with great talent that is confident and brave enough to be shot out of a canon! Join the circus today!' George kept the flier for years and years.            Years later, George was eighteen years old. He was at his beautiful, new house, unpacking the last box. When he unpacked that box, he saw the same flier that he had kept since he was 11. He had just remembered that he wanted to be a circus preformer. He went to the new contest to join, and showed his skills and bravery!            A week later, he got a note reading, 'Congrats! You won the contest to join the circus! Come to the same place as you did last time for the show tomorrow night. See you there!' George was very happy to hear this news, since it has been his dream for years! He finally got to his goal in life! George always knew that he had what it takes!            The night of the circus, George had to sign a contract in order to preform. When he went into the stadium, he was a little nervous. He was mostly amazed of all of the obsticals and animals. He warmed up and went into the stadium on a tight rope! When he got down from the rope, he got launched out of a canon, and hung his feet on the bars connected to the ceiling. George landed on an elephant, and rode it out of the stadium.            After the show, George was wiped out! He went into a trailor to sleep in while he is changing into pajamas and sleeping there. George knew that the show was great, and it amazed the crowd of people! He had a dream about what will happen in the next show.                       In the morning, George felt great. He went to the pie car for eggs and bacon. He also had orange juice to drink, because he didn't want to drink soda for breakfast. George was exited to go to the next show in Louisiana! It was far, but worth the long wait. He was just so exited about it though.            That night, he arrived in New Orleans, Louisiana. Another clown told George that they would be in a parade for Mardi Gras! He knew that Mardi Gras was a big holiday in the whole state! Alot of people were there for the parade to start. George was throwing necklaces and dabloons into the crowds from a float. After that, he started doing backflips in the very top of it! The parade was over, and George was even more tired than the last show. He did the same thing as he did at the end of the last show, and in the morning.            After George ate breakfast, he was ready to go back home for a while. When he got home, he was happy to have a job as a circus preformer, and loved it! He was wore out after every show, but he didn't care. The only thing he really cared about is accomplishing his dreams.

Item_Response: Life in the Circus                  I live in a trailor with my family, and others from the circus. in the mornings I do Just what any ordinary 10 year old girl may do. But overall my life is not ordinary!              Every morning when I wake up, I eat breakfeast, and get dressed to go to school. But I don't go to a reagular school. We have a one room school house in our trailer. That's where I go to school. Like any normal school we take test, and have grades, and report cards' and all that stuff. But unlike other schools ours is of course only one room, and it travels with us on the trailer. Also many of my classmates speak a forien language.            When school is over insted of going straight to homework, and chores like a normal girl would do I actually get a short break. During my break I juggle, and ride unicycles.             But, after that I have to do my chores. Some of my chores are things like taking care of the circus animals, and  helping get ready for our next show.              Once I am finished with my chores it is dinnner time. We must eat lightly or we will be to full to perform. Once we are finished we head down to tonights show.               I am exited tok watch the show, and know that someday I will be a part of that. But I am also exited to come home and get some sleep. Living life in the circus is both complecated and exiting. I hope that some day you will live your dream just like I am mine.

Item_Response: Jasper The Elephant                                      By: Jasper Keefauver                       I am Jasper the elephant.  Before the show starts and after the show,they let people ride on my back.  In the show I do a special trick, me and my fellow elephants stand up on our hind legs and balance a ball on our trunk and toss it to another elephant,until we get our ball back.  Another trick we do is stick our trunks into a bucket of water and stand on our hind legs and SQUIRT WATER EVERY WHERE.                          After the circus is over we load up and go to bed and we are at another city by the morning.We practice in the morning and all the way to when the show is about to start and people start to pile in.  I always want to make the little kids smile and be happy.                 We just love to make every body happy. I love what I do as an  elaphant.  Otherwise, I would be in Africa doing nothing not making anybody smile or laugh.  I would just be an elaphant.

Item_Response: Being a circus performer isn't an easy life. It actually is vary hard.You need to be good at a ton of things to be in the circus.You have to travel from place to place every few days, you have to practice a lot, and you have to every stunt well or else the crowd might leave the show.There are upsides and downsides.      Getting started as a clown isn't as easy as you think. You have to be determined and be in good shape. You also have to be good at performing and doing whatever you are asked to do.      Some upsides are that you get to travel the world performing circus acts. Some downsides are that you have to practice a lot, you spend a lot of time away from home, and you have to work long days.      It takes a lot of skill to be in the circus. You have to be good at doing lots of things. Plus you get to travel the world performing.   Being a circus performer isn't easy to do.

Item_Response: THE LIFE OF CIRCUS       I'v got to go to school and travel a lot.The only time I ever get to see my family is when I performe in flordia.I really miss my home and friends.       Being in the circus isn't as easy as it looks.I'd like to be in a sport but where never in one place.If im not traveling then im practicing or at school.       Theres only three other kids in the circus so I dont really have any friends in the circus.I performe with my Uncle.Im working on being an acrobat.Thats what I wanted to be before I came here,but they said I had to be twelve im only eleven.       I wanted to quit the circus,but im only one year away from becoming an acrobat.The reason why I wanted to quit was because I have to in a pie car, never get to see my friends or family and I have to travel so much.       I have to live in a trailer with my Uncle.Every breakfast,lunch ,and dinner I have eat in a pie car,but the worst thing is,is that I only go to school two days a week.This circus stuff is really wearing me out. Item_Response: Calypso   This is a story about a black, talented, and sweet horse who grew up in the Circus and became the star of the show.                               Hello I'm Calypso, an Arabian Circus horse born with an attitude. When I came into the world it was in the middle of the Circus. My mother who was pregnant had such cruel care givers that they didn't notice that she was pregnant until in the middle of a show she gave birth to me. Some little 11 year old girl ran from the stands and helped my mother with everything. Now that little girl is my owner and she is not so little anymore. She is now 22 and her name is Brooklyn. Brooklyn and I are the stars of the show in the Barnum and Bailey Circus. Our signature move is when Brooklyn is standing on my back while I'm loping and I jump a 5 ft fire lit pole and we make it every time because we trust eachother so much. When she is on me she becomes part of me. It is just so magnificent. Well anyway today we were doing our signature trick and the pole was not balanced right so the pole fell right of when I jumped over. Before we knew it the whole tent was on fire. Brooklyn ran me outside and when everyone else ran all over the place  Brooklyn called the Fire Depatment. Then she ran back into the tent and sprinted back out with as many animals or animal halters with an animal atached to the end as she could. She raced in and out until everyone and every animal was out of the burning tent. She went in to take one last look around and thats when a beam that held the tent up fell directly on her. She was screaming for help. I raced in there as fast as I could and pushed and pushed until the beam was off Brooklyn. Then I helped hr onto my back and carried her all the way to the hospital. She turned out all right but if I had not gotten the beam off of her that fast she would of died. When we got back to the Circus the fire was put out and I was known as the horse her saved her owners life.                                              The End

Item_Response: THE DAY OF THE CIRCUS                                    BY : MONIQUE LOPEZ                     Today is the day of the circus,at the circus I'm going to do        the best part?First, I'm going to do somersaults off a running horse,Second, I'm going to juggle,Then,I'm going to be an acrobat.It's going to be so much fun!.But there's one HUGE problem,I'm stage fright.How am i supposed to make it through the whole show?I'm ruined!.Everything is going to be a disaster and what if the audience laugh's at me ? Everyone cheered for me i had so much fun.For now on i will always perform.                                                 THE END

Item_Response: Life In The Circus                      A lot of stuff happepens in the circus. You have to eat right and stay in shape. It is hard to be in the circus as hard work as they work if you had to do the thing they do. They have to walk on ropes, breathe fire, and a lot of hard thing that you would not even thing of doing I hope. THere is a lot of bad thing about the circus too. You have to have long trips, wake up early, and a lot to do.             Why I think it is hard to stay in shape is because if you dont eat alot you will be hungry if you eat alot then you will be full before a shoe. What do you do in that case. Staying in shape is hard but not that hard. You just need to work out and go to that gym. But that is two reasons why being in the circus is har and not fun to be in.            My other reason why it is fun to be in the circus is because you get to walk on some ropes. It might be dangerous but it might be fun. Most trapeze preformers have a net below the rope if they fall. Some trapeze preformers think that they are so good that they dont need a net but if they fall they are not good anymore.            Other reason why it is fun to be in the circus is that you get to breathe out fire if you are the fire eater or something like that. I dont know how they do that but they get a big long stick with fire on it and puy it in there mouth. That is so cool and dangerous alot of poeple think that is cool why I don't know. That is my other reason why bering in the circus is fun.            My othe reason why it is fun to be in the circus is because you get to do a lot of stuff that you don't see everyday. People practice a lot of how you stuff that is fun nd cool. You should thank people if you go to the circus because they but a lot of work in to it. Please it is not easy to but fire down you mouth, or walk on thin ropes and if you think it is than try.That was my last reason why the circus is fun and some reason why it is not fun.            I would love to be in a circus but I have to be more.

Item_Response: The Jiggly-Doo Circus       Bella Wakefield just woke up after a long, tiring day. She had   just started the circus life. Bella woke up to the loud noise of horses running around. She had slept at the Jiggly-Doo Circus! Bella quickly went to the trailer, changed her clothes, and did her hair. She was ready to practice at the Jiggly-Doo Circus. Her father was training the lions to jump through a ring of fire. Her mother was doing gymnastics. Bella's job was to do tricks on a horse.           The next circus show was going to start in a couple of hours.   All of the performers were practicing their hardest because the mayor of the town was going to watch. It was very loud in the Jiggly-Doo Circus because all the performers were there. Bella was so nervous that she did not even feel like practicing. It was hard to work in a circus, for Bella, because none of her friends were with her. She did not have anyone to talk to nor did she have anyone to play with.       The circus was going to start in a couple of minutes. The circus   manager came in with a worried look on his face. 'Bella Wakefield, you're going to have to walk on the tightrope. Our tightrope walker went home, sick.' Bella wanted to burst into tears because she did not know how to walk on a tightrope. Finally, her father said,' Don't worry, Bella. If you think you can do it, you know you can do it.' Bella was comforted by this and stood headstrong. The Jiggly-Doo Circus was off to a great start. The host, Jim West, welcomed everybody with a warm smile. Bella was going to walk on the tightrope.

Item_Response: My Circus Life                     Hello, my name is Miranda Gomez. I work in the amazing circus called THE EXTRAVAGANZA. I started working there when I was only a little girl. People may think that working in a circus is fun, and that you get to play around all the time. But no, it's not like that. If you want to be in a circus, remember there is a whole lot of work ahead of you. But at the same time, it is not torture.                              Everyday, I wake up at 7:00 A.M. I get ready, and go to the pie car for breakfast. Today is the big show, so the crew is getting everything ready. Then, at 9:00 A.M. it's school time. We have a tiny one-room schoolhouse that travels with us. We have all the advantages that a normal school would have such as, computer, tests, report cards, etc. My classmates are from all over the world, so we experience many different languages. As we travel around the country, our geography lessons come alive.               At 3:00, school is finally over. I get to play with my little dog, Brownie. We are not allowed to keep big dogs because of our miniature trailer. Later, at 3:30 P.M. I do my chores like, grooming, feeding the animals for tonight's show. My parents are practicing their solo act. My dad is going to somersault off a running horse, and my mom is going to walk a tightrope. I am going to train animals to do tricks. At 6:30, we eat our dinner. Finally, it is time for the show!               It is 10:45, and the show is over. I am exhausted. Then, at 12:00, I am ready to sleep. Every show night, I go to sleep thinking that two days from now I will have to do another show.               As you can see, my life is not only fun, but tough. My life is a circus!

Item_Response: The Life of a Circus Performer                                I hear the claps and cheers from the crowd as I finish jumping through the hoop of fire. I am Emma, the tightrope walker. As a circus performer, we do many different jobs. For example, you may be wondering, why is a tightrope walker jumping through a hoop of fire? Well, that is why I am going to take you on a journey to see what a circus performer does and how I got interested in being one.                     First, in a circus, you have to be and early bird because we sleep at  12:00 and we have to wake up at 7:00. In a typical day, I go to the pie car, go to school, have some free time, have dinner, and have a circus performance. After all my shows I am wiped out! As a tightrope walker, it takes a lot of balance and concentration, so I have to practice five hours everyday!                     Next, let me tell you how I got interested in being a  tightrope walker. When I was young, I had a habit of balancing myself and walking on the terrace. My whole family performed in circuses, but I was too young to start performing. But, when the day came, I showed the crowd what my talent was, walking on a tightrope. Later, it was said, I was going to be the tightrope walker for all my shows.                    Lastly, as I got older, my dad told me that I was old enough to do different stunts, not only the tightrope walk. You may be wondering, is'nt it hard doing different performances at once? Yes, it is very hard, but being in the circus meant a lot of training and I wanted to win my dream and be a circus performer. There are many ups and downs of being a circus performer, but I don't want to let down my family and quit the circus.                    Today is my last show and I want to show the world who I really am. Today, I am walking on the tightrope, getting shot out of a canon, and jumping through a hoop of fire. As I walk on the tightrope step by step, I see the crowd staring at me in astoshment as I jumping off the tightrope and land perfectly in the canon. I get shot and make an amazing flip through the hoop of fire. I was the star of the show. As you can see, being a circus performer means a lot of hard work in order to accomplish your goals.

Item_Response: The Circus Mystery            Glurp Glurp Glurp. The pie car doesn't have the best food, but it is the best you will get around here. I then heard a scream when I was in the middle of biting my bacon. I ran to the tent to see our show host looking at the broken leopard cage. I then saw a shade of blue on the lock. All of the circus performers then walked out of the tent to find the leopard. I then met up with my close friend Puly, which is his obvious nickname. He is always bugging me about not having a pet and always about his nails. This might seem odd, but his favorite hobby is painting his nails blue. He paints a different shade every day. Other than that, he is a pretty cool person.            We were both looking for the leopard together, but he wasn't that worried or paying much attention. But whenever i got near his trailer, he would wonder off another way as if he didn't want me near his trailer. I probably figured it was because that was where he kept his nail polish stashed. And since he is always braging about it, he might think that I am jealous and I want some. That's when I relized were the leopard went. God, icould notice that shade of blue any where by now. I felt dumb not knowing that it was him.            I then aproached Puly and dragged him to his trailer and kicked the door open. The leopard was found.

Item_Response: Life at a Circus          Being in the circus is not fun and games.If you asked Bella Castini she would say it is not She works from sunup to sundown she works ten days a week and sometimes works from 7:00 to 12:00 midnight.      Being in the circus has it"s upsides and it"s downsides. The upsides of being in the circus are that you get a chance to travel around the world, and you get to meet people from all over the planet.The downsides are that circus workers work long days and spend a lot of time away from home.this is what one circus performer thought:“On tour, you  don"t really have anywhere to call home and you're always thinking about that night"s show.I miss my home and garden and I don"t see my family.You have to work long hours and weekends as well.”       If you work in the circus you would only get 7 hours of sleep if you had Bella"s schedule.I would not want to be in the circus because I do not want to be traveling.I am not the kind of person who likes long trips.       Being in the circus doesn't look that bad because I like animals. So if I were to work in the circus I wold like to be working with :       Lions Tigers Chimpanzees Horses Elephants Leopards           Being in the circus could also be fun because you can do cool tricks like:       being a circus juggler being a circus tightrope walker being a circus acrobat           Being a circus performer is fun but it can be can be hard work.                  Becoming a Circus performer               Not just anyone can be a circus performer.You need to have the right body type ,be determined ,and have a specific talent.For example, Phillippa did musical theatre, ballet, music, singing, and acting when she was five years old.then when she was eleven, she knew that she wanted to be a performer .She then gave up everything and concentrated on dancing and performing.

Item_Response: The Circus Boy            There once was a very poor boy. He had no money and didn't have any parents. One day while he was begging for money and food, he saw a poster. The poster said that the circus needed one more person to start performing. The boy was excited about the offer, but he was also worried. He always wanted to be a juggler, but he couldn't juggle.            Then he decided to go to the circus and see how the professionals juggled. He took two bottles from the dumpster and decided to juggle the way the professional did. It was very hard and he couldn't keep the bottles in the air for ten seconds. He tried again and again, but couldn't seem to improve. He wanted to quit, but he would rather keep trying than go back to the dumpster. He practiced in the circus for weeks and weeks. Finally he got the hang of two bottles and then started adding more. After a month of practicing, he decided to juggle in the circus. He went to the circus owner and showed him how he could juggle. He was very tensed and couldn't keep the bottles in the air.            Then he decided to leave when the owner said that he could be a clown. That seemed to be a good idea at that time. He messed up a lot, but that was what made that funny. He was hired to be a clown and, if he could improve juggling, he could be a juggler too.             It was the day to perform everybody was waiting for my tricks, and it was very funny.             These days, you can still see him in the circus. He is a famous juggler and a clown. He sometimes says that life in the circus is hard, but he likes it a lot better than the dumpster.

Item_Response: It is 7:00 A.M. I wake up rubbing my eyes. I looked around. I was in my trailer. You see, I work at a circus and we constantly travel. So, we live in these. A thought was nagging me at the back of my mind. I knew it was important, but I just couldn't place it.            Suddenly, my mom, in her acrobat's suit jumped into my room. 'Get up, you need to have a good breakfast, so you will energy to parctice for tonight!' Tonight, I thought. What was tonight? But, I sat up groggily and changed out of my pajamas.            I went to the pie car and grabbed a bagel. I ate it slowly, still not fully awake. After that I went to school. Today, I had a test. Was that what I forgot? No, my mom said tonight.            At 3:30 I went to take care of and train the animals. I saw my friend Annie waiting or me. We both trained the animals but I had to do the acts on stage. 'I suppose you know what to do for tonight,' she said. There it was again. Tonight.  What was so important that happened tonight? 'Uh, I guess so,' I replied. I started handing out meat for the tigers. They ate happily.            At dinner everyone was a little nervous.They didn't eat much. But I took a baked potato and slice of pizza with fries on the side. I sat down at the table my mom was sitting at. 'Why are you eating so much?' she asked. 'Is there something wrong with that?' I wondered. 'Yes, tonight is the biggest show of the year.' she hissed. I gasped. How could I forget that? I only ate my slice of pizza and ran off to practice even more.           Before I knew it, show time came. I ran on to the stage for my part and did my acts: jumping from a diving board, twirling in the air, and landing on a circus elephant. I did it. The crowd roared in approval. After that everyone clapped me on the back saying I did great. I was a little uncomfortable with all the attentinon, but I was still glad. The day had ended on a happy note.

Item_Response: Hi, I'm Christine, and I am a circus performer. I joined the circus when I was eight, and now I am ten. I haven't been home in a long time, and I really miss my family. But sometimes, when I am performing, I know my family is watching me on T.V. But on the bright side, I have made many good friends in the circus. My life is busy, busy, busy. We visit a lot of cities every week to perform. The act I am now learning is very dangerous. I am practicing how to juggle knives.       I have always wanted to be on a basketball team, but we don't have time. We do have school though, our classroom is full of people who speaks languages that I don't understand because, they are different people from around the world. It is really fun to travel as we can really see what the teacher was talking about in the geography lesson.       Becoming a circus performer takes a lot of practice and skill. Everybody has always asked me, 'What did you always want to do in a circus?' I would always reply, 'A circus acrobat.'

Item_Response: 'Honk!' What is that sound? It's an elephant of course. We are   at a circus after all. My name is Emily Johnson , and my family is at the circus. It will be in our town for the next three days. When my brother, David, and I found out that we were going to the circus, we were both ecstatic. In fact, I want to be a circus performer when I grow up. We got into the car and drove until we reached the circus. Once we are inside, we sit down in our seats and wait for the performance to start. It is noisy , and everyone is anxious to see the trapeze artists, the acrobats, and all of the animals.   At last, the performance begins, and everyone is suddenly   silent. The music starts and we see the animals start to file out. There are elephants, horses, monkeys, and many more. They are all doing tricks with their trainers. We all watch in awe as the trapeze artists and tightrope walkers start their peformance. Next come the acrobats. It must take balance, hard work, and concentration to be a circus performer. Before I know it, the performance is over.   We are led to the back where we are informed that we have the   lucky seat numbers and that we are allowed to meet the circus performers. Because I am interested the most by the tightrope walkers, I ask to meet them. When I ask them how they decided to become a circus performer, one replies. 'I knew that I wanted to be a performer at a young age. You just have to go for it and give everything else up.' she says. 'Is it fun to travel around a lot?' I ask. 'Yes, because we get to travel the world, go to so many places, and meet different people that all enjoy watching us perform. However, we sometimes miss our family and our home. When we are performing we have to move constantly. We also work from sunup to sundown.' another circus performer says.   Before, I wanted to be a circus performer when I grew up. Now,   I know that circus life is fun but also has its downsides. They experience the joy of performing in front of a live audience, and get to travel to many places, performing tricks. However, they have to travel often, work from sunup to sundown, and give up everything else. For now, I'll just settle for watching the circus performance instead.

Item_Response: My name is Callia Catini. I am a trapeze artist. I wake up at 7:00 AM sharp and eat breakfast in the pie car, it is a trailer where we eat. While then the crew gets the tent ready. It is huge. Now it is 9:00, time for school. My school is a small room where there are computers, desks, and a teacher that travels with us. There are children who speak Russian, Italian, and French. Now I look outside and I see the geograhy lesson in real life.                      Now it is 3:00 school is out for today. I go and groom a horse. My father calls to me he says,' I finally figured out how to do a handstand on a ball while holding rings with my feet.' I say great and go and practice my trick. It is doing a juggling act on a tightrope. I fall but luckly there is a net under me. My mother is practicing tricks with a lepord. Them suddenly I hear someone saying,' Callia. Can you help me here.' Right a way I knew that was my mother. I raced to her. I thought she was in danger because of the lepord but to my suprise the lepord sat down and wouldn't get up. I helped my mom and went back to my practice.      Now it is time for the show I was nervous but my mom said,'I  don't think there is anything to worry about Callia. You did great in your practice and you will do great in this show too.' So I did do great in my show and my mom and dad had no trouble at all.

Item_Response: I am a circus performer. I know that many people think circus actors live a fun and easy life, but that is not true. There are both upsides and downsides to living in a circus.            As a circus performer, I get a chance to travel around the world and visit many places. But I work from sunup to sundown and spend a lot of time away from home. If you decide to work in a circus, you need to have a specific talent, the right body type and be very determined. Not everyone can become and acrobat or a trapeze artist.            You have to wake up early and live in a train most of the time. You might need to learn to understand many different languages because circus performers come from all around the world.            To be a circus actor, you need to have patience, balance, and concentration. The stunts might seem a bit dangerous. You might be bitten by a lion or a tiger. You might crack your skull somersaulting off a running horse of leaping from a trampoline onto a running horse.            In a circus, you have to perform every day and usually 10 times a week.            So now you see what hard work it is to be in a circus. You might change your mind now about wanting to perform in a circus.

Item_Response: ~Life in the Circus~       Have you ever dreamt of joinning the circus? How it would always be fun? Well, sadly, its not all fun and games. It takes talent, practice, and deteramnation . I know becaus I, myself am in the cricus       Well I wake up about 7:00 am, and go to the pie car to eat with all the other performers as the crew prepares lights, tents, and music. After I eat I head to the school house. Its like a normal school. There are kids from all over the world that are in the circus so many can speak other laungues.       Schools over and its about 3:00 pm now. I get to rest for 30 mintues before I began my chores and start practicing.I only have 3 hours untill I eat dinner then go to the show.      About 4 hours of working, i go back to the trailer and get ready for bed.      The circus is fun, but its a busy and hard life. You must have talent, a certain body type, be very determined, and have great focus.       Not all the circus is bad, there are upsides, like getting to travel the world and meeting new people and learning new cultures.       So, do you have what it takes to join the circus?

I tame various animals, from lions to bears, but that is not my whole life. I miss my sister Kate from time to time, and i dont get to visit her much bit I dont have the time anyways! Item_Response: Hi, my name is Gwendolyn. I have been part of the circus for as long as I can remember. My father is the ringmaster, my mother is the trapeze artist, my brother is a clown, and I am an acrobatist. I have been to every state in America at least once, and I have been to Japan, Turkey, Costa Rica, and Italy for a world tour.   Most people think that being in a circus would be the best thing ever, but it isn't. I have to wake up a 6:30 every morning, eat a quick, light breakfast, go do a few hours of school, then go and practice my act until lunch at 11:45. After lunch, I do my chores and help anyone who needs help with something. Then I do an hour or two of more practice, and then it's time for the show. We do two shows each night (sometimes three) and always three on Saturday and Sunday too. Another bad thing about circus life is accidents. I lost concentration a few years ago on an act, and I fell and broke my leg, a rib, and my wrist. One year, my dad also lost three fingers when a lion got too excited. There have been other accidents too, but those we're the worst.

Item_Response: The Circus life dream         Hi. I'm Angkitha. I'm an animal trainer at the Great American Adventure circus. We circus folks travel many places each day. We have a tight schedule for were we travel and what time we have to leave.             Being in the circus is not easy. You will have to wake up at atleast 5:30 in the morning and work all the way until 9:00 in the night. In the morning you will have to wake up and eat your breakfast. Afternoon you will have to get ready for the show. After the show is done, you go to the trailer and get a good night's sleep and wake up in the morning at a new place.            Many people do not join the circus because they think it is a crazy place with no fun. Well, I can assure you that they are absolutely wrong. The circus is a very fun place for people and it is NOT crazy. You will experience the job of your lifetime! You won't regret it if you join!             To have a circus job you will have to be talented and determined.   If you want to be a tightrope walker you will have to maintain a good balance. To be animal trainer like me you will have to work well with animals and be willing to take care of them. To be an animal handler you will have to be neat and be willing to walk the animals back to their cages.            Their is also a pie car, a place were the circus people eat. You can be a cook in the pie car. In the show, many people will come to see you, whatever job you have. Make sure to do your best and smile!

Item_Response: Circus Life           Welcome. I am going to introduce you to my amazing yet tough circus life.            Early in the morning at 7:00 A.M. I wake up and go eat breakfast. In the pie car, I eat bacon and pancakes everyday. You may think that is luxurious but it gets boring after a while. Then I go to school at 9:00 A.M. like every other kid. Just because I live in a circus, doesn't mean I can skip school. Class is in one big schoolhouse that travels with us wherever we go. Parents may be thinking that kids won't learn as much, but the truth is, we all learn the samethings even if the schoolhouse is portable. We also get tests and report cards like everyone else.            School ends at 3:00 P.M. Then, we get a quick break for about 30 minutes. Then, we have to practice for 3 hours. Some people would practice juggling and others would practice aerobatics. At 6:30 P.M. I would eat dinner. I don't want to eat too much because I might vomit while performing. When performing, you think about all the practice you have done and say to yourself,'I cannot fail,' as you do your amazing trick. Once the performance is done you feel proud as the audience gives you a standing ovation, amazed of what everyone thought about the circus.            At 10:30 P.M. the circus is over. You feel very tired and you are ready to hit the hay. At midnight, you go to bed thinking about your family wishing you could meet them or even call them.

Item_Response: It is 7:00 and my dad knocks on the door of my trailer. Yes, trailer. I live in a circus, doing acrobatics and horse-stunts. I was probably destined to be a horse-stunter, as my dad is the ringmaster. As for acrobatics, I'm like a rubberband- elastic. I am so flexible that one could twist me into a pretzel. Hi, I'm Yvonne Lutz, your average 11-year-old circus performer. I always wake up this early, so I'm so used to it, I don't even stretch anymore. I get dressed, brush my teeth, and go to the pie cart for breakfast. The pie cart is like a dining hall, except it is a moving dining hall. As usual, on the menu is pancakes and bacon. I eat up quickly so that I have time to rest before school at 9:00.                It is school time now.We only have one room, and like the pie cart, it is a moving school. My classmates all speak different languages from all over the world. I am French. We all get to learn about our lessons like history and geography hands-on, because as we move around, we get to experience many places with a wide range of historical and geographical views. Today we learn about Hopi Indians, as we are in Arizona, quite near to the Grand Canyon. We even get to see a medley of varieties of Hopi dances. Girls my age and even younger dance intricate foot patterns in noisy dresses. Noisy because they have shells that clang together, and as in loud, like gaudy. We go on a short one hour round-trip hike down into the canyon, learing about different plants we had never seen or heard of before, and their needs, adaptation, survival skills, and habitat, going deeper into it than 'desert' or 'canyon' or 'hot weather climate area.'                Now school is over at 3:00, and I can take a half hour break to let loose. This is when I write. I have a diary and a journal. I record the events that occur daily and school notes in my journal, why my diary holds my feelings, like my on-and-off hate for this hectic life. Sometimes I feel like I am going to explode.                 It is 3:30 now. Break time is over. I have to do chores and practice. My favorite routines are the trapeze, tightrope walk, and anything to do with horses catches my fancy as long as I get to ride in the routine. And sometimes, the stunts don't involve riding. I practice crazy stunts on galloping horses, and many dangerous acrobatics like the tightrope. Sometimes I lose my balance and fall into the net that is not very far down. I only stunt when there is a safety feature involved. I never mess up in a show, luckily. That would be extremely embarassing. I pratice for three hours so that everything is perfect for the show. After I practice, I quickly try on my costumes before dinner. My acrobatics outfit is a neon sequined head-to-toe suit. It is cross-hatched metallic pink, bright yellow, electric blue, neon orange, and a neon or metallic version of almost every color of the rainbow. There is an argyle pattern of red-orange, yellow-green, blue-purple, and pink-purple. Clear and silver sequins dot the entire thing. It is like feety pajamas in style. But it is tight on the body, and flexible, too. The back of it also extends above the neck, grasping tightly to the shape of my body until halfway up my head, where it flares out. A Marti-Gras type mask, patterned the same as my suit is attached, perfectly fitting my face. My horse-stunting cosume is the same pattern, but with different colors, like a sparkly black, white, cream, tan, and peach, and for the argyle print a metallic mahogany, cadet blue, cerulian, and mauve. The style is breeches, with a silk button down shirt and a velvet coat with a pea-coat collar. The helmet, I wear none of. That is just more of the danger, and to add on, my boots, patterned just as my riding clothes, are high heeled. They are knee-high, and cut off in triangle shapes on the two sides, the cut-outs about four inches deep. I stare at them in awe, as they are lovely. I am a colorful person, and therefore love them both, but the acrobatics outfit to a higher extent.                It is 6:30. I have a light dinner, and then go to the Big Top to perform, as that is the tent for the major acts. I perform, always nervous yet excited, and think about how amazingly I did in practice, and my confidence soars. As I finish my routine for the millionth- and last- time this night, I wipe the sweat of my face and smile, taking a bow with the rest of the crew.                 Wow! It was a long show as usual, but I'm always surprised by how long it is. It is now 10:30, and the show is over. I walk back to my trailer as slowly as a slug, as I am really tired. Once I get back, I brush my teeth and change.                  Now it is around 12:00. It is really late, and I pretty much collapse into my bed, falling asleep before the sheets even settle down.

Item_Response: WHAT   HAPPENS   IN  THE  CIRCUS                                                                                                                                                                                                            Many   things   happen  in  the  circus.  If  you  want  to  join  the   circus  you  must    have   a   lot  of   potion  for  what  you   want  to  do. You  also  have to  have       talent.some  people  enter  the  circus  with  out  talent  , but  they practice  and   practice  until  they  are  experts  on  what  they  are  doing  . Some  people think  that  working  in  a  circus  is  humiliating  and  embarrassing.The  people that  work  there  don't  think    that  way.Some  people  work  in  the  circus  because  they  need   money.                                                                                                                                                        Let  me   introduce     my  self   my  name  is  Rosaline  my   family   works  in  the   circus.My parents  decided to  work  at the  circus  because  they  needed  money. My  parents  also  work  in  different  places  we  travel  all  over  the  world.Now  they  don't  have  to   take  me  to  school  so  early  in  the  morning.Our  school  is  a  little   different from  the   normal   schools .Our  school  is  a room  like  a  house.  We   also    get  report cards  .                                                                                              ?                                                                                                                                                                  People  in  the   circus  have  different  jobs . Some  people  are  the  ones  who  preform.Other people take  care  of  the  animals.Some  people  build the  tent  and  then    bring  it  down.Some  people  cook breakfast and  dinner .There are  lots  of  different    jobs.                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                 Almost  all  of  the   people  that  work  in  our  circus  are  our  relatives.The  only  person  that  does  not  work in the the  circus  are  like  20  of   them .  My  mothers  family  is  really  big.My  fathers  family is  not  to  small  and  not  to   big   either.We   also  have  people  that  are  not  part  of  our  family,but  most  of them  are  .                                                                                                                                                                 We  also  have  people  that  speak  different  languages.Some  speak   Italian  ,french,Russian. My family   speaks  french. Me  and my  family  learned  how  to  speak    Spanish  and  other  languages  too.We  learned  different  languages  because  we  travel  almost  every were.                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                    Some  of  the  tools  we  use  are   a   one  wheel  bicycle.juggling  balls.We  also  use  animals  to  do  acts  like  for  example:horses,seals,elephants.some  acts  we  do   are  juggling  while  riding  a  one  wheel  bicycle.We  also do  acrobats  .                                                                                                                                                                                  We  perform   all  weekend   and   months  we  always  work  .  When  we  finish   our  acts  we  eat dinner  and  wake  up  the  other  day   and  it is the  same  routine.         We also  have  chores .We eat  on   a   pie  car  a  pie  car  is   where  circus  performers  eat.                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                          Circus  acts  may  look  easy  for  some people   but  for  some  people  they  think    they  are  hard  .  The  circus  is  really  tough  . When  you  do  an  act  you  get  wiped  out . especially me  because  I  do   the  acrobats.
